ExtendedComments: Continued to work on 2nd pass and 3rd pass. Production was lower due to delays and dig face is low due to small coverage. 3rd Pass had better CYWH in the beginning since there was more sand than clay. 2nd Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 24'. 3rd Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 32' LM took 3' steps after clogging cutter for the 2nd time. No issues with clogging after bars cut off. Starboard swing ranges vary for inbound.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Compl. 3rd pass. Start on 1st pass on south slope. Good coverage.
ExtendedComments: Continued to work on 3rd pass on north slope then moved to south slope in AS4. TE was low because the starboard swing wire broke and the dredge moved twice to change cuts. 3rd pass and 1st pass had similar production even though there was more clay in the 3rd pass but the LM covered alot of area . 3rd Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 32'. 1st Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 18'. North slope had starboard swing range vary while the south slope had port swing range vary.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 2nd pass. Start on 3rd pass. High coverage but low face.
ExtendedComments: Continued to work on 2nd and 3rd pass in the south slope. 2nd pass had higher production since there was less clay material in that pass. CYWH was higher than estimate since there was alot of area covered although the dig face was lower than expected due to the material in the passes. 2nd Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 24'. 3rd Pass: 3' steps in each corner with a BOS at 32'. South slope had the port swing range vary.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Compl. 3rd pass. Pulled back for 4th pass. Good Coverage.
ExtendedComments: Finished 3rd pass in the south slope. 4th pass was started . CYWH was beating estimate due to the area covered with the 4th pass. Dig face is low since the material has more clay but the cut width is large for the 4th pass which allows for production to be higher than the slope areas of AS4. 3rd Pass: 3' steps in each corner with a BOS at 32'. 4th Pass: 3' steps in each corner with a BOS at 39' but changed to 4' steps because LM said the density stayed the same. South slope had the port swing range vary.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Compl 4th pass. 142 pin keeper broke & new one welded on. Moved to AS3.
ExtendedComments: Finished the 4th pass inbound. Dredge will begin on 1st pass outbound on north slope. High coverage rate due to LM taking 4' steps instead of 3' steps which increased CYWH. Low available face due to the clay material in the pass. 4th Pass: 3' steps in each corner with a BOS at 39' but LM said the density was staying consistent so they decided to take bigger steps.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Compl 1st pass. Digging 2nd pass. High coverage & cywh. Good TE.
ExtendedComments: Finished the 1st pass on the north slope and continued digging the 2nd pass. High coverage rate due to LM taking 4' steps instead of 3' steps which increased CYWH. High production due to available dig face. TE beats estimate because there were few delays. 1st Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 23.5'. 2nd Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 33'. North slope had the port swing range vary.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Compl 2nd pass n.slope1st pass s.slope.On 2nd pass s.slope.Fixed suct elbow pipe.
ExtendedComments: Finished 2nd pass on north slope and continued digging 1st2nd pass. High coverage rate due to LM taking 4' steps instead of 3' steps which increased production. CYWH was lower because 2nd pass on south slope had low dig face. TE was lower because we had to pull back three times to do passes. 1st Pass on N. slope: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 23.5' (Port swing vary). S.Slope:1st Pass 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 24'. 2nd Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 33' (Stbd swing vary)

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Rock entering Main Pump when digging main channel at 40'. Moved back to N slope
ExtendedComments: Attempted to dig Main Channel at 40'. Rock was encountered and kept getting in the main pump instead of changing cutters the decision was made to continue digging material on the North Slope of AS-3. Had to dig around channel marker on North Slope cut. Low TE due to removing rock from the main pump delays.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Continue digging AS31st & 2nd pass on North Slope. Great day
ExtendedComments: Stayed on the north slope all day. Main delay severed port swing wire. Other than that normal delays. Great day of production due to being on the top two passes with high dig face and wider cut then south slope. TE was higher then usual due to not having to stop for rocks. Port swing rang varies. BOS 23.5' first pass. BOS 33' second pass

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK dig AS3 Widener. high coverage and cywh. Completed 1st pass on Widener side
ExtendedComments: Replace port swing wire delay carried over. Early morning FH had to be swung around other side of G7 piling to finish rest of AS-3. No rocks encountered on top pass. high run time causing us to travel far. Lower CY then expected due to the BD being deeper about 11ft now. Majority of the day on top pass BOS 23.5. Second pass BOS 33'. RNG varies on port side. Beat estimate.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK dug 2nd Pass on Widener. Change Ladder Wire &swap cutter head (38DS)
ExtendedComments: AK stopped on second pass when traffic was coming. During this down time crews changed the ladder that was due and swapped cutters so they could weld bars on the cutter (no bars on the cutter yet. coming to use it on full channel pass). Crew also inspected thrust and spring bearings and did a ladder inspection. Resumed digging at 16:58. RNG varies on port side. good prdocution day for the TE we had due to being on the second pass with high face and cut width.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK continue AS-3 Widener move to South Slope. Skinny cut on south slope.
ExtendedComments: AK moved to south slope early in AM. Travel high due to average about 40' width in South slope. Shift anchors 9x times due to the thin cut width. BOS @ 24' in south slope first pass. BOS @ 33' in north pass second pass Roll new eye in swing wire. Inbound ship cause extended delay due to not leaving their dock until all equipment out of channel. *MiscOther Delay = Manatee sighting*

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK complete 1st pass s. slope pull back for 2nd pass. 7.15 hrs traffic. low facewidth
ExtendedComments: After first traffic Alaska pulled back for 2nd pass BOS @33'. First Pass BOS @ 24'. Roll eye in swing wire. TE low from the two long traffic delays during the day. Low production due to only diggin on south slope that has low face and a skinny cut width due to the steep slope on the south side. Material is good no rock.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK completed s. slope 2nd pass. Good production for s. slope. Swap cutter w bars
ExtendedComments: Completed just before midnight pulled back for full channel pass. Swapped cutters in the morning with one that has bar for preparation for full channel pass where we expect rock. Other delay = issues with hull. Narrow cut width but decent face help production be decent for the day for being on the south slope

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Cont. on 3rd pass. Low TE bc clean MP (8x). Higher available face.
ExtendedComments: Dredge is digging full channel pass (3rd pass) at 41.5' at first then changed back to 42.5' when dredge jumped ahead. Low TE due to cleaning MP so crew changed teeth to break up rock and dredge jumped ahead to station 83+00 to dig better material according to boring logs. Good CYWH due to higher coverage. LM started to take 4' steps in starboard corner and 2' steps in port corner since there was more material to dig on south part of the channel.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Digging 3rd pass. High Coverage. Low TE due to trafficclean MP.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig outbound at 42.5'. Even though there was low TE the production was high due to available face in the corners. LM started to take 4' steps in both corners again since the material on the port side of the dredge was improving. CYWH is beating the estimate due to high coverage in this pass. Less teeth replaced today due to better material.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Digging 3rd pass. Low TE: Downtime for main generator stern conn & spud wire.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig outbound at 42.5'. Low TE due to planned maintenance work because crew wanted to use the traffic delays during the day already. Dredge should sit in starboard corner with 4' steps to get a better slope cut. CYWH is beating the estimate due to high coverage in this pass even though the dig quantity matched the estimate. LM is taking 4' steps because the material on both port and starboard side are similar and improving throughout the cut.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Cont digging 3rd pass. High TE & production.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig outbound at 42.5' then the LM changed it to 42' because dredge was encountering rock from station 70+00 to 68+00. Production was double the estimated values. CYWH was good due to high coverage and travel. Available face decreased since LM raised the ladder depth. High TE due to limited delays to crews cleaning main pump less and traffic. LM instructed to stay in starboard corner to get better slope cuts.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Cont digging 3rd pass. Good TE. High coverage.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig outbound at 42.5' but raised ladder if the dredge encountered rock. Good TE due to less time to work on cleaning out main pump and one traffic delay. CYWH was good due to high coverage and travel. LM started to take 3' steps due to rock and clay in the pass to clear the material better.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 1st & 2nd pass in north slope. High TE.
ExtendedComments: Very good TE due to limited delays of traffic and shift anchor changes. CYWH beats estimate because dredge had good cut coverage and travel. No cutter teeth replacedchanged out due to better material. 1st Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 23.5'. 2nd Pass: 4' steps in each corner with a BOS at 33'. North slope had the port swing range vary.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 3rd pass. Pulled back to AS-3 for grade pass. High TE.
ExtendedComments: Moved from the 2nd pass back to do the 42.5' pass. Finished the 3rd pass as far as the subline 2 allows the dredge to dig. High TE due to better material and cleaning cutter one time. CYWH beat the estimate because dredge had good coverage. Lower available face compared to previous days due to port & starboard corners having less material.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Started on 4th pass. Low TE due to clean MP. Low available face.
ExtendedComments: Began the grade pass at 46.5'. High DP so LM raised ladder to 46' to decrease it. TE is low due to shutting down dredge to clean main pump (7x) but after raising the ladder reduced the number of times to clean main pump since there's less face to dig. Low production due to low available face even though coverage beats the estimate. Ladder calibration will be performed to redjust the ladder to its correct depth.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 4th pass. Low TE. Good coverage.
ExtendedComments: Continued the grade pass at 46.5'. High DP so ladder calibration was performed along with the inclinometer to correct the ladder depth to avoid overdigging. Cutter was swapped to one with bars to avoid rocks in main pump which reduced the number of main pump delays. CYWH is higher than yesterday due to coverage and less main pump delays. Production is lower than the estimate due to low available face.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished grade pass. Added 600' FH. Started on 1st pass north slope.
ExtendedComments: Finished the 4th pass at 46.5'. Low TE due to floathoseplanned engine room maintenance delays and traffic. CYWH beats the estimate due to higher available face in north slope. DP improved with this cut because started to dig the slopes which had better material. North slope BOS at 24' had port swing range vary.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 1st pass & 2nd pass on n.slope. Started on 1st pass on s.slope. High Coverage
ExtendedComments: Good TE due to minor delays other than changing cuts. CYWH beats the estimate due to high available face. High coverage because LM decided to take 4' steps since the material was better than expected. Small cut widths allowed for high travel. North slope BOS at 24' and at 34' had port swing range vary. South slope BOS at 24' had the starboard swing range vary.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 1st & 2nd pass on s.slope. Started on 3rd pass.
ExtendedComments: Production was lower since there's less available face in the south slope and the cut widths of the south slope are smaller than the north slope. Coverage didn't beat the estimate due to delays that needed to readjust the shift anchors multiple times and changed cuts twice. South slope BOS at 24' and at 34' had starboard swing range vary. Full channel pass had a cut width of 286'.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Digging 3rd pass. Low TE due to 700 hr main generator PM.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig 42.4' pass. High production due to high travel and coverage even with low TE. LM took 4' steps if material allowed it which made dredge have a high coverage rate and increased the CYWH. Higher available face in this pass because north slope has more material than the south slope.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK continue 42.5' pass pull back for grade pass midday
ExtendedComments: While the dredge was down for traffic crews greased ladder and repaired the rock box liner on the main pump. Dredge pulled back at 12:53 for grade pass BOS 46.5'. Above average TE and good CYWH. Sandy material helping procudtion be high for the day. *Manatee delay as Miscother delay*

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK complete AS-2 digging moved to AS-3 (SJ42)
ExtendedComments: AK continued to dig outbound in AS-2. Finished to where the slopes were dug at 14:22 and turned the dredge around and moved o AS-3 to dig grade pass (moved to SJ42). great production in AS-2 due to sandy material about 4-5 foot of face high TE from minimal delays.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Ak dig inbound AS-3 grade pass. 3.19hrs manatee delay. rock on port side of cut
ExtendedComments: AK dig grade pass about 3-4' of face available. encountering rock on port side while digging inbound causing to check cutter and change teeth more often. Dead manatee floated into working area FWC came out to investigate. **3.19 hrs manatee delay under miscother**

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK moved from AS-3(SJ42) to AS-2 North Slope top pass outbound
ExtendedComments: After moving subline over AK able to dig outbound in AS-2 on the north slope. Fill site crew replaced bad shore pipe at the landing which extended the delay. Good run time after dredge was in position. Cut varies due to digging to contour on port side. BOS 27' taking about 8-9' of face on the slopes. Good sandy material

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK continue north widener top pass narrow cut. Dig into AS1 midday
ExtendedComments: Top pass BOS: 27' cut width varies due to digging to a contour on the port side. Averages about 60-70'. Average produciton day from the narrow cut. Taking about 8feet of face. Sandy material. Changed cutter to 38DS with no bars.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK continued into AS1 midday Inclinometer failure 3.12hrs
ExtendedComments: Top pass BOS: 27' cut width varies due to digging to a contour on the port side. Averages about 60-70'width . Average produciton day from the narrow cut. Taking about 8feet of face. Sandy material. Inclinometer going out troubleshooting problem ongoing. Marks on ladder wide so leverman know how deep to put the ladder while figuring out the inclinometer problem.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK dig north widener till FH became tight pulled back to south slope (SJ41)
ExtendedComments: AK continue north widener broken swing wire in AM. Traffic at 12:09 troubleshooting PLCInclinometer while down extended delay after traffic passed. Port range varies due to digging to contour. BOS @27'. 300' stretch BD went up 10 feet had to do a 18' BOS before doing the 27' BOS.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK dig top pass skinny cut width. crossed into AS-1(SJ40)
ExtendedComments: AK skipped 100'ahead into AS-1 in the morning due to discovering a piece of pipe potentially being in the cut crews founded it and moved it out of the way for when we come back. new subjob starts at STA 32+00. Great run time. Moving anchors was the primary delay due to the skinny cut making us travel far. Inclinometer still not reading correctly in the AM.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK entered into AS-1 from AS-2(SJ41) midday. Top south slope skinny cut width
ExtendedComments: AK continued digging through the next AS. Move anchors more then usual due to skinny cut having high travel (about 30-40' width). Steep slope making cut skinny. PLC card was changed and ladder calibration preformed. Ladder depth coming through normally on the PLC and positioning computer. pulled back just before midnight to start second pass on North slope the next day. digwh lower due to more delays then other AS.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Digging 2nd Pass. High TE. Low available face.
ExtendedComments: Started to dig 36' pass in the north slope after moving from the south slope. High TE since there were minor shift anchor delays. CYWH was lower than estimate due to low available face. LM started to step 4' which allowed the production to beat the estimate due to high travel and coverage. Port swing range varies for the 2nd pass.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Digging the 2nd pass. Good TE. More available face than AS-2.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig 36' pass in north slope. LM took 4' steps when the material allowed it which increased the coverage and travel for this cut. High CYWH due to higher available face than AS-2 north slope. Good TE since there were limited shift anchor delays. Port swing range varies for the 2nd pass.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Started digging the 2nd pass. High TE. Low CYWH.
ExtendedComments: Digging the 36' pass in the south slope. Higher available face in this cut compared to AS-2. High TE due to minor shift anchor delays. Narrow cut reduced production even though there was high travel in this cut. Starboard swing range varies for the 2nd pass.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Continued digging 2nd pass. Low TE due to wind. Low CYWH.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig 36' pass in south slope. CYWH increased due to more available face and LM swinging faster to collect material with this skinny cut. Production didn't beat the estimate because it was a narrow cut in south slope. Low TE due to high winds causing tows to move slower during traffic. Starboard swing range varies for the 2nd pass.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Started digging 3rd pass. High CYWH due to dig face & TE.
ExtendedComments: Started to dig 42.5' pass. High production due to high travel and coverage. LM taking 4' steps whenever material allows it. CYWH is 2x bigger than estimated value due to more available face and wide cut width. Minimal delays due to few shift anchor delays and sandier material in this cut.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Continued digging 2nd pass. Avg TE. High CYWH.
ExtendedComments: Finished 36' pass on south slope. Delays due to moving shift anchor multiple times due to narrow cut. Better CYWH because LM increased swing speed since it was a small cut width. Higher DP due to digging slopes. Starboard swing range varies for the 2nd pass.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Continued digging 3rd pass. High CYWH due to available face.
ExtendedComments: Continued the 42.5' pass for the full channel. High CYWH due to wide cut width of 278' and available face. Traffic delayed most of the day along with a manatee sighting (Misc.). Good DP since there are no slopes in this cut. High coverage and travel due to LM taking 4' steps when material allowed it.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Cont. 3rd pass. Low TE due to 1000 hr PM on Cutter motorgearbox.
ExtendedComments: Digging the 42.5' pass swinging the full width of the channel. Engine room worked on 1000 hr PM was the primary delay. High CYWH due to high coverage and travel. LM taking 4' steps because material allowed it. Wide cut width allows LM to increase swing speed compared to slope cuts.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Digging 3rd pass. High coverage rate. Good TE.
ExtendedComments: Continued digging 42' pass in the full channel. Traffic was promiment delays throughout the day. CYWH increased from previous day due to high coverage and travel. LM taking 4' steps whenever the material allows it. Raised ladder will help the grade pass be more productive. Swing speed increased which allowed for more coverage and travel.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Continued 3rd pass. Good coverage. Good TE
ExtendedComments: Continued 42' pass. LM taking 4' steps allows dredge to have a high coverage rate and travel. Primary delays were traffic (2x) and clean MP. High CYWH since LM swinging around 60 fpm with good available face and wide cut width. Production is 2x the estimated dig quantity.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Continued 4th pass. High Coverage. Low available face.
ExtendedComments: Digging 46.5' pass (Grade Pass). Lower CYWH because this pass has low available face. Good TE and primary delay was traffic. Higher DP due to overdigging the grade pass. Swinging speed increased in PM which increased travel. LM taking 4' steps but will take 5' to cover more area since there's less available face and leaving 47-47.5'. *MiscOther delay: Manatee Sighting*

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished AS-2 grade pass. High Coverage. Low available face.
ExtendedComments: Completed 46.5' pass. Beats estimate for CYWH since LM is taking 5' steps allowing for more travel and coverage since there's low face in this area. DP has been consistent through this pass even though it's above the estimated value there's still good production occuring.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Continued 4th pass. High travel and coverage. Good CYWH.
ExtendedComments: Started to dig 46.5' pass. Lower TE compared to AS-2 (AM Digging) since there was traffic delay. High CYWH due to LM stepping 5' in grade pass allowing for AK to travel far and covered more area. DP was better than the morning since there was a little more face in this area compared to AS-2. *OtherMisc Delay: Manatee Sighting

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished grade pass. Started 1st pass on north slope. High Coverage.
ExtendedComments: Completed the 46.5' pass. Added 2000' to extend Subline 3 to finish AS-1 which was the primary delay. Started the 26' pass on north slope. High CYWH due to high travel and coverage. Better DP since this area had more available face compared to grade pass in AS-2.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK continued dig AS-1 ladder pump & walking spud repair
ExtendedComments: During traffic ladder inspection revealed cutless bearing valve needed to be repaired. Mid day crew realized jacking motor coupling on walking spud needed to be repaired. Range varies narrow cut due to steep slope making travel high. TE low due to multiple delays. *MiscOther delay = dead sea turtle.*

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 1st pass south slope in AS-1 started 2nd pass.
ExtendedComments: At 6:15 the dredge completed the first pass in AS-1 and moved back to begin the second pass on the south slope in AS-1. While the dredge was down the crew greased the ladder. The dredge started digging the second pass at 9:00 and was able to dig most of the day. There were 3 mechanical delays at 11:30 12:45 and 19:53 that accounted for 0.3 hours of delay. The range varies. Narrow cut because of the steep slope. TE was good CYWH high for narrow cut.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 2nd pass S slope AS-1 Started 3rd pass across main channel.
ExtendedComments: The dredge finished the second pass on the south slope and pulled back to begin the third pass across the main channel. Once the dredge was in position the crew greased the ladder before starting the third pass. CYWH was high from main channel cut due to wide cut and high face. High TE from less delays causing good production. Stepping 4' on each side. Range varies in the cut.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK continue 3rd pass main channel. Wide cut with good face for production
ExtendedComments: 3rd pass all day cut got wider towards the end of the day due to the flare in the channel that leads to the main channel. Delay for inside bushing on stbd swing winch made temp repair. Great production due to the wider cut and full swinging across the channel with about 5' of face. Great TE and run time for the day making cywh high.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Continued 3rd pass on main channel.
ExtendedComments: Pass grew narrower throughout the day due to the shape of the channel. Completed south flair of channel. High CYWH due to wide cut and good material. Limited delays during the day made for high TE.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: Finished 3rd pass AS-1. Started grade pass.
ExtendedComments: The dredge fnished digging the 3rd pass in the north flair of the entrance channel. At 16:24 the dredge pulled back to begin the grade pass on the main channel. Narrow sweeps at the begining of th day that gradualy widened as the dredge continued the pass. High TE from few delays. Moderate CYWH from longer passes and lighter material.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK conitnue to dig grade pass outbound. Minimal delays
ExtendedComments: Full day on grade pass. Start BOS at 46.5' and raised to 46' to help prevent over digging. Great run time for the day making produciton to increase. 3-4' of available face. Leverman stepping 3' in each corner to make sure we clear the area.Start tp make the turn to the south of the flair late at night. Majority sandy material

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK continue digging south flair in AS-1 grade pass
ExtendedComments: AK digging south flair into main channel. 90% TE due to only shutting down for cleaning the main pump and greasing ladder. Less moving anchors due to wider cut and not traveling as fast as slope work. CYWH lower from before due to less face availabel on grade pass.

ProjectName: TAMPA HARBR.-BIG BEND CHANL-NEW WORK DRG
BriefComments: AK continue digging outbound AS-1 grade pass
ExtendedComments: pulled back at 6:31 to dig north flair of entrance to Big bend channel. In position greased and clean main pump and resumed digging 9:49. Only move anchors rest of the day. Great travel from high TE for the day on the grade pass. Ranges vary in size due to taper in to main channel.stepping 3-3.5' in each corner with BOS 46'.

BriefComments: The Alaska continued digging 2 passes on one anchor set.
ExtendedComments: Dredging operations continued in Cut D. The leverman picked up the ladder on the bottom pass to 39.5 feet after surveys showed some overdug areas. At ~20:00 the leverman were instructed to stop digging 2 passes and dig a single pass at 40 feet. This was done for the remainder of Cut D. Average Swing Speed: 58 ftmin. Average Velocity: 20.5 ftsec. Average Density: 1.21.

BriefComments: Dredging continued in Cut F with BOS @ 33'
ExtendedComments: The port swing wire was repaired at 00:40. Leverman noticed that the tide gauge went out and worked with survey to get it repaired. At 10:40 dredging operations were put on hold after high turbidity levels were found on the beach. The cutter was picked up from 35' to 33' as the dredge moved into an area with low face. Average Swing Speed: 59 ftmin. Average Densty: 1.21. Average Velocity: 20.4 ftsec.

BriefComments: Towed to the staging area at 11:00 in anticipation of rough seas.
ExtendedComments: Work continued in cut G. BOS was 39.5 feet. Leverman were taking 4-6' sets in each corner. At 10:41 leverman becan washing out the line to prep the dredge to tow back to the staging area. Average Swing Speed: 61 ftmin. Average Density: 1.25. Average Velocity: 20.3 ftsec.

BriefComments: The dredge began digging at 16:30 BOS 32' taking 4-6' sets
ExtendedComments: Dredging began in Cut 1of Section F. the leverman were instructed to double swing the port side of the cut due to the high face. This reduced average travel and production. Average Swing Speed: 65 ftmin. Average Density: 1.17. Average Velocity: 20.5

BriefComments: Broke Port breast wire twice due to strong ground swell. Wire replaced.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued diging to the north on the west side of the borrow area. Leverman are instructed to double swing the western half of the cut taking 3-4' sets in the center and stbd corner. Average Swing Speed: 59 ftmin. Average Density: 1.18. Average Velocity: 19.5

BriefComments: Wire break dly due to ground swell Chng cut to acct for wind direction
ExtendedComments: Cont'd digging north in cut E until 11:20. Down due to wire break (3.05 hr) caused by strong ground swell. At 14:23 change to cut C and dig east to west to account for change in wind direction (NE). Start digging westbound at 17:02 single swing. Avg swing speed 59 ftmin Avg density 1.2. Avg velocity 20.6. Dump delay due to 3x adding shore pipe (1.32 hr).

BriefComments: Cont'd dig EW in cut C. Chng 4 cutter teeth
ExtendedComments: Cont'd digging westbound in cut C1 move to cut C2 @18:14 to continue digging westbound and keep wind at the stern. Single swing until passing range of 882 (marked by yellow arc on background) then double swing. Avg swing speed 63 ftmin. Avg density 1.22. Avg velocity 20. Dump dly: advance y-pipes (0.57 hr). Main pump dly: check main pump engine (0.18 hr).

BriefComments: Cont'd cut C2 until 13:52 then tow dredge to staging area
ExtendedComments: Cont'd digging westbound in cut C2. Poor sea conditions cause delay from 0:10 - 4:21 (4.18 hr) then dredge resume single swinging westbound until reaching the yellow arc then double swing west of the yellow arc on the dredge background due to higher face. Sea conditions did not improve so the dredge shut down to tow into the staging area @ 13:52 (switching to SJ 070). Avg swing speed 72 ftmin. Avg density 1.22. Avg velocity 20.4.

BriefComments: Dredge down 2.42hrs to remair a coolant line leak on the generator.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska resumed operations at approximatly 13:56 digging Cut D1 (Max Depth 38.2') westbound. The leverman were instructed to single swing holding BOS @ 37.7' due to low face and the need for zero overdig. Average Swing Speed: 60 ftmin. Average Density: 1.17. Average Velocity: 20.5

BriefComments: High DP due to over-filling beach taper. Dig Cut D
ExtendedComments: Dredge started up at midnight when seas calmed. Digging westbound in cut D start with 3D then move to 2D then 1D. Single swing with BOS @ 37.7 in 3D2D double swing with BOS @ 37.7 in 1D. Larger digpay due to filling in the north taper beachside and slightly overfilled. Breast port wire broke @ 20:20 and the crew was unable to fix due to rough weather. Wire dly: port breast wire (3.65 hr). Other dly: 3x hydraulic positioning issue (4.03 hr).

BriefComments: Dig westbound cuts D&E. Lower BOS in cut D to 38 ft.
ExtendedComments: Resumed digging westbound in cut 1D @ 06:12. After finish cut 1E pulled back to the north and continued westbound in 4D & 3D. After reviewing survey data in cut D had leverman lower BOS from 37.5' to 38.0' for the remainder of the cut. Engine room dly: Glan seal on stuffing box (0.43 hr). Electrical dly: Main generator lost power (0.28 hr). Mechanical dly: Adjusting the brake (0.1 hr). Avg swing speed: 57 fpm Avg density: 1.16 Avg velocity: 17.9 fps.

BriefComments: Cont. cuts 3D1D1E add 2000' float hose then move to Zone B
ExtendedComments: Cont'd WB cuts 3D1D1E BOS @ 38' in Zone D 33.5' in Zone E. Single swing 3D1E Double swing 1D. Add 2000' of float hose to reach zones ABC Move to B at 18:37. Levermen skip zone C bc wide cut (270') & rough seas. BOS @ 37.9' (max depth) in zone B single swing until 10' face. Dig eastwest for zones ABC. Wires dly: roll eye stbd swing wire (2.0 hr) Engine room dlys: 2x clutches trip bc compr. air loss (0.36 hr) 2x engine shut down bc high rpm (0.49 hr). Pipeline dly: float hose leak at bell (1.27 hr).

BriefComments: Dig cut 1B as seas calm use wide swing into cut 2C on the port
ExtendedComments: Cont'd WB in cut 1B. Did not dig from 01:15 - 06:24 due to rough seas. Sea conditions improved throughout the day and levermen able to swing wider by the evening cutting into cut 2C (port side) while in B then moving over to dig cut 2C at 23:15. BOS @ 37.9 single swing in B raise ladder 0.5' double swing in B where face >8' swing at 40 fpm velocity to 18 fps while double swing. Pipeline dly: replace bell conn. on float hose (3.76 hr) Avg velocity 18.7 fps Avg swing speed 36.8 fpm Avg density 1.27

BriefComments: Chng dig instr. to dig in lifts cleanup 2C and 1B.
ExtendedComments: Cont'd westbound cut 2C then pulled back to cleanup cut 2C and 1B then cont'd in 2B. Cleaned up narrow part of cut 2C (170' cut) to dig remaining 4' of face same amt of face remained in double swing portion of 1B. Chng dig instructions to dig face >8' in zones A & B in lifts and slow swing speed and velocity. Lift 1: dig with BOS 1.5' below max depth lift 2: dig with BOS at max depth. PM survey confirmed this method worked for cut 2C. Avg swing speed: 53.3 fpm Avg density: 1.21 Avg velocity: 18.4 fps.

BriefComments: Cont'd cut 2B westbound. leaving grade w new dig method
ExtendedComments: Cont'd digging in cut 2B westbound w BOS @ max depth (37.9 ft). New dig method of lfits working well minimal over dig and leaving grademax depth. Finished cut 2B at 21:57 after chng cut and lining up for cut 3B at 23:28 stbd breast wire broke. Avg swing speed 45.3 fpm Avg density 1.24 Avg velocity 18.7 fps. Dump dly: 2x pump water (0.5 hr). Wires dly: stbd breast wire (0.53 hr). Engine room dly: patch leaking raw water hose to cooling unit for main generator (2.09 hr). Other dly: Turbidity (1.96 hr)

BriefComments: Cut 3B lift BOS up 1' to avoid overdigging in corners.
ExtendedComments: Cont'd westbound in cut 3B after repairing the stbd breast wire at 06:40. Digging dig face > 8' in lifts. Survey showed slight overdig in corners so raise BOS to 1' above max depth for the 2nd lift. Avg velocity: 18.2 fps Avg density: 1.23 Avg swing speed: 44.1 fpm. Dump dly: 2x pump water (0.52 hr). Mechancial dly: 3x stbd swing motor auto shut down (0.14 hr).

BriefComments: Startup @ 08:20 cut 1A turbidity shut down (2.22 hr)
ExtendedComments: Resume digging westbound in cut 1A. Digging one pass until reaching 8+ feet of dig face then 2 passes with the second lift BOS @ 34.5' (0.8' above max depth in Zone A = 35.3'). Exceeded ntuturbidity limit @ 16:43 shut down for more than 2 hrs when allowed to start back up seas were too rough to work go to SJ 070. Other dly: shut down for turbidity (2.22 hr) Pipeline dly: leak in float hose (0.7 hr) Mechanical dly: swing system brake (0.09 hr). Avg swing speed 31.7 fpm Avg velocity 20.5 fps Avg density 1.26

BriefComments: Westbond Zone A cuts 1A2A. Preventive turbidity shut down (1.68 hr)
ExtendedComments: Cont'd westbound in cut 1A digging both first and second lifts. Move to cut 2A at 01:42. Worked until 12:40 then shut down for turbidity preventively. Cont'd after turbidity until seas became too rough to keep diggin at 16:26 - move to SJ070. Updated site viewer map on dredge & tugs. Surveys show leaving 0.5 - 1.0' of material behind. Other dly: turbidity (1.68 hr) while down grease ladder chng 2 teeth & 1 keeper. Avg swing speed 35.1 fpm avg density 1.12 avg velocity 18.5 fps.

BriefComments: Resumed digging at 10:11 in cut 2A surveys showed DP @ 1.05
ExtendedComments: Continued westbound in cut 2A digging both remaining lifts for the area. Raise up BOS to 34' for both passes to try and avoid over dig. Redesign cuts 3A4A so that SE wind will be to the stern and could dig 79% of the two cuts while allowing breast anchors to spread out. CND surveys showed that DP is now at 1.05. While pulling back for 2nd lift @14:05 lift cutter and inspectgrease ladder. Preventative turbidity shut down dredge @ 16:07 for 1.17 hr. Avg density 1.11 avg vel 19.5 fps avg swing 32.7 fpm.

BriefComments: Dredge continued digging NW in its second pass of Cut 3A BOS@34.0'
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging 2-6' of face in its second pass due to digging in lifts. Dredge would complete Cut 3A at 9:10 before having to shut down for 3.85hrs and reposition 3400' south in Cut 1F. Dredge was set up to dig South in Cut 1F however large ground swells shut the dredge down for the remainder of the day. Avg density 1.18 avg vel 19.1 fps avg swing 60.0 fpm.

BriefComments: Dredge shut down 0.44hrs to pull back and begin digging Cut G with BOS @ 35.0'.
ExtendedComments: The dredge attempted to resume digging operations at 10:26 but was shut back down at 11:17 due to the ground swell. Digging operations recommenced at 13:28 digging south in Cut 1F with BOS @ 35.0'. Low production due to slow swing speed and small step sizes (2-3'). Avg density 1.14 Avg vel 18.0 fps Avg swing 40.0 fpm.

BriefComments: Dredge down 3.26hrs to advance y-valves for the fill site. Down 2x (1.64hrs) gland seal.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in lifts southbound in Cut 1GH with BOS @ 35.0' first pass and 40.0' second pass leaving 0-2' material behind. The dredge had to shut down (2x) for 1.64hrs to repair the Gland Seal on the main pump. Low production due to ground swell slow swing speed and small step sizes (2-4'). Avg density 1.16 Avg vel 17.2 fps Avg swing 43.0 fpm.

BriefComments: 3.22hrs delay for beach turbidity.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in lifts southbound in Cut 1H with BOS @ 35.0' first pass and 38.0' second pass leaving 0-2' material behind. The dredge had to shut down (2x)for 5.81hrs to repair the service water pump. Low production due to ground swell and cautious digging. Avg density 1.21 Avg vel 17.3 fps Avg swing 49.0 fpm.

BriefComments: Dredge down 4.39hrs turbidity2.31hrs for Captain ordered safety meeting.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in lifts southbound in Cut 1H with BOS @ 35.0' first pass and 38.0' second pass leaving 0-2' material behind. At 21:01 the dredge went down for a pipeline leak where the dredge connects to the float hose. The gasket on the pumpkin was repaired and the dredged continued digging at 21:54. Avg density 1.24 Avg vel 17.0 fps Avg swing 50.0 fpm.

BriefComments: Dredge down 1.86hrs (6x) Anchors 1.85hrs (2x) advance pipey-valves.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in lifts southbound in Cut 1H with BOS @ 34.0' first pass and 38.0' second pass leaving 0-2' material behind. At 13:10 the dredge completed Cut 1H and moved to Cut 1I double swinging in the stbd. corner with BOS @ 32.1'. The dredge would pump on a sifter from 09:58 - 11:30.Avg density 1.19 Avg vel 16.8 fps Avg swing 50.0 fpm.

BriefComments: Cont'd SB in cut 1 JK. Double swing in high face areas.
ExtendedComments: Dredge working southbound along cut 1 in Zones J and K. Double swinging high face areas on westside of SBA2. Continued into widened cut while working in Zone J bc calmer seas allowed. While the y-valves were being advanced on the beach the cutter was inspected and cleaned and the crew also worked on the UWP gland seal. Dump delays: 2x advance y-valves (1.33 hr) change out broken basket (0.94 hr). Mechanical dly: pin coming out of winch (0.48 hr).

BriefComments: Adj dig instr to dig material in lifts to get closer to grade wo over dig
ExtendedComments: Cont'd southbound in cut 1 Zones J & K. Double swinging high face (and only stepping) in stbd corner. Surveys showed leaving 2-3' material on stbd side so chng dig instr to dig in lifts 1st BOS @ 30.0' 2nd BOS @ 35.0'. Max depth 33.2'. Lifts will gather mat'l wo over dig. Low face reported due to lifts. 1 basket left @ 4:49 leads to long dump delays for rest of the day (4x for avg 1.32 hr). Chng stern buoy wire grease ladder check cutterladder during dlys. Other dump dly: advance y-valves (2.17 hr).

BriefComments: Cut 1 Zones JKL. Shut down @ 17:57 move to Job 72511.
ExtendedComments: Cont'd southbound in cut 1 along Zones JK and L. Digging in lifts thru all zones with 2nd lift BOS just above grade. Lifts abe dredge to dig more CYWH. Long beach-side delays continued until 09:47 when the 2nd basket was repaired. While repairing basket: grease chng stbd breast buoy wire chng 1 tooth. Dump dlys: pump water (0.25 hr) repair basket (2.94 hr). Shut down to tow in for startup of PBH project 72511 @ 17.57. Average swing speed 55.2 fpm average velocity 18.8 fps average density 1.13.

BriefComments: Startup @ 12:02 in cut TB1 west side of TB
ExtendedComments: Dredge start digging @ 12:02 in west side of Turning Basin cut TB1. BOS @ 34.5' swinging as fast as possible to not overdig. Surveys showed no over dig on 40x40 grid of lines. Digging low face -> 3-4' to OD. Site engineers calibrated gyro velocity re-standardized density while pumping water. Observing lots of trash pumped on beach. Several dlys cleaning cutter and baskets due to trash. Dump dlys: 2x clean basket (0.87 hr). Average velocity 18.3 fps average density 1.09 average swing speed 42.7 fpm.

BriefComments: Southside of turning basin move barges in staging area (2.37 hr)
ExtendedComments: Cont'd diggin SW in cuts TB23. Move to dig E in cut TB4 @12:39 to 15:35. 3x long dredge move dlys due to shifting barges around in staging area (avg 2.23 hr). 3x shifting anchor dlys (avg 0.79 hr) while in cut TB4 due to minimal area on south side of the cut bc of AT&T cable & no anchor sea grass area. BOS @ 34.5 surveys showing no mat'l left above grade and limited over dig. Engine room dly: port engine exhaust valve bridges (0.27 hr). Dump dly: clean baskets (0.55 hr). Total 2.63 hr for trash on cutter.

BriefComments: SE cornerstaging area of TB moving barges = long anchorchng cut dlys
ExtendedComments: Cont'd working in SE corner of TB where staging area is located. Multiple and long chng cut dlys from moving barges around and morelonger shift anchor delays from limited space to place anchors. Recvd multibeam survey from 3rd party showing high spots on toe. Change dig instr to swing 5' outside of toe for remainder of cut TB5. Clean cutterclean pumpclean baskets due to trashwirescablestiresconcretesteelwood. Dump dlys: fix shore pipe (0.34 hr) clean basket (0.26 hr).

BriefComments: Finish @ 11:30 then spot cleanup.
ExtendedComments: Cont'd digging east side of TB. 3rd party survey analyzed in AM start spot cleanup at 11:30. Total 12 spots in S & SW parts of TB as well as a 33' contour area in NE corner of the TB. Long chng cut delays due to rearranging barges in the staging area while moving to cleanup (7x average 1.13 per dly). Lower BOS to 35.5' for cleanup to ensure that all mateiral is gathered. Offset toes & cleanup borders 3-6' depending on amt of material. Avg velocity 18.5 fps avg swing 32.7 fpm avg density 1.11

BriefComments: On location in SBA2 @ 4:25. Start dig southbound cut 3G @ 11:25.
ExtendedComments: Finish tow and arrive on location in SBA2 @ 4:25. Begin digging southbound in Zone G cut 3 calm seas allow for dredge to swing 225' cut. Max depth 39.4 BOS @ 39.5 single swing entire area. Dig instructioncuts designed for cuts 3G 3H 3I and 2G 2H 2I. All these combined will give enough CY to finish beach. Digging on 1880' float hose bc can reach all designed cuts. Dump dlys: Clean basket (2.36 hr) 2x add shore pipe (1.75 hr). Grease ladder while chng teeth also chng 23 keepers.

BriefComments: Cont. dig southbound Cut 3G move to Cut 2G hi dump delays- adding shorepipe
ExtendedComments: Dredge cont. digging southbound in Cut 3G with BOS@ 39.5 one pass. Survey showed leaving 3-4' of face. Changed to dig in lifts with BOS at 35' 1st pass 39.5' sec pass. Moved to Cut 2G @20:09 and resumed digging @21:39. Majority of delay time due to adding pipe on the beach.

BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 2 finish cut 2G cont. on into Cut 2H two passes wBOS@34 and 37
ExtendedComments: The dredge cont. to dig in Cut 2G and on into Cut 2H. Instructions changed to dig in lifts because of high face.1st pass BOS@ 34 2nd BOS@ 37'. Survey showed leaving +-1' of face. Majority of delays due to adding shorepipe. Dump delays were mostly for adding pipe.

BriefComments: Cont. dig lifts in Cut 2H BOS@34 1st pass 37' 2nd all delays due to beach work
ExtendedComments: Dedge cont. to dig in lifts in Cut 2H with BOS@ 34 ist pass 37 2nd pass. Delays on beach were for adding shorepipe removeclean basket pushing material to end of taper moving equipment

BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut2H BOS@37 cross into Cut2I BOS@33' high dump delays-add shorepipe
ExtendedComments: Dredge cont. to dig in Cut 2H swinging wider to grab material in Cut3H holding BOS@37'. Crossed into Cut 2I holding BOS@33 making one pass. High dump delays due to addingremoving all shore pipe and re-constructing dikesgrading stockpilesBroke swing wire @23:51.

BriefComments: Cont dig in Cut 2I finish pumping beach at 13:55
ExtendedComments: Repair swing wire until 02:43. Cont. to dig in Cut 2I. unable to swing full cut in heavy seas broke cut in 12 finished pumping on beach at 13:55

BriefComments: Cont. dig green side entrance channel move to red side for traffic
ExtendedComments: The Dredge cont to dig on the green side of the channel holding BOS @41 . The majority of delays were for cleaning baskets adding shore pipe and shifting anchors. The narrow channel and tidal currents make it difficult to set anchors. An excavator broke down in the discharge area and had to be piped around causing a 1.85hr delay.

BriefComments: Start in ext basin @ 14:15. Hold BOS @ 38' let material run to cutter then sweep.
ExtendedComments: Resume digging in extended settling basin @ 14:15. Red arc on dig bckgrd marks where survey showed we had already reached grade. Holding BOS @ 38' and letting fine sand material run to the cutter. Swinging slow across cut to make sure to gather material. After first pass pull back and sweep. Surveys show overdig of 3-4' up to slopes. Dump dlys: 2x pump water (0.49 hr). Engine room dly: clutch issue right before startup (0.16 hr). Traffic not an issue due to anchors not across channel.

BriefComments: Cont'd inbound SB1SB2. 1st pass BOS @ 38' sweep with BOS @ 40'
ExtendedComments: Cont'd digging inbound in the extended settling basin finish sweep pass @ 03:39 then move north to cut SB2. Dig first pass with BOS @ 38' then pull back and sweep per anchor sets. Sweep with BOS @ 40'. Much more sandy material in this area many dump delays for pumping water (9x avg 0.34 hr) and 2 delays for adding shore pipe (avg 0.78 hr).Surveys showed need one more sweep in cut SB1 to get all material. Chng 6 teeth and 6 keepers during dump dly from 04:42 - 06;05.

BriefComments: Expanded settling basin then channel red toe. Dig BOS @ 38' sweep @ 40'
ExtendedComments: Cont'd digging in expanded settling basin until 16:08 then moved to the channel to dig the red toe (part of the extended settling basin). Holding BOS@ 38' for all areas with a sweep pass at 40' to gather all material. Sitting in corners of settling basin cuts to let the material run down to the BOS. Dump dlys: fixing ruptured shore pipe (3.15 hr) pumping water for dump (0.63 hr). Other dly: wash out line for main pump (0.14 hr). Anticipating high traffic volume tomorrow so move to channelAS2 today.

BriefComments: 10:47-20:35 cleanup sweep in both cuts inbound. stbd swing wire (2.55 hr).
ExtendedComments: Start dig in settling basin @ 10:47. Set up dig areas to sweep with BOS @ 41' based on contours for respective settling basin areas. Grade ext - 35' grade exp - 33'. Sweeping slow to gather all remaining material. Holding cutter on slopes to let material run to suction. Working in the settling basin allow for full survey in entrance chnl areas return for minor cleanup (sj 041 @ 20:35). Multiple chng cut delays to reach areas on pos bckgrd (3x avg 0.88dly). Broke stbd swing wire @ 12:12 2.55 hr dly.

BriefComments: Dredge shut down at 0735 for a pipeline leak for the rest of the day
ExtendedComments: The DR Alaska continued digging in Cut 1 with BOS at 45' single swinging taking 3-4' steps in each corner.At 0735 a leak was discovered on the discharge side of the Booster Barney.Due to inclement weather the crew was not able to complete the repair and the dredge was down for the remainder of the day. The new day time levermen is still getting used to digging close to swing wires and swung slower than usual. Avg Corr Density- 1.23; Avg Vel- 14.0; Avg SS- 51 fpm; Avg Step Size 3-4'

BriefComments: Dredge resumed digging at 1242 when uw pump repairs were completed. BOS 49'
ExtendedComments: Upon finishing repairs to the underwater pump the DR Alaska resumed digging in Cut 1 with a BOS at 49'. Levermen are single swinging and taking 3-4' steps in each corner. Main pump pedestal bearing was overheating so dredge shut down at 1729 to examine and regrease. Resumed digging 2022. UW pump repairs (12.7 hr); Overheating bearing (2.88hr). Avg Corr Density- 1.24; Avg Vel- 12.8; Avg SS- 50 fpm; Avg Step size 4'

BriefComments: Cont'd Cut 1 BOS 49'.4.79 hr Booster Delay for generator mp bearing heat exchanger
ExtendedComments: The DR Alaska continued digging in Cut 1 with BOS at 49'. Levermen are instructed to single swing with 3-4' steps. Booster repairs to generator and mp bearing (4.79hr); Main motor lubrication (2.11hr); Remove plugs from pedestal bearing (1.85hrs).Avg Corr Density- 1.18; Avg Vel- 13.5; Avg SS- 50 fpm; Avg Step size 3.5'

BriefComments: BOS 49' 3-4' Steps. Worn Pump. Short swing due to nearby riser pipe.
ExtendedComments: Single swinging with BOS at 49' stepping in each corner. Leaving 44' 5' of spillage. Running MP 310 RPM 0000-1100 then 338 RPM. Getting a lot of water in corners when stepping due to sticky material not running into cutter; combined with shorter cut to avoid digging near the riser (~half the cut) means more stepping and therefore more water in line. Targeting a 1.40 density by varying swing speed. Dye Test: vel adj. by -0.8 fps. Avg Corr Density- 1.24; Avg Vel- 13.6; Avg SS- 49 fpm; Step 3-5'

BriefComments: Went down to move dredge to next cut and change ME bearing lubrication.
ExtendedComments: Finished cut 1 moved to cut 6 W of cut 1. MP RPM reduced in cut 6 due to overheated pedestal bearings. Reduced cutter rpm in cut 6 and it caused an insignificant increase in production to be confirmed (~125 cywh). When digging in continued single swinging with BOS at 49' stepping in each corner. Step size increased slightly to 3-5'. Barney: 312 RPM64 psi in156 psi out. Avg Corr Density- 1.31 sg; Avg Vel- 12.5 fps; Avg SS- 54 fpm; Step 3-5'

BriefComments: Lowered BOS to 50' 5-6' steps went down for Haul Gear Generator problem
ExtendedComments: At 1000 the dredge began taking 5-6' steps and lowered the BOS to 50'. The dredge was usually pump limited and when not pump limited they were swing limited pulling 700-800 swing amps. In the evening the hauling gear motor kept losing power on the dredge and the dredge shut down 2 times to make repairs (6.27 hrs). Barney: 318 RPM72 psi in172 psi out. Avg Corr Density- 1.30 sg; Avg Vel- 12.8 fps; Avg SS- 51 fpm; Step 5-6'

BriefComments: Down to repair hauling gear motor. moved to Cut 8 BOS 50' 4-5' steps
ExtendedComments: Single swinging. Step size adjusted to 4-5' to optimize production based on behavior of material in surveys (5.2 WH under new step size). The cutter was run at a speed of 25-27 RPM. Higher production may be skewed because dredge finished cut 6 and because of low run time. The dredge moved to Cut 8 in the evening through midnight. Much down time due to mechanical issues with hauling gear motor and generator (14.56 hrs). Avg Corr Density- 1.32 sg; Avg Vel- 12.9 fps; Avg SS- 51 fpm; Step 4-5'

BriefComments: Started digging in Cut 8 BOS 50' 4-5' Sets
ExtendedComments: The dredge was delayed while the hauling geaer was being repaired. Leverman brought the cutter speed to 30 RPM after disscussion of the production analysis from yesterday showed reduced CYWH. The limiting production factor remained to be the pump. Average Swing Speed: 52 ftmin. Average Density: 1.25. Average Velocity 13 ftsec. Sets were between 4-5 feet.

BriefComments: DR AK finished in cut 8 moved to Cut 7 BOS 50' digging E-W now.
ExtendedComments: The dredge finished digging cut 8 as it neared the riser pipe and moved to cut 7 to continue work. The move took longer than usual due to the current and new digging orientation; cut 7 was pointed East. The booster barney was set to auto flow based on 20 psi incoming pressure in cut 7 because the rack position might have been reading incorrectly. The Barney's rpm changed from ~320 before to 343 rpm with autoflow but the velocity change was negligible. Avg SS: 51 fpm Avg Dens: 1.30. Avg Vel: 12.8fps Avg Step: 3.3'

BriefComments: Digging in Cut 7 BOS 50' 4-5' by inst avg step size 3.2'
ExtendedComments: Digging Eastward. Survey revealed a fluff layer 1.5-2' thick settling in cut 7 behind dredge possibly due to cut's E-W orientation and current. Booster Barney remained on auto flow setting and cutter speed remained at max. Dredge was pump limited. Cutter amps increased from ~350 to ~815 at 1720 fill also reported seeing sand in the evening. Avg SS: 53 fpm Avg Dens: 1.32. Avg Vel: 12.6fps Avg Step: 3.2'

BriefComments: Began digging at 07:35 in Cut 4. Single swing with 5-6' steps. BOS varies
ExtendedComments: After completing calibrations and tests the dredge began digging at 07:35 in Cut 4 at Station 48+83. Levermen are instructed to single swing with 5-6' steps to maximize production in lower face material. BOS varied from 18 to 20 as BA allows. Production was also being limitied by the pump and hoffer valve as cavitation would occure if densities were too high. Velocity: 15.0; Average Density: 1.21; Swing Speed: 63; Cutter Speed: 29

BriefComments: Cut 4. Single swing with 5-6' steps. BOS 20'. Reduced step size to minimize spillage.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in Cut 4. Levermen were instructed to single swing with 5-6' steps. After repairs were made to the ladder pump and motor digwh increased. The step size was reduced to 4' after surveys showed that material was being left above grade. Velocity: 15.0; Average Density: 1.17; Swing Speed: 53; Cutter Speed: 30

BriefComments: Cut 5. Single swing with 5' steps. BOS 1820'
ExtendedComments: The dredge finished moving into Cut 5 and began digging at 03:49. Levermen are instructed to single swing with 5' steps in each corner. The dredge started the day in lower face material so the digwh was lower than normal. Velocity: 15.8; Average Density: 1.19; Swing Speed: 58; Cutter Speed: 30

BriefComments: Cut 5. Single swing 5' steps each corner. BOS 20'. Better production in higher face
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in Cut 5 single swinging with 5' steps in each corner and BOS at 20'. The dig face increases moving down the cut so production rates have increased. The BOS changed between 18.5 19.5 and 20.5 which lowered production when the ladder stopped swinging during depth changes. At 23:33 dredge shut down for cutter motor bearing leak. Velocity: 16.8; Average Density: 1.19; Swing Speed: 55; Cutter Speed: 30

Velocity: 16.4; Average Density: 1.17; Swing Speed: 57;

BriefComments: Dig with 1 cutter motor. Better production during dayless in evening rough seas
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in Cut 2 with BOS at 18.5' then lowering to 19.5' in deeper part of template. Levermen are taking larger step in port than starboard corner in order to minimize cutter amps. This imroved production but levermen must focus on taking large enough steps to maintain sufficient travel and coverage. Velocity: 16.3; Average Density: 1.19; Swing Speed: 52;

BriefComments: Digging with 1 cutter motor. Hoffer Valve auto-control was repaired.
ExtendedComments: Leaks developed on the trunk line on the fill site. The UWP couldn't prime due to hydraulic issues. There is a delay on the hoffer valve auto-control so the the setpoint on the PLC was changed from 5 to 10 PSI. Average Velocity: 16.4. Average Diensity: 1.22. Average Swing Speed: 55. The leverman were taking 2-3 foot sets in the STBD corner and 4-5 foot sets in the Port corner. The cutter speed was lowered from 30 to 25 RPM to lower the torque on the cutter motor.

BriefComments: Dig with 1 cutter motor. Had to dig around anomaly slower travel.
ExtendedComments: Cut 1 has low face between 3.5 to 5 feet. The material in the cut consists of hard compacted sand that is sripping the cutter. The cutter tripped a total of 24 times since the leverman started keeping track at 10AM. The upper valve wouldn't open and close after sand was found in the valve and the hydraulic solenoid. It took 2.65 hours to flush out the material and correct the problem.

BriefComments: Dig with 1 cutter motor. Moved into higher face in cut 1 increasing production.
ExtendedComments: Hard compacted sand tripped the cutter 29 times in the early morning. Once cut 1 was completed crew laid 2000' of subline. Dredge then moved to cut 1A. Average Velocity: 16.9 ftsec. Average Density: 1.21. Average Swing Speed: 55 ftmin.

BriefComments: 1 cutter motor.Moved to Cut 1A. Increased MP RPM to ~300. More face in beginning of cut.
ExtendedComments: While in 24' grade face was ~10 ft Production hovered around 3000 CYWH and was dug for ~7hrs.When the dredge advanced to 20' grade face dropped to 6-7' and production dipped to 2600 CYWH. The remainder of the cut will be in the 20' grade. The cutter only tripped 9 times the leverman reported that stalling the cutter occured more frequently. The MP speed was increased to ~300 RPMs to increase velocity to improve production while in high face.Velocity: 16.4. Density 1.2. SS: 62

BriefComments: Digging with only 1 cutter motor. Cutter tripped 13 times
ExtendedComments: Continued digging in Cut 1A. Face started out around 6' but diminished to 5' as the dredge advanced through the cut. the last 350 feet of the cut began to taper from 280 feet wide to 160 feeet wide. Both contributed to lower production than the previous day. Cutter was picked up at 1300 from 2 to 1.5 feet below grade afte surveys showed 0.5 feet of overdig. Average Density: 1.20. Average Velocity: 16.4. Average Swing Speed: 60

BriefComments: 1 cutter motor. Leverman increased step size to 5-6' keeping production up.

Face in the area was roughly 5 feet which increased to 6 feet by the end of the day. Because of the low face leverman were instructed to increase step size to maximize production. Average Velocity: 16.1. Average Density: 1.23. Average Swing Speed: 61

BOS was set at 21.5' and dig face increased from 5 feet to 5.5 feet moving down each of the cuts. Production rates were reduced due to low face and having to dig into each cut. Average cutter motor amps are 724 and the levermen did not report any stalls. Average Velocity: 16.1. Average Density: 1.22. Average Swing Speed: 60

Cutter was inspected showed minor signs of wear. Wear will continue to be monitored during the project and a spare cutter head is on site. Average Velocity: 16.7. Average Density: 1.23. Average Swing Speed: 62

Average Velocity: 16.3. Average Density: 1.27. Average Swing Speed: 60

Average Swing Speed: 62

The wire was removed at 21:45 and crews worked to replace the wire.Average Velocity: 15.8. Average Density: 1.24.

Average Density: 1.21.

Material has become softer and more muddy allowing leverman to take larger step sizes to keep production consistant with the lower swing speeds. A wire broke in the evening and had have eye rolled. Survey showed 2-3' of material being left behind so Dredge pulled back 500 ft. Swing speed was slowed down to 40 ftmin on second pass of cut 6 to reduce leave in volume. Avg. Velocity was 15.1 fts. Avg. Density was 1.21.

BOS on top swing was ~21' ~30' on bottom pass. Avg. swing speed 66 Avg. Velocity 15.4 Avg. Density 1.23 Avg. Cut Head speed 28.

There is a no disturbe limit 3 feet below grade that limits the BOS to only 1 ft below. 2 passes were needed to remove material to grade. The MP speeed is low to keep velocity down for the fill site. Average Density: 1.20. Average Velocity: 15.2 ftsec. Average Swing Speed: 59 ftmin.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: The dredge production was 2254 CYWH.
ExtendedComments: At station 44+73 the face increased to about 14 feet at that station the leverman was directed to start making two passes.For the first pass the BOS will be at 16' and for the last pass the BOS will be at 23'.This will be monitored to ensure that there is no over digging.The dredge had 10.3 hours of delays the most significant delays being due to waiting on the dump and due to having to flush the line multiple times.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: The daily production was 2146 CYWH
ExtendedComments: The dredge continues to exceed the estimate in production and dig cy.They were not able to beat the estimate in TE though mostly due to the fact that we finished pumping the pad and the Y-valve was added. There was 5.08 hours of delays due to the dump.The Levermen are having a problem with the material colapsing and causing the ladder to drag.They have been instructed to dig two lifts one at 17 feet and one at 23 ft.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: The production has increased to 2501 CYWH.
ExtendedComments: The dredge was shut down shortly after midnight due to a possible subline leak.A survey of the line was done the morning of 1224 and no mounds were found.The sensor on the density gauge got painted so the density spikes out at very high numbers causing the dredge computer to report false values.The dredge was able to beat the estimate in production and in dig CY.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: The production was 2282 CYWH
ExtendedComments: The dredge resumed digging at 8:50 after a subline survey and a velocity test were conducted.The survey didn't show any mounds around the subline and the velocity test showed no change from what the guages said.The dredge went down again at 18:55 due to the engine room working on the Port Main Engine andhaving to replace a broken STBD swing wire.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: The production was 2119CYWH.
ExtendedComments: At 15:00 the velocity went up to 33 FPS and the UWP lost all power.When they tried to prime the pump back up the pump would not prime.Once the enginners repacked the UWP the dredge went back to work.Per the request of the client we set the dredge up to dig to the 21' contour.We had to shift her farther to the STBD side and set up new cuts.The dredge continues to dig the top pass at 17-19' and the bottom pass at 24.5 feet.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Production was 2095 CYWH.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continues to dig in Cut one making two passes the first one at 17ft and the second pass at 24.5ft.She was down for weather starting at 8:20 for 4.42 hours she was also down for 3 hours due to having to replace a swing wire.The night leverman was having problems with the ladder dragging and the dredge getting hung up on the bottom at low tide.They are still making the first pass closer to 19ft to allow the dredge to not get hung up at low tide.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 1 disp in AS 1. Avg. low face bc of digging to contour
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 1 on this day and disposing in section AS 1.The cutter is daylighting a little while digging in Cut 1 becuase the dredge is digging to the 21 foot contour line (grade) when swinging to the STBD side. Main pump averaged 327 RPMs on this day while interim pressure averaged 17.4 PSI.Density gauge is not recording proper values electrician is on board to fix problem because after standardizing the gauge is it still not working properly.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 1 making 2 passes. Dig to 21' contour line on STBD side
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continued to dig in cut 1 between Sta. 26+88 and 22+20 digging in 2 passes.When digging to STBD the cuts extend outside of borrow area ~100 in order to dig to 21' contour line per contract owners' request.Since BA slopes down on STBD side face value is lower than average and production is limited.Density gauge remains broken and is being tested to replace either the density gauge or the power board. Suction pressure increased on this day from 17.5 avg to 18.3 avg PSI.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Finish Cut 1 move to Cut 2. Dig 1 pass at start of Cut 2 mjr dly: move anchor chng cut
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska finished Cut 1 digging to station 17+55 before moving to Cut 2.Low face at the end of Cut 1 so leverman were only taking 1 pass. Also low face in beginning of Cut 2 and currently making only 1 pass. Velocity dropped when digging in Cut 2 possibly due to higher shell percentage in the material; will monitor velocityproduction further.At end of cut 1 main pump RPMs increased to 333 as well as suction and discharge pressures increased to 19.5 and 213 PSI respectively.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Start dig in Cut 2 dig 1 pass for first 561 feet more shellwash out line often
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska started to dig in Cut 2 between Sta. 46+12 and 40+33 at 02:10. Between stations 46+12 and 40+51 the dredge was only digging 1 pass because of low face.Higher shell content in first pass causing velocity to drop in pipeline and leverman had to wash out line three times.Bottom pass digs much better and dredge can swing faster without velocity drops. Delays: STBD swing wire was cut and had to be replaced washing out line moving anchors and stepping dredge back grease ladderchange teeth

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont to dig in Cut 2 Low TE: pumping shellvelocity drops dig in 2 passes
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continued to dig in cut 2 between Sta. 40+34 and 36+60 making 2 passes while digging.There were 7.5 hours of delays to wash out the pipe line because of the velocity dropping due to pumping shells.Only pumping shells on first pass and production picks up on the second pass; swinging slower on the top pass. Should be getting into favorable material in next day or two while digging in section D2 Cut 2. No advancement on beach because they pumped in middle of beach moving sand on berm

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 2 still pumping shellswashout line bc of velocity dropping
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 2 between Sta. 37+84 and 33+46 continuing to make 2 passes.At Sta. 34+47 the dredge started to dig towards the SW anticipating shell content to decrease as seen while digging in the adjacent location in Cut 1.Off-shore conditons started to build in the late hours of the day and will continue to next day so production dropped slightly at night but shell content remains the largest contributing factor for decreased production.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 2 bad WXchoppy seas causing decr. prod. Digging less shell
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 2 betwen Sta. 34+20 and 29+23 making 2 passes.Choppy seas up to 5' and wind gusts up to 30 kts throughout the day caused lower production.Leverman reported dcreased amounts of shell in the cut and had fewer delays to wash out the pipelinedecreasing velocity. Only ~300' of beach left in section AS 1 before we break back and start pumping South decreasing the line length and combined with better WX conditions production will pick back up.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont to dig in Cut 2 not digging shell.Low TE: wait on dump to move to AS 2
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continued to work in Cut 2 making 2 passes between Sta. 31+97 and 25+90.No longer washing line out because of digging shell. Density gauge radiaiton detector was replaced and now density is recording correctly.Major delay: wait on dump to move to section AS 2 after finishing AS 1 misc delay: adjust STBD breast friction.Approx. 850 feet of travel left in Cut 2.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 2 make 2 passes. Mjr dly: Move anchors. 300 ft. remain in Cut 2
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 2 between Sta. 26+07 and 21+02 making 2 passes.Approx. 300 feet remain in Cut 2 before dredge will shift back and start digging in Cut 3.Possibly move to Cut 4 to dig finer material to evaluate how fine sand will fill in slopes.Major delay: move anchors; minormisc delays: shift dredge back wait on dump to pipe up. Contiue to pump on beach section AS 2.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 2 add 360' of pontoon. Move to Cut 6 after finishing Cut 2
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 2 making 2 passes between Sta. 22+08 and 16+98.Dredge could reach further than in Cut 1 because 360' of pontoon line was added behind dredge; reason being so the dredge could reach more area in the borrow area especially in the Eastern cuts where the material is finer.Minor delays to shift anchors and step dredge back also to wait on dump to pipe up.Will be moving to Cut 6 once the dredge finishes in Cut 2 to dig finer material to help pump slopes on beach.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Finish Cut 2 @ 01:15 and move to Cut 6. Excessive move delay bc of anch brg 108 malfunctn
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska finished digging Cut 2 at 01:15 and moved to Cut 6 to dig finer material to help pumping the slopes on the beach.The move to Cut 6 was excessively long because anchor barge 108 was having great difficulty lifting anchors often taking 30 minutes to lift one anchor.Digging all of cut 6 in one pass due to low face and finer material.Only 670 feet of travel in Cut 6 and will be moving to Cut 3 once it is finished.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Finish Cut 6 move to Cut 3. Making 1 pass in both cuts. Dig some shell @ start of Cut3
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska finished digging in Cut 6 at 04:00 reaching Sta. 23+71 before moving to Cut 3.Cut 6 was able to be dug in 1 pass throughout entire cut because of low face and fine material.Started diggin in Cut 3 at 08:45 at Sta. 39+89 and making 1 pass until Sta. 35+00.Few shells dug at start of Cut 3 causing 0.75 hrs of wash-out delays due to velocity drops in the pipeline. Minor delays: clean main pump and adjust packing move anchors.Misc dlys: fix hole in discharge pipe switch valves on beach.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 3 dig 2 passes. Mjr dly: wait on dump to pipe up move anchors
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 3 between Sta. 35+04 and 29+35 making 2 passes.Excessively long delays to move anchors because anchor barge 108 continues to struggle to lift anchors.Shut down for dump for 2.42 hours to pipe up and wash out line.Crew fixed leak on spud frame pipe.No delays to wash out pipe due to velocity dropsdigging shell.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in cut 3 2 passes. Anticipate bad WX remove pontoon line.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 3 between Sta. 31+01 and 25+52 making 2 passes when necessary.Sea conditons up to 5' are forecasted for next day so pontoon line was removed in preparation for bad weather.While moving anchors anchor barge 108 continues to struggle lifting anchors causing excessively long delay times.Several slow downs for dump to add pipe and rocket rainbow nozzle while pumping slopes at low tide.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to in Cut 3 w 2 passes. Mjr dly: Down for weather
ExtendedComments: The Alaska continued to dig in Cut 3 from station 25+78 and 22+24 making 2 passes.Down for 3.42 hours due to weather causing the cutter to slam into the bottom. 1.08 hours due to the ladder pump shutting off.Delays to move anchors are a longer then normal due to having to drag the stern anchor because the Anchor Barge 108 is struggling to pick up the anchors.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 3 making 2 passes.Mjr Dly: Rough WX can't hang anchors
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued to dig in Cut 3 making two passes from station 22+24 to 19+00 where they shut down to prepare to move to the next cut.The tide was too low to move the dredge at that time and it contuned to dig until theWX got to rough then they were not able to hang the anchors so the dredge was not moved.The material has gotten finer and the leverman say that it is digging a lotbetter then the pervious material.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: The dredge started digging in Cut 4 making 1 pass.Mjr Dly: Rough WX
ExtendedComments: Once the seas laid down and the tide came up high enough for the tug boats to get ot the anchors the dredge was moved to Cut 4 and resumed digging at 10:20.She dug from station 36+50 to 31+76 only making one pass .Once the dredge gets a little farther ahead the leverman will have to resume making two passes.The major delay was that the dredge was not able to move to a new cut right away but other minor delays were due to waiting on the dump to switch valves and moving anchors

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Dredge continues to dig in Cut 4.Mjr Dly: Wire coming off Pt Breast Anchor
ExtendedComments: The Alaska continues to dig in Cut 4 from station 31+76 to station 27+22 now making two passes.Shut down for 2.08 hours due to the wire coming off the Port Brest Anchor.The seas have been 2-4 feet over the last few days so the pontoon pipe has not been put back in the line yet.We will need the extra pipe to be able to reach the end of this cut; weather permitting the pipe will be put back in the line in the next couple of days.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Alaska continues to dig in Cut 4 making 2 passes.Mjr dly: Gasket falling out of pipe
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continues to dig in Cut 4 from station 27+22 to 23+06 making two passes.Shut down for 3.33 hours due to adding the pontoon pipeline to ensure that we will be able to reach the end of the cuts and have enough material.Once the Pontoon pipes were put in place and we started pumping on the line the gasket blew out of the pipe twice.That segment of pipe line was removed and will have to be replaced.We will not be able to dig the volume we need on the beach without 3 pontoons.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Alaska finished cut 4 and moved to cut 5making only 1 pass in cut 5.
ExtendedComments: The dredge stopped digging in Cut 4 about 11:45 they then washed out the line and prepared to move to the next cut.They didn't finish the whole cut due to the tide had they finished the cut it would have caused them to try and move anchors at low tide.When they reached station 22+67 they found shell fragments again causing the line to be washed out more frequently.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: The Alaska continues to dig in Cut 5 with no major delays.
ExtendedComments: The dredge dug in Cut 5 making two passes from station 29+25 to 23+29 there were no major delays however there were a few minor delays due to moving anchors.Also the last 120' pontoon was added to the line.Based on the current dig to pay the dredge should be able to reach all needed material with the current amount of float line.The air valve also had to be replaced due to a leak.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 5. Some shell at end of cut. Mjr dly: Wait on dump & move dredge
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 5 between Sta. 23+38 and 19+56. There is ~100 feet of travel left in Cut 5 before the dredge will move back to Cut 4.Periodically while digging in Cut 5 a few small pockets of shell were encountered and the dredge had to wash the line out due to velocity drops approx. 1 hour of delay.Several minor delays to wait on dump to switch valves because of berm width and pumping slopes.Extra pontoons will be made-up in the event the dredge will need to reach Cut 7.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Finish dig in Cut 5 cont. dig in Cut 4. Add 1 piece pontoon. Mjr dly: Anchor padeye repair
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska finished digging in Cut 5 and moved to Cut 4 to finish small are previously not dug due to moving out of cut because of weather.
