Permission was given to dig in areas F and G in the borrow area as long as we dig uniformly and don't have any isolated pockets of deep spots.Will now dig in Cuts 1 - 4 in sections F and G.One piece of 120' pontoon was added behind dredge.Major delay: Fix broken padeye on line stern line anchor.Minor delays: Wait on dump to switch valves move anchorsdredge

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Finish cut 4 and move to cut 3 areas F & G. Mjr dly: Shift cut wait on dumpswitch valve
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska finished digging in Cut 4 reaching Sta. 11+58 in section G in the borrow area and then shifted South to begin digging in Cut 3.Will continue to dig topbottom passes in Cut 3 up to Sta. 11+28 before moving to Cut 2.Major delays to shift the dredge to new cut and wait on dump to swtich valves and pipe up.Increasing beach delays because berm is starting to taper inwards so beach travel is increasing each day.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Finish Cut 3 and move to Cut 2; section F. No mjr delay. ~1 day of pumping remain
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska finished digging in Cut 3 sections F & G on this day and shifted South to begin digging Cut 2 in section F in the borrow area. Dredge will travel approx. 400' on both top and bottom passes in Cut 2 before moving to Cut 1 the ancitipated final cut for the project.No major delays on this day.Minormisc delays: Pick up crew boat beside dredge (line caught in propeller) move to Cut 2 shift anchors.No shut downs for the beach on this day.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Finish Cut 2 move to Cut 1. Dig a lot of shell causing several delayslow TE
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska finished digging in Cut 2 reaching Sta. 10+89 before shifting South to begin digging Cut 1.Once digging began in Cut 1 pockets of shell were almost immediately being dug between center-line and the STBD corner on the top pass.The velocity would drop as low as 9 ftsec and line washouts would last up to 2 hours before digging resumed.The dredge stepped back to dig the bottom pass in order to dig less shell and velocity slow raised to ~13 ftsec but washouts still occured.

ProjectName: TOWN OF HILTON HEAD- 2011 BEACH RENOUR.
BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 1 w pockets of shell causing low TE. Finish digging at 12:30 PM
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging in Cut 1 with continuing pockets of shell experienced while working.Low TE due to frequent velocity drops and having to wash out the line due to digging shell.Between Sta. 14+98 and 14+60 dredge was only making a 175' swing in order to avoid bad areas of shell in order to finish digging the project.As 12:30 PM the dredge began pumping water and washed out the line to finish the digging portion of the project.

BriefComments: Drdge Alaska began Digging at STA 1214+75
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska began its first full day of digging. She was digging a 430 ft cut digging 15 ft past both toes to ranges -215 on port and +215 on stbd taking 12 ft sets. Low prod day leaving ~19 ft in the beginning then went back to cover area again and clear grade. Re-setting carriage is taking a little longer than usual due to it being done manually by the crew. 1.33 hr of Misc Delay due to recalibration of the ladder depth as well as a die test. 5.25 hr delay due to work required on the Idler Barge.

BriefComments: Cont digging wBOC@28.5'. Low Production. Low TE.
ExtendedComments: The Alaska had a low production day mainly due to the low TE accomplished for the day due to the mechanincal delays. A combined 14.5 hrs down due to working on friction brake idler barge and dredge spud brake. The dredge resumed digging at 2130 hrs. After she resumed digging we switched to taking 8 ft sets due to cutter not being long enough to take 12 ft sets. The 0.5 hrs of miscellaneous are due to gps going out at 2330 hrs and working on fixing it.

BriefComments: Cont. Digging wBOC @ 28.5 Hi Prod due to Hi TE
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging increasing STAs facing outbound. Still digging 15 ft past each toe but changed from 12 ft to 8 ft sets. Misc. Delay due to work on GPS and Positioning Screen (00:00-00:20). Largest Delay for work on Ladder Pump (13:45-15:00). Fixes of Dishcarge Pipe being taken at time of repositioining as well as 2 hrs after to ensure no movement is occuring.

BriefComments: Alaska Cont Digging wBOC@28.5 at 8 ' sets
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging nearly matching the estimate wBOC@28.5 digging 15' outside the toe with 8 ft sets. Ladder Pump Kickoff from (14:35-18:10). Production hampered by need to slow velocity down to prevent cavitation due to inability of the pump to close the foot valve of the degasser system. Currently a valve from the Dredge Texas is being sent to Morgan City will be used to replace the valve currently on the Alaska.

BriefComments: Cont. Digging wBOC@28.5 at 8' sets
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued dredging wBOC@28.5 digging 15' outside the toe with 8 ft sets. Ladder Pump Delays (08:05-09:40; 11:35-14:10) for Kick off and Change Contacts. Degasser Foot Valve replacement from Dredge Texas installed on Alaska now working properly at full capacity. Switched to Heavier Anchor for Discharge Pipe to prevent movement due to the currentdredge guaranteeing disposal will occur within the ODMDS Area.

BriefComments: Dredge Alaska cont. digging wBOC@28.5 hi prod due to hi TE
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging as it has the past couple days wBOC@ 28.5 digging 15 ft outside each toe heading outbound with increasing STAs at 8 ft sets. High productivity due to high time efficiency of 88.5% (compared to estimated 72%). Ladder Pump Delay (16:20-17:20) for kickoff and Mechanical Delay (17:20-17:30) for fixing port side engine. Maintenance performed during down time includes greasing the A-Frame and Ladder.

BriefComments: Cont. Digging wBOC@ 28.5 dig over Pipeline
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging but changed digging instructions for Pipeline (BOC@22 no digging outside toe lock cutter etc.) Misc. Delay due to Pipeline Dredge Procedures. 0.75 hrs (14:45-15:30) for Ladder Calibration (tested Water LevelPressure Sensor and worked well within 110 ft of Tape Meas Method). 0.75 hrs (20:40-21:25) to put chain on cutter for digging over the pipeline. Dredging over pipeline went smoothly. Low Production due to slowdown for pipeline procedures.

BriefComments: Finished Digging over Pipeline Changed Direction
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska finished digging over a pipeline with no incidents. Once finished the Dredge changed position and direction from 05:15 - 11:15 and is now digging inbound. Mechanical delay (12:50-15:30) due to hoffer valve repairs. Slowed down the Cutterhead RPMs and pipeline velocity to get a better density (preventing excessive turbidity) to get better survey data. Low Productivity due to Low TE.

BriefComments: Digging on one engine; slow down cutter to 13RPM cleaned material around pipeline
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska cut outbound to the pipepline where we cleaned up the residual material that was left from our first pass over the pipe. The Dredge then was moved from station 1269+05 to 1217+00 resulting in a 8.17hr delay (12:00to 20:10).Due to contract specs the discharge was moved from the ODMDS West to ODMDS East where it is now discharging. The cutter was slowed down from 30 RPMto 13 RPM. This has increased productivity and the quality of the surveys we are now getting.

BriefComments: Digging on stbd engine; narrowed cut 5' on each toe digging at -27' with 12' steps
ExtendedComments: Cutter is running at 12-15rpm and swinging 420ft. The stbd engine is running between 65-70%. The plan is to add restrictor plate to float line to allow for engines to turn at a higher rpm but material to flow at lower velocity. The cuts are looking good with the cutter at slower rpm and ladder at -27'. We continue inbound toward ANR pipelines expected to reach buffer of pipelines Monday or Tuesday. 1040ft of pontoon pipe had to be removed when the flanged steel pipe kinked while they were working on it.

BriefComments: Digging on Prt Eng ladder lwrd to -27.5' degasser priming pump failed
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continues to dig inbound. After lowering the BOC to -27.5' cross sections showed that we are leaving -22.5 and a little deeper in the corners. The degasser priming pump failed last night and the system has not been working since. The priming motor will be changed out later this afternoon. Patches are being welded on the hull of the skidder barge and should be back tomorrow. Discharging 4000' from CL due to gas line. The Stbd engine only is running @ 75-80% with restriction plate inline.

BriefComments: Digging Prt Eng @ 80-90% digging the same leaving -23' - -24' degasser down
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continues to dig inbound. Still digging with BOC to -27.5 w 12' steps; we are leaving -23.5' of water. The degasser priming pump was changed but still did not prime. It was discovered that the foot valve & screens were missing at the end of the hose. down for 4.08 hrs due to spring bearing. The Prt engine only is running @ 80-90% with restriction plate inline. The Stbd turbo seal is leaking. Using 3rd crew boat to be with the Derrick while they are working on subline at God's Pass.

BriefComments: Digging Prt Eng @ 80-90% Replaced wrong fuse in STBD eng (9.33hr delay)
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continues to dig inbound. Still digging with BOC to -27.5 w 12' steps; we are leaving -23.5' of water. Seeing good production after morning delay. While trouble shooting the STBD main engine a blown fuse was found. It was found that the wrong size fuse was inline. Thedegasser is still having problems priming. Approaching the ANR gas line it is expected to be there Tuesday night or Wednesday morning. Using 3rd crew boat to be with the Derrick while they are working on sub line at God's Pass.

BriefComments: Prt Engine Only @ 80-90% w restrictor plate inline. Good Production w Low Down time
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continues digging inbound with BOC @ -27.5' and taking 12' steps. The tug ms. Melinda dragged a line anchor updown the channel infront of the dredge for 10 hours to help remove the gas from the material. The leverman did notice a reduction in rams and could swing faster in some areas. We are approaching sublines and are tracking swing anchors relative to ANR pipelines closely. Still disposing material 4000' from centerline due to pipeline in disposal area.

BriefComments: Prt Engine Only @ 80-90% added 1000' float hose down to replace swing wire (3.67hr)
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continues digging inbound with BOC @ -27.5' and taking 12' steps. The tug ms. Melinda dragged a line anchor updown the channel infront of the dredge to remove gas from material reduction in rams and faster swing rates in some areas. added 1000' of float line to our discharge line. Still disposing material 4000' from centerline due to pipeline in disposal area. Developed digging stragity for approaching ANR pipeline. Will calibrate ladder and beggin at STA 1160+00.

BriefComments: Prt engine only at 80-90%. Picked BOC up to -25' MLG with 8' steps. RNG 205 to 50 buffer
ExtendedComments: The dredge Alaska continues digging inbound with BOC @ -27.5' and taking 12' steps until STA 1160+00; changed BOC to -25' with 8 ft sets and swing RNG to 205 on port and varied on the srbd with the south ANR pipeline buffer. Still disposing material 4000' from centerline due to pipeline in disposal area. Met with USAC and ANR rep to discuss digging over ANR pipeline @ 22' with cutter inorder to leave less material Bullgang laid the 2600' of subline from bird islandand set PVC to mark subline location.

BriefComments: PRT eng only 80-90% BOC @ -25' w 8' sets changed to BOC at -22' w 4' sets @12:15
ExtendedComments: Alaska dug around ANR pipeline. Fishished digging area1 frm STA 1160+00-1152+18 frm green toe (RGE +205) to 50' buffer. BOC was @ -25' MLG and taking 8' sets; leaving 21.5'-23.0' of water. Moved the dredge back to STA 1160+00 chained the cutter and performed a ladder calibration. Dug 22'+tide from 50ft buffer to Red Toe (RGE-205) & took 4' sets for full carridge backed up and recovered the area taking 12' sets. Still disposing material 4000' from centerline due to pipeline in disp area.

BriefComments: PRT eng only 80-90% Cutter chained off.BOC @ 22'+tide w 4'sets backup & then 12'sets
ExtendedComments: Still digging the ANR pipeline area.Digging Area2 from 1160+00 to 1152+18 from Red Toe to 50' buffer. Taking a full carriage of 4'sets then backing up and taking 12'sets. Survey shows 19.5-20.5' of water. Also dug full channel (RNG -205-205) w same dig pattern as above from 1151+00 to 1148+00. After we finish the area Dr will turn around and dig North to South towards ANR line. Still discharging 4500' from centerline due to gas line. Misc delay due to GL142 kicking off.

BriefComments: PRT eng only 80-90% Cutter chained off.BOC @ 22'+tide w 4'sets backup & then 12'sets
ExtendedComments: Still digging the ANR pipeline area. Finished digging Area3 from 1151+00 to 1148+00 full channel with cutter chained off. Ladder at 22'+tide taking full carraige of 4'sets then backing up and taking 12'sets. CND survey shows leaving 19-20.5' of water. Dr moved to 1136+60 @830 to dig outbound over pipeline to 1153+00. Cutter is still chained off and ladder @22'. Digging from 50'buffer to Green Toe. Still discharging mat'l `4000' from centerline due to gas line

BriefComments: PRT eng only 80-90% Cutter chained off.BOC @ 22'+tide w 4'sets backup & then 12'sets
ExtendedComments: Still digging the ANR pipeline area. Digging Area4 outbound to 1153+00 full channel with cutter chained off. Ladder at 22'+tide taking full carriage of 4'sets then backing up and takin12'sets. Digging from 50'buffer to Green Toe. CND survey shows leaving 19-20.5' of water. Still discharging material ~4000' from centerline due to gas line crossing the area.

BriefComments: PRT eng only 80-90% Cutter chained off.BOC @ 22'+tide w 12'sets
ExtendedComments: The dredge finished digging Cut 7 over the ANR pipelines taking 12ft sets cutter chained off holding a depth of 22.0ft and swinging the full channel. @10:30 Dr moved back to Sta 1129+00 unchained the cutter BOC@27.5ft swinging the full channel until Sta 1134+00.Tug Newman dragged pontoon pipe for 5 hours in Contago Pipeline area Survey showed that the dragging operation is working. The dredge has been discharging material approx. 4500 ft from centerline due to gas line.

BriefComments: Still in ANR pipelineCutter unchaine.BOC @ 27.5' 12'sets@1136+52 BOC@25' 8'sets
ExtendedComments: Dug to 1136+52 BOC@27.5 w12'sets then picked ladder up to 25' w 8' sets-swinging Red toe to 50ft buffer. Tug Newman drgged for 5hrs in Contango pipeline area. Survey showed drgging ops is working but more time needed. Still discharging matl ~4500' frm centerline due to gas line. Prt Eng only running @ 80-90% w restrictor plate inline. MSI installed new flex pieces-align & secure the exhaust pipe for stbd pmp eng turbo. Still a small leak but plan to switch over to stbd engine @ next shut down & test.

BriefComments: Dug to 1149+50BOC 25' w 8' sets-swing clean up 1131+00 ladder BOC 27w12'sets
ExtendedComments: Dug to 1149+50 ladder BOC @ 25' w 8' sets-swinging Red toe to 50ft buffer then picked ladder up to 1131+25 BOC@27 w12' sets in cleanup area and will lower the the to 27.5' after finishing the cleanup area. From Sta 1131+00 to 1129+00 will be cleaning up material left while digging outbound. Still discharging matl ~4500' frm centerline due to gas line. Prt Eng only running @ 80-90% w restrictor plate inline.

BriefComments: Dug to STA 1118+15 with BOC at 27 ft w 12' sets. Main delay for cleaning cutter & UWP
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska finished digging around the ANR Pipelines today. She then continued to dig inbound. The dredge dug to STA 1118+15 with the BOC @ 27' swinging a full cut of 420ft and w 12' sets. The Alaska is still discharging materialapprox.4500' from center line due to a gas line. The Alaska is approx 2200 ft away from crossing the Embridge gas line. Please note that we have found there is an issue with the swing speed. We are working on fixing the issue.

BriefComments: Continued Digging inbound. Dropped BOC to 27.5' at 1030 w 12' sets.
ExtendedComments: The Alaska continued to dig inbound to STA 1108+22. At 1030 the BOC was dropped to 27.5 w 12' sets and a full channel swing of 420'. The longest delay today was for traffic (0.58 hrs). The issue with the swing speed has been improved but not completely resolved. We are continuing to look into the situation.

BriefComments: Continued digging inbound to sta 1099+19. 0.83 hr delay for calib ladder. Ended @ pipeline
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound to STA 1099+19 with BOC @ 27.5 and a swing of 420 ft w 12 foot sets. The day ended right before entering the buffer zone for the pipeline in the channel. The longest delay today was for calibrating the ladder (0.83 hrs) which was done before we entered the pipeline zone.

BriefComments: Dug Inbound over Enbridge Pipe. Jumped to Sta 108+900. 8' setsBOC @ 26.5 @ 1230
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound and passed over the Enbridge Pipe with 12' sets and BOC at 25'. She then jumped to sta 1089+00 and switch to 8 foot sets w BOC @ 26.5' at 1230. The weather was too rough to get any good surveys today. The longest delay today was for the jump to the new cut STA (3.92 hrs).

BriefComments: Clean up 1096+10 to 1099+63. Jumped to 1089+24 (2.25 hr delay). Done w pipeline digs
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska began digging outbound from STA 1092+54 to 1096+10. As we approached 1096+10 survey showed that there was remaining material between sta 1096+10 to 1099+63 so she went back over the stations to clean it up. Durring clean up the BOC was at 25.5 ft with 12ft sets and a swing width of 420ft. The longest delay to day was for changin cuts (2.25 hrs). Befroe and after clean up BOC @ 26.5 w 8ft sets

BriefComments: Conituned to dig inbound. at 0800 droped to 27.5 and 12' sets. No major delays
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska coninued digging inbound to STA 1075+94. at 0800 she dropped the BOC to 27.5' and startd 8' sets. There were no major delays today only small delays for traffic and anchor shifting. She achieved a high TE of 92% but her dig cy wh still fell below the estimate.

BriefComments: Contind digging inbound to STA 1066+79. BOC @ 27.5' with 12' sets. 2.5hr delay clean pumps
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued to dig inbound to STA 1066+79 with the BOC @ 27.5 and 12' sets. The Jack newman was dragging a pipe infront of the dredge to remove gas from the material. She was ale to achieved 7264 cy digwh with a TE of 81.5%.

BriefComments: Contd diggin inbound to STA 1056+02. 12' sets BOC at 27.5. Dragged pipe infront of dredge
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued to dig inbound to STA 1056+02 with 12' set and BOC @ 27.5'. It was a great day for production with a cy dighr of 8336 cywkhr and travel of 1070 ft. Yesterday we had a tug tow a pipe along the bottom in front of the dredge. This released the gas in the material and allowed the Alaska to dig faster and be more productive. Longest delay today was for cleaning the pumps (X3) 1.5 hrs

BriefComments: Dredge dug inward to Sta1043+40. Continued dragging pipe in front. BOC @28.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound from Sta 1056+02 to 1043+40. Production was great as the dredge moved a total of 1260ft. Step size remained at 12ft and BOC at 28ft respectively. This dig plan in addtition to dragging in front is working well for the material. The longest delay was to clean the UWP. A material sample was collected and from the sample a density of 1.36KgL was calculated.

BriefComments: Dredge was down due to a choke in pipeline. BOC dropped to 28.5ft w12ft steps.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging inward. Dredge was down off and on trying to find choke in pipeline. Pipe was removed from and then returned into the line.Vessel traffic is picking up in the channel. BOC was dropped to 28.5ft. Dredge traveled 910ft up to Sta 1034+30.

BriefComments: Dredge dug inward to Sta 1020+35. BOC @28.5. 1.23hr delay for vessel traffic.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging up to Sta 1020+35. All non essential equiptment was towed into safe harbor in preparation of the coming storm. Longest delay was 1.23hr for vessels returning inbound due to coming storms. BOC was at 28.5ft. Very good production day.

BriefComments: Dredge resumed digging inbound @0400hrs on sta1021+25.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska resumed digging after the Major Weather Delay at 0400hrs. She traveled 1211ft while taking 12ft steps and a BOC at 28.5ft. At 0800hrs the second engine came online. Longest delay came from cleaning and changing contact on the ladder pump. The Miss Melinda resumed dragging in front of the dredge to release built up gasses.

BriefComments: Dredge traveled 1688. BOS picked up to 28' and ranges brought into 5' off toe.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska traveled 1688ft. The longest delays she endured were 0.83hrs for the main pump and 1.42hrs for moving anchors. The BOS was raised to 28ft with step size being the same in order to reduce overdigging. The swing width was also reduced to 5ft past the toe of the channel in an effort to reduce overdigging in the toe.

BriefComments: Alaska dug from Sta992+26 to Sta 977+81. Delay of 4.33hr for travel spud wire.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound from Sta 992+26 to Sta 977+81. The BOC is at 28.0ft with step sizes of 12ft. She is swinging 5ft passed the toe on each side of the channel. The major delay was 4.33hr for repair of the travel spud wire. She averaged 79ft of travel per hour for a total of 1445ft for the day.

BriefComments: Contind diggin inbound. BOC @ 28' swing 5ft past each toe. Prim delay clean Ladder pump
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued diggin inbound from STA 977+81 to 962+96 with BOC at 28' and 12' sets. The dredge is now swinging 5 foot past each toe to make a full swing of 410 feet. Primary delay for cleaning ladder pump X3 (1.29hrs). Good TE at 80.25% and travel of 76 ft per hour.

BriefComments: Contind diggin inbound to sta 951+31. BOC @ 28' 12' sets. Dragged pipe for gas release
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued diggin inbound to STA 962+96 to 951+31 with the BOC at 28' and 12' sets. Yesterday we began dragging a pipe infront of the dredge to release gas. The dredge achieved a TE of 82.7% and a digwk hr of 9170. We will continue to drag in hopes of breaking the 10000 yardswork hours mark.

BriefComments: Contd digging inbound to STA 944+09. Long delay for pontoon pipe repairs and main gen 6.5h
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska Continued digging inbound from STA 951+31 to 944+09 with BOC @ 28' and 12' foot sets. She is swinging 5' past each toe with a full width of 410'. The dredge expierenced many delays today totaling 10.89 hrs. The longest delay at 4.33hrs was to repair a pontoon pipe connection that came apart. The Tug Jack Newman continued to drag pipe in front of the dredge to release gas from the material. TE and production were lower then noraml today due to the various delays.

BriefComments: Contind digging inbound to STA 932+00. BOC @ 28' 12' sets. No major delays. good TE @ 89%
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued diggin inbound from STA 944+09 to STA 932+00 with BOC at 28' and 12' sets. She is swinging 5 foot past each toe for a total swing width of 410'. The Alaska had no major delays today which allowed her to cover just over 1200 feet. She was still unable to break the 10000 dig cywkhr. We will continue to drag pipe to release gas from the mateiral.

BriefComments: Contnd dig inbound to STA 920+432 BOC@28' 12' sets 410' width. took out 120' pipe
ExtendedComments: The Dregde Alaska continued to dig inbound from STA 932+00 to 920+42 with BOC @ 28' and 12' sets and a total swing width of 410' (5 foot past each toe). The Jack Newman was dragging in front of the dredge while she dug to release gas. She was still hitting some gas while digging so we had the drag pipe lowered. A hole in a pontoon pipe with the new type connection casued the longest delay of 1.33hrs. The pipe was removed. The line length is now 5520ft.

BriefComments: Contind digging inbound to STA 908+32. BOC @ 28.2' 12' sets. 410' swing width.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging in bound from STA 920+42 to 908+32. The BOC was dropped to 28.2' in order to get more material in the middle of the channel. Acording to the CND it helped. It was apparent from PLC data and cross sections that the material is much denser around the middle of the channel (pipeline density = 1.3) and much less dense near the toes (pipeline density = 1.12). The swing width is 410'. The longest delay today was to clean the cutter and ladder pump of wire (1.67hr

BriefComments: Cntd diggin inbound to Sta 903+72 til 10am when a elec. delay occured (13.25hrs)
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued to dig inbound from STA 908+32 to 903+72 until 1000 when she encountered an electrical delay for the UWP. The Pump was checked and it was determined to be fine. It was later discovered that there was an electrical issue with the contactors for the UWP in the engine room. This delay lasted the rest of the day (13.25 hrs). The dredge is waiting for an electrician to arrive. Due to this delay we were only able to achieve a 33% TE and fell short of meeting the production est.

BriefComments: Cont delay for UWP contactors. Started up at 805. Dug inbound to STA 894+74. BOC @ 28.2'
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska started the day continuing to stop for the UWP contactors delay. At 0805 she started up after the contactor cooled down. A new UWP motor controller contact assembly was received today and will be swapped out when the old one trips out again. The Alaska dug inbound from STA 903+72 to 894+74 with BOC at 28.2' and 12' sets. Total swing width of 410' (5 feet past each toe)

BriefComments: Contd to dig inbound to STA 882+53. BOC at 28.2' swg width 410. 1.42hr delay clean cutter
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska Continued to dig inbound from STA 894+74 to 882+53 with BOC at 28.2' and a swing width of 410' (5 ft past each toe). The Jack Newman contind to drag infront of the dredge. Boats continue to run aground up ahead of the dredge. A material sample will be taken soon to check on density and material conditions in that area as it seems to be sand. Good TE at 85% allowed travel of 1221 ft. DP of 1.4 due to existing deep trenches of less dense material on toes. Degasser cont to not work properly

BriefComments: Cont. Digging inbound to STA 870+84. Switched out UWP contactors at 0830 (3.58hr)
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound from STA 882+53 to 870+84 with BOC at 28.2' and a swing width of 410' and 12' sets. Today at 0830 we shut down for 3.58hrs to switch out a faulty UWP coil module with a new one. The average swing speed for the day was 48 fps. The production is at 10897 cywk hr and the discharge velocity dropped to 22fps. Please note that at 14:35 we change over to only one engine. We were able to travel 1169 ft yesterday at a TE of 79.29% (61.43 lfwkhr).

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound to STA 859+79. BOC @ 28.2' 12' sets. Material mudsoft clat 1.7kgL
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound from STA 870+84 to 859+79 with BOC @ 28.2' 12' sets and a 410' total swing width. The longest delay today was to change out the second UWP module (3.75hrs). Tug Jack Newman continues to drag pipe now hanging from the barge to release gas. A sample was taken and it was found that the material consists of mud and soft clay with a density of 1.7 kgL. Decent travel at 1105 ft with a TE of 75%. It is believed that the heavy clay is slowing down the travel of th

BriefComments: Cont. diggin inbound to STA 847+12. Turned off degasser jets 1230 no effect. BOC 28.2
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued diggin inbound from STA 859+79 to 847+12 with BOC at 28.2' a swing width of 410' and 12' ses. It should be noted that at the start of this day there was an object stuck in the pump which caused reduced production until 0810 when they cleaned the suction. Cleanning it earlier would have made up for the delay time with production. It should also be noted that at 1230 they turned off the degasser jets. This had no effect on production which leads us to believe the jets do not work.

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound to STA 837+14. Switched to strb engine. BOC @ 28.2'
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska cont digging inbound from STA 847+12 to 837+14 with BOC @ 28'2' 12' sets and total swing width 410'. Today we switched to the stb engine at 0950. The longest delay today was to weld on a strb swing sheave (2.67hrs). TE fell to 71.88% today due to multiple delays. TE only allowed us to travel 998 LF but we were still able to pump 10430 cyhr. Fuel and Water was transfered to the dredge today; she took on 95000 gallons of fuel and 20000 gallons of water. Vel = 23fps. Degasser is not on.

BriefComments: Dredge dug inbound. BOC@28.2 w12ft steps. Dragging cont.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued working inbound traveling 1120ft. The Jack Newman continued to drag in front of the dredge to release gas trapped in the material. Since the degasser is not working the gas in the material causes the pump to ram up and limit production. On two different occasions the UWP wouldn't start up causing an electrical delay of 0.5hrs. The longest delay was for cleaning the cutterhead.

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound to Sta 817+15. Electrical problems with UWP. BOC@28.2ft
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued encountering difficulties swinging due to gas trapped in the seabed. The tug Jack Newman continues to drag infront of the dredge to try to release the built-up gas. The major delay of 3.5 hrs was due electrical problems with the UWP. The UWP has been tripping during start-ups. The electrical contacts were switched and there has not been a problem since. The BOC remains at 28.2ft while the dredge is taking 12ft steps.

BriefComments: Dug inbound to Sta806+71. BOC@28.2ft w12' steps. UWP electric problem caused delay.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued having electrical problems with the UWP causing the major delay. Crew is working with mgt in order to get this resolved. Extended traffic delay due to tow running aground behind dredge. ProductionWH increased from previous days. The trapped gas is limiting the swing ability and production. Most of the gas being encountered is along the toes where the drag barge cannot reach.

BriefComments: Traveling northbound up to Sta797+09. Major Delay was electrical prob w UWP
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued having electrical problems with the UWP (at start-up pump trips off having to let components cool off before it can be properly engaged). Electrician is coming to the Dredge on Monday to work on this. The Jack Newman continues to drag ahead of the dredge to release pent up gas. Dragging is improving production but we are still having problems with gas in the corners where the drag bar cannot reach. The degasser is still not working. The BOC is @28.2ft while taking steps of 12ft.

BriefComments: Alaska cont. having problems w UWP. Jack Newman cont. dragging. BOC@28.2 w12ft step
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging northbound towards Sta 787+31. Problems continued with the UWP contacts causing a total delay of 4.67hrs. Electrician will be out on Monday to address the issue. The Jack Newman continues to drag ahead of the dredge. We are still encountering gas along the toes of the channel where the Newman is unable to drag. Material is getting heavier and is stacking up in the discharge area. More clay is being encountered in the material.

BriefComments: BOC@28.2 w 12ft steps 10ft past toes. Major electrical delay for UWP.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging up to Sta 780+85. The UWP caused a delay of 9.83hrs. Company electrician will be on site on Monday to work on this. The swing pattern was widened from 5'to 10' past each toe because the denser material isn't falling into the channel as much. The Newman continued dragging in front of the dredge. The dredge is encountering gas especially along the toes where Newman cannot drag. Dredge safety drills completed today: fire drill abondon ship drill and man overboard drill.

BriefComments: BOC@28.2 w 12ft steps 10ft past toes Major delay due to UWP
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound to Station 771+06 with BOC at 28.2' and 12' sets. The Alaska continued to have a swing length of 420' (10' past each toe) due to the denser material.The Jack Newman continued to drag in front of the Alaska to reduce gas. Trapped gas continues to be a problem especially in the corners where the Newman cannot drag. Problems continued with the contacts with the UWP. Equipment for Bird Island was loaded at Morgan City and transported to dredge for fueling.

BriefComments: BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps 10ft past toes Cont. electrical problems w UWP
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inboundto station 761+25 with BOC at 28.5 with 12 steps.Marsh buggies and ramp barge fueled and mobilized to Bird Island.The Alaska continued to have elecrtical problems with the underwater pump.Due to large amounts of gas on the toe the Dr was setting ahead just inside the toe but survey showed we were leaving material.Dr. is now back to setting ahead on the toes. Morning survey showed less material is being left.

BriefComments: BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps 10ft past toes. Major delays were due to UWP.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska contiued digging inbound to sta 753+69 BOC@28.5.Dr. continued to have problems with the UWP. Ed Sajdera and Gary Fortin were on board continuing the investigation with the UWP. The Dr. continued to to set ahead on the toes and surveys show that the toes are now clear.

BriefComments: BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps inbound to station 744+28. Major delay due to cleaning UWP (1.25hr)
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound to station 744+28 with BOC @28.5 with 12ft steps. There were no major delays. UWP has not shut down after restart but will continue to monitor. The Jack Newman is continuing to drag in front of the dredge to reduce gas but we are still experiencing gas in the toes.

BriefComments: BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps inbound to station734+12.No major delars.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound to station 734+12 with BOC @28.5 with 12ft steps. Jack Newman continues to drag infront of the Alaska to reduce gas. At 6:45 Dr. began to take on fuel. Late yesterday evening it was reported that the Dr. is starting to cut into sand.We will continue to monitor this by taking a soil sample off of the cutter head.

BriefComments: BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps inbound to station724+55.No major delays.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound to station 724+55 with BOC @28.5 with 12ft steps.The Jack Newman continued to drag in front of the dredge to reduce gas.Equipment barges were towed to Bird Island in preparation for the rough seas caused by incoming storm. Misc. delay was due to work on the hoffer valve. We gathered a material sample yesterday and found that we are now into 95% mudsilt and 5% fine sand.

BriefComments: BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps inbound to station 715+18 w no major delays.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued to dig inbound BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps to station 715+18.The Jack Newman continued to drag ahead of the dredge. The weather began to pick up later in the day. The misc. delay above was caused by adjusting the wire on the stbd spud drum.

BriefComments: BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps inbound to station 707+58.Maj.Delay (3.58) move disch wash line
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued to dig with BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps inbound to station 707+58.The Jack Newman continued to drag ahead of the Alaska to reduce gas.Major delay (3.58hrs) was caused by moving anchors washing line out and moving the discharge. High winds up to 45 mph kept the survey department from running a daily conditional.

BriefComments: BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps inbound to station 698+25 w no major delays.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued to dig with BOC@28.5 w 12ft steps inbound to station 698+25.The Alaska had no major delays with the biggest delay caused by traffic.Jack Newman continued to drag infront of the dredge.

BriefComments: Alaska cont digging inbound to Sta690+04. Second engine online at 2340. No major delay
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska has continued digging northbound traveling a total of 821ft. Cutter amps are up due to the density of the material. Dredge went down a number of times to clean foreign debris from the pumps. A total of 1.67hrs was needed to clean the main pump. The second engine was put online at 2340. BOC is @ 28.2ft while swinging 10ft past toes. Dredge is closing in on the end of the option Sta 670+00.

BriefComments: Cont digging northbound. No major delays. BOC@28.2. Approaching Bird Island.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging inward up to Sta 681+13. @Sta 670+00 dredge plans to move to ahead to begin pumping onto Bird Island. Dredge had no major delays but had multiple short delays to clean the pumps. Cleaning the pumps often is improving hourly production. Alaska continued digging with both engines. BOC @28.2 while swinging 10ft past the toes taking 12ft steps.

BriefComments: Continued digging inbound. BOC raised to 28.0ft. No major delays.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging northbound up to Sta 673+52. At Sta 670+00 dredge is moving to approx Sta 565+00 to begin pumping on Bird Island. Cutter rpm's are up due to the density of the material. The Jack Newman continued dragging in front of the dredge to release the trapped gas. The longest delay (.58hrs) was to break the line in order to find a choke. At 1000 the cutter was raised to 28.0ft while continuing to take 12ft steps.

BriefComments: Cont. digging until 670+00. BOC@28.0 w12ft steps. No major delays.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging up to Sta 670+00 @ 1130hrs and then switched to subjob 041. Cleaning the main pump (4x) caused the longest total delay (1.83hrs). Dredge continues to encounter gas especially along the toes where the Jack Newman cannotdrag. Cutter speeds remain high.

BriefComments: Dredge stopped digging in 040 to move tow Sta 580+85 subjob 045. No major delays.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging working in subjob 040 until 0935 @ Sta 663+50. Dredge continued to encounter gas especially along the toes. The longest delays were for vessel traffic (3x) and to clean the main pump (2x) for (0.75hrs) each.

BriefComments: Cont digging inbound pumping on BI. Swing width changed to 215 on GT. BOC@28.0 w12'
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging northbound pumping on Bird Island. At 1345 the swing width was widened to 215 on the green toe. Longest delay (2.99hrs) was mechanical for wires to change the hoist wire of the anchor barge and change pad eye on anchor barge. Dredge is encountering gas in trapped seabed. Velocity was lowered and density raised from previous day with no noticable production difference.

BriefComments: Cont. pumping on BI. Electrical problem wPLC. BOC @28.0ft w 8ft steps
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging Northbound up to Sta 568+25. Dredge had a number of delays (5x) to clean the main pump for a total of 2.08hrs. Electrical problems with the PLC caused a 1.5hr delay. Electrician to come onsite on 1010 to investigate. Step size brought into 8ft from 12ft after surveys showed that template wasn't cleared. Sample collected off of the ladder @ Sta 571+60 showed a density of 1.70kgL.

BriefComments: Cont. pumping onBOC @28.0ft w 8ft steps maj delay packing main pumpwashing out line
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging Northbound up to Sta 562+72. with BOC 28.0 with 8 ft steps. The dredge incurred a number of small delays. The major delays caused from packing the main pump (2.38hrs) and washing out the line(Misc 2.21hrs). Conditional surveys show that we are leaving 23' of water and toes look good.

BriefComments: Con. digging inbound pumping on BIBOC 28.0 w 8 ft steps maj del thrust bearing (1.17)
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging Northbound up to Sta 554+69. with BOC @ 28.0 with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island.The largest delay was a Mech. delay of 1.17hrs due to fixing the thrust bearing. The Jack Newman drug in front of the dredge which seemed to help reduce gas and increased the travel.

BriefComments: Con. digging inbound pumping on BIBOC 28.0 w 8 ft steps. maj del eng leak (1.16)
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging Northbound up to Sta 545+58. BOC @ 28.0 with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East.The largest delay was due to an Engine Room Port Eng Oil Leak (1.16hrs). The Jack Newman continued to drag in front of the dredge which seems to help reduce gas and help increase the travel. At station 550+74 Dr widened out the cut. She is now digging 15' past Each Toe in order to clear both toes better. Released one short arm Marsh Buggy yesterday from the Dump.

BriefComments: Con. digging inbound pumping on BI. BOC 28.0 w 8 ft steps. Maj Del:Fixing Liner Bolt
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska continued digging Northbound. BOC @ 28.0 with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East.The main delays were due to Fixing a broken liner bolt on the Main Pump (1.17hrs) and removing pontoon (1.33hrs). The Jack Newman continued to drag in front of the dredge which seems to help reduce gas and help increase the travel. Material on dump doesnt seem to be building up.

BriefComments: Con. digging inbound pumping on BI. BOC 27.0 w 8 ft steps. Maj Del:Clean UWP & MP (2.42)
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska continued digging Northbound. BOC was raised to 27' at STA 534+20 with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East.The main delay was due to cleaning UWP & MP (6:00 - 8:25). The Jack Newman continued to drag in front of the dredge which seems to help reduce gas and help increase the travel. Material on dump doesnt seem to be building up.

BriefComments: Con. digging inbound pumping on BI. BOC 27.0 w 8 ft steps. Maj Del:fix bolt on MP (1.05)
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska continued digging Northbound. BOC @ 27' with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East.The main delay was due to fixing liner bolt on MP. The Jack Newman continued to drag in front of the dredge which seems to help reduce gas and help increase the travel. Material on dump doesnt seem to be building up.

BriefComments: Con. digging inbound pumping on BI. BOC 26.0 w 8 ft steps. No maj. delays
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska continued digging Northbound. BOC @ 26' with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East. Based on conditional surveys and cutter head sample the dredged moved the cutter head up to 26'. The largest delays were due to boat traffic (1.34hrs). The Jack Newman continued to drag infront of the dredge to reduce gas.

BriefComments: Con. digging inbound pumping on BI. BOC 26.0 w 8 ft steps Maj Del check engines add pont
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska continued digging Northbound. BOC @ 26' with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East. Maj. delays were caused from checking all the engines and adding pontoon pipe.The other repairs in Mech. due to the travel spud that would not start up. (.42hrs) The Jack Newman continued to drag ahead of the dredge to reduce gas.

BriefComments: Con. digging inbound to Sta 49329 w BOC@27. Trav back for clean up.
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska continued digging Northbound. BOC @ 26' with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East.Conditional surveys indicated that we were leaving material on the Green Side.@10:10 the dredged moved back to stat 503+40 and dropped the cutter down to 27' (Misc 1.58hrs)and cleaned Green Side only for 12 hrs. The cleaned up material was not included into the dig and pay.

BriefComments: Con digging inbound pumping BI. BOC 27.0 w8 ft steps Maj del add pipefix swg wire (2.5
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska continued digging Northbound. BOC @ 27.0 with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East. Major delays (2.58hrs) were caused from adding pontoon pipe and fixing the roll eye on the starboard swing wire. A soil sample from the cutter head shows we has dropped from 1.68 kgl to 1.33 kgl and proves the material is becoming more sandy.

BriefComments: Con digging inbound pumping BI. BOC 27.0 w8' set. Dug into rock late last night
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska continued digging Northbound. BOC @ 27.0 with 8 ft steps and continued pumping on to Bird Island East.Dredge incurred several small delays dealing with anchors and continuously cleaning pumps.Late in the night the dredge began digging into solid rock. Night operator decided to lower swing range on port side to 195 to aviod and once passed returned to 215. Conditional surveys show material being left behind on the red side. We will be pulling back to dig the rest of the material.

BriefComments: Finished to 475+00 clean up 9.67 hrs. @19:40 Dr waiting for daylight to move to 570+50
ExtendedComments: The Dr Alaska dug Northbound until 474+50 w BOC @ 27.0 with 8 ft steps pumping on to Bird Island East. Survey showed matr'l was left on the red side.Dr. pulled back 900 ft and proceeded to clean out red side and finished digging clean up at 19:40. Preperation were made by night crew so that the morning crew would have everything ready to move the dredge safely in the daylight.

BriefComments: Dr. moved to 570+50 clean up moving outbound Maj del moving dredge in daylight(14.25)
ExtendedComments: Dredge went on Standby Monday night to wait for daylight to move the dredge to STA 570+50.Began moving the dredge around 7:30 and began digging at 14:15. All of yesterdays was Clean up doing 12' sets with BOC @ 27'.Clean up will continue until Sta 579+40 then Dr will continue diggin at 8ft sets with BOC @ 28'.

BriefComments: Digging outbound pumping on BI. BOC@28.5. Finished clean up.
ExtendedComments: Around 06:00 Dr. finished clean up and began digging un-dredged material. At 8:35 dropped cutter to 28.5'. There were no major delays through out the day. Conditional survey on 102412show the Dr. leaving material.The dredge will move back and perform clean up from Sta 581+00 to 586+50.At Sta 586+50 the Dr. is switching to 6ft set with BOC@ 28.5'.

BriefComments: Cont digging southbound discharging on BI. Pulled back to clean. 2-passes w.BOC@26.0
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging outbound up to Sta 588+04. After CND surveys showed tpl wasn't cleared dredge pulled back and cleaned from Sta 581+00 to 586+97. After cleaning she dug with the BOC @26.0 w12ft steps while taking 2-passes. Jack Newman continues to drag infront of the Dredge to release trapped gas.

BriefComments: Alaska cont digging outbound. New dig pattern used. Major Delay changing breaker in PLC.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging outbound to 593+47. Changed dig pattern to dig out complete anchor set digging the first pass at 22' pulling back and digging second at 27'. Traveled top pass to 593+74 and bottom pass to 593+47. Jack Newman continued dragging to release trapped gas. Major delay (2.08hrs) was to change out the breaker in PLC. Due to lowered velocity (down to 17.5fts) on the longer line and to increase production site management has decided to switch to a 95in impeller on 1026.

BriefComments: Major delay Impeller switch to 95 Dredge cont digging southbound. BOC@27 w.8ft steps
ExtendedComments: The Alaska went down to switch to a 95 impeller causing a delay of 10.5 hours. Impeller changed due to dropping velocity (~17.5fts) on 10500ft of line and stretching to 17000ft. After the impeller was changed production increased from ~5500CYWH to ~6800CYWH and velocity increased to ~21fts. Dredge is digging w BOC@27.0' and taking 8' steps in each corner. Morning and afternoon CND surveys were run to verify leave depth. Sample collected from ladder to send to Oakbrook for sieve analysis.

BriefComments: Production improved ~6600CYWH w 95 impeller. BOC@28' w 8'step
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging outbound traveling up Sta 604+60. Velocity has been holding at 21fts since 95 impeller installed. Production has increased from ~5500CYWH to ~6600CYWH since impeller change. No major delays. 2 separate delays for cleaning debris (tires and wire) from pump. BOC lowered to 28.0ft after morning CND surveys. Jack Newman dragged in front of the dredge to release trapped gas. High winds caused dredge to over dig along the on red toe.

BriefComments: Major Delay (3.58hrs) to add 1800ft of subline. BOC@28.0ft w 8ft steps.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging outbound while pumping on Bird Island. The Jack Newman continues to drag ahead of the dredge. Gas is still being encountered along the toes. The major delay was 3.58hrs for adding 1800ft of subline into the line. Velocity dropped from 21fts to 19fts and production dropped from 6500CYWH to 6100CYWH after the addtitional line was inserted. The dredge BOC is @28.0ft with 8ft steps. AM and PM cnd surveys show that we are clearing the template.

BriefComments: Cont digging to Sta 616+57. Material consistency remains the same. Dredge took on fuel.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging southbound. Dredge took on 88860 gallons of fuel in the afternoon. Velocity picked-up from 19 to 20fts yesterday due to increasing pump RPMs from 325 to 340. BOC@28.0 w 8ft steps. Morning and afternoon CND surveys show that the dredge is clearing the template. Main pump cleaned (7x) causing a delay of 2.76hrs.

BriefComments: Gas limited swing speed in evening (~34ftmin). BOC@28.0ft w8ft steps
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued working southbound. Misc delay of (0.50hrs) for problem with the PLC computer. CND surveys show dredge is clearing template. Miss Melinda dragged ahead of the dredge to release trapped gas. Even with dragging dredge is encountering alot of gas in the channel limiting swing speed (~34ftmin). Production dropped from ~6500CYWH to ~6000CYWH in the afternoon due to the gas causing the pump to ram off. Dig pattern remained the same w BOC@28.0ft taking 8ft steps.

BriefComments: Gas limiting swing speed (~35fts). BOC@28.0ft w8ft steps.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging southbound up to Sta 629+75. The Jack Newman dragged ahead of the dredge to release trapped gas but the swing speed was still limited. Gas is causing cavitation causing the pump to ram off. No major delays. BOC@28.0ft w8ft steps. Velocity continues to hold @20fts.

BriefComments: Pulled back to 628+00 for cleanup. 1800' of pontoon line added. BOC@28.5 w 8ft steps
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska had to pull back and clean from Sta 628+00 to Sta 632+70. From 628+00 to 630+00 dredge only cleaned green side from 630+00 to 632+70 dredge cleaned entire channel. Total of 7.75hrs of time lost due to cleanup. BOC dropped to 28.5' after cleanup. Liner in rock box on UWP pulled up and had to be cut out. 1800ft of pontoon line added. Velocity dropped from (~20.3fts) to (~19.3fts) after addition using 342 pump RPMs. Drop in velocity caused decrease in production of ~500CYWH.

BriefComments: Cont digging southbound. No major delays. BOC@28.5' w 8' steps
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska dug south to Sta 640+95. Leverman are running the main pump wide open (~342RPMs) maintaining ~19fts velocity. Dredge is continuing to encounter gas in the channel. Morning and afternoon surveys showed template cleared. At the current rate of travelday project completion should be on Tuesday 116.

BriefComments: Cont digging southbound pumping on Bird island No major delays. BOC@28.5' w 8'
ExtendedComments: The dredge dug south to Sta 647+72 BOC@28.5' w8' sets.Afternoon condtionals showed a collapse on the toes especially the green toe. Because of this on every other set Leverman are now making a full swing then going back to Range 180 -180 and back to the toes.Thismornings conditionals show this method has solved the problem.

BriefComments: Total RH=25hr. WH=16.77. Major Delay for rubber blow out. 1600ft pontoon pipe added.
ExtendedComments: Clocks fell back an hour so total 25RevHrs and WH 16.77. At 2100hrs short rubber between dredge and GL142 (spud) barge blew out for (3hr delay). 1600ft of pontoon line added in the early afternoon making final line length 15740ft.After every other swing dredge is swinging back to +-180 and swinging into the toes. Dredge continues to hit gas in throughout the channel. Dredge crew completed man overboard fire and abandon ship drills.

BriefComments: Major Delay to replace rubber hose.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska was down for 12.75hrs to replace the rubber hose between the dredge and GL142. The hose was replaced with one from the Dredge California. The main pump had to be cleaned 7x throughout the afternoon. Travel was limited due to the number of WHrs. Dredge continues to hit gas in the channel. Due to the delays expected project completion has been pushed back to approx Wednesday afternoon.

BriefComments: Cont digging south pumping on BI. Bolt on MP blew out (1.83hrs). BOC@28.5' w 8'
ExtendedComments: Dr went down from 0:00 to 2:00 due to bolt blowing out on MP Shell. Dredge continues to hit gas in the channel. Swinging 220' Green side and 215' Red side. Setting ahead in both corners. After a full swing in order to insure toe clearance every other step operator is swinging back to range +-180 and swinging back to the toe. Project completion is approximately tomorrow @1400.

BriefComments: Dredge Alaska Finished Digging on the Atachafalya River
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska Finished Digging on the Atachafalya River Bar Channel at 12:50.

BriefComments: Started digging at 1635 with the BOS at 33' in cut C1
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska digging in SOBA first pass with BOS @ 33' second pass @ 42'. Dye test gyro check gps check and ladder calibrations performed before starting up. Dredge is digging out the 2 passes before moving anchors. Spent a total of 0.75hrs digging down the first pass and 0.67hrs digging down the second pass. Dredge finished the first pass at 2320 and pulled back for the second pass. Surveys shows dredge taking ~9' of face on lift 1 leaving 27' and ~8' of face on lift 2 leaving 35'.

BriefComments: Better production today due to less time spent digging down. Great TE
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska digging in SOBA first pass with BOS @ 33' second pass @ 42'. Spent 0.67hrs digging down the 2nd lift. Dredge completed the 2nd lift at 1320 and picked up to dig 1st lift (Sta-1651-1958). Longer move anchors in the afternoon due to anchor barge having trouble lifting anchors (~0.33hrs longer). Cutter Amps high on the bottom lift & UWP ramming off some on the top lift.

BriefComments: Reduced production due to rough seas causing cutter amps to surge
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska digging in SOBA first pass with BOS @ 33' second pass @ 42'. Dredge finished cut C1 by the end of the night and was moving to C2 as midnight passed. Added extra cut facing south because of bad weather for a few days. Higher swells reducing production due to cutter amps surging. Pipeline repair to fix leaking stern flange. Survey delay to calibrate gyro using rtk rover.

BriefComments: Low prod due to large rolling swells reducing production to ~1600cywh until 0950
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska digging in SOBA cut C2 first pass with BOS @ 31'. Added extra cut facing south because of bad weather for a few days. Higher swells reducing production due to cutter amps surging. From 0000-0950 production was ~1600cywh due ot cutter amps being high from the rolling swells. Pipeline delay was 4.92hrs welding crack between stern pipe and flange 2.67hrs fixing leaks around the flange bolts. Wire repair for broken stbd swing and breast wire.

BriefComments: Moved to cut A1 and replaced stbd breast wire. Digging A1 using 2 lifts
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska digging in SOBA cut C2&A1. Digging 3 lifts in cut C2 BOS @ 31' 37' 42' in cut A1 we went back to digging two lifts with BOS @ 33' and 42' due to production being below estimate using 3 lifts. Digging cut A1 due to good weather out look. 4.58hrs Wire delays to fix stbd breast wire and then a 3.67hrs to replace it after moving to cut A1. 2.58hrs moving to cut A1

BriefComments: High TE leading to a strong production day. Digging 2 lifts cut A1
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska digging in SOBA cut A1 we are back to digging two lifts with BOS @ 33' and 42' due to production being below estimate using 3 lifts. Digging cut A1 due to good weather out look. Long shift anchor delay due to stbd swing buoy sinking. Mechanical delays to adjiust breast friction 0.33hrs and repair stern hauling gear 0.83hrs. Dump delay to slow down to switch valves. Dredge continues to leave ~34' behind us.

BriefComments: High TE leading to a strong production day.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska digging in SOBA cut A1 we are back to digging two lifts with BOS @ 33' and 42'. Digging cut A1 due to good weather out look. 1.42hrs Dump delay to slow down to switch valves 1.33hrs fixing 2 leaks.

BriefComments: Delays for washing out (Fill Site) switching valves (Fill Site)
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska digging in SOBA Cut A1 continuing to dig two lifts with BOS @ 33' and 42'. Digging cut A1 due to good weather out look.Material Composition based on visual inspection; leaving between 35' and 36.5' after 2nd pass.0.46 hours for fixing a leaking shorepipe on the Fill Site.

BriefComments: High %TE leading to Good Production Day
ExtendedComments: Continued digging in cut A1 with BOS at 32' and 42'.Delays included 0.92 hours for switching valves on the fill site (5x); 0.83 hours for setting dredge back for second lift (2x); and 1.57 hour delay to weld a broken stern flange.23:05 to 23:35: Washing line due to low velocity and high density.Once the end of Cut A1 is reach will reset to STA 426+00 and begin digging with BOS at 45'.Material Composition based on visual inspection.

BriefComments: Dredge returned to work at 1655 after completing repairs to West internal cross dike
ExtendedComments: Digging three lifts in cut A1; BOS at 32' for lift 1 and 42' for lift 2 45' for lift 3.Material composition based on visual inspection from behind cutter.More difficult to dig material in Lift 1 (higher cutter amps) than lift 2. Survey delay resetting PLC not showing production charts or ladder depth.

BriefComments: Long move delay due to stern anchor getting stuck and changing a buoy due to a crack
ExtendedComments: Digging three lifts in cut A1; BOS at 32' for lift 1 and 42' for lift 2 45' for lift 3.Material composition based on visual inspection from behind cutter. Dredge moved to cut A3 to save material in A2 for repairs to primary containment dike. Long move delay due to stern anchor being stuck due to not moving for 5 days during containment dike delay and stbd swing buoy needing to be replaced due to a crack found in it. Eletrical delays to reset MG set. Changed port swing wire.

BriefComments: Primary delay due to broken breast wire (5.08hrs).
ExtendedComments: Digging three lifts in Cut A3. Bottom of suction for each lift are as follows: 32' (1st) 42' (2nd) and 45' (3rd).Material composition based on visual inspection from behind cutter. The primary delay was casued by a broken breast wire and making the necessary repair (5.08hrs); rotation of valves and dealing with a sticky Y-valve on the dump was secondary (1.32hrs).

BriefComments: Good TE leading to a strong production day. Digging in plenty of face in A3
ExtendedComments: Digging three lifts in Cut A3. Bottom of suction for each lift are as follows: 32' (1st) 42' (2nd) and 45' (3rd).Material composition based on visual inspection from behind cutter. Less face on third lift continuing to make it our least productive. Looking at seas and surveys and will consider lowering ladder additional foot. Primary delays for repairs to clean out on MP(1.5hrs) and welding on the stern flange(1.25hrs). Ladder pump repair to fix air line on hoffer valve

BriefComments: Elevated TE% as per increased production. 3rd lift at 46' from previous 45'.
ExtendedComments: Digging three lifts in Cut A3. Bottom of suction for each lift are as follows: 32' (1st) 40' (2nd) and 46' (3rd).Material composition based on visual inspection from behind cutter. Additional foot of face improving production on third lift. Still needing to swing ~20fpm faster but maintaining density better. No major delays today with shifting anchors causing the most delays.

BriefComments: MP delay to weld on clean out box. Digging in A3 taking 3 lifts
ExtendedComments: Digging three lifts in Cut A3. Bottom of suction for each lift are as follows: 32' (1st) 40' (2nd) and 46' (3rd).Material composition based on visual inspection from behind cutter. The extra foot on the final lift allowing it to be as productive as previous 2 although still requiring faster swing speed. Main pump delay to weld on clean out box

BriefComments: Digging in A3 Minimal delays resulted in high TE%. 1hr delay for ME computer
Cut A3 completed.Delays between PLC & dump significant - Cut A4 begun at 2400hrs
ExtendedComments: When digging production was favorable as the sea conditions were great in the Gulf. Reduction in TE% due to increased delay periods. Dredge Alaska finished Cut A3 by digging a small portion of lift 2 (32') and lift 3 (46') from BOS. Dig plan continues to be 3 lifts digging from BOS at 32 40 and 46' but as always is subject to change as current surveystripchart data is obtained.

BriefComments: Three lifts taken in Cut A4 before shutting down to drain marsh containment area
ExtendedComments: Alaska continues to dig from BOS taking lifts at 30 42 and 46'.

BriefComments: Alaska Digging in Cut A4. Down for 4.92hrs waiting for marsh containment area to drain
ExtendedComments: Still digging from BOS at lifts 30 and 42ft an adjustment has been made to the third lift which is now at 45.5ft from 46ft.While dump experienced a minor leak draining containment area was the primary delay. In down time crew greased ladder. Other activities pertain to that of welding: repairing andor replacing walkways and fabricating roller systems in preparation for removing discharge pipe as well as assist with the ease to which it is removed. Worsening sea conditions within next 48-76 hrs expected.

BriefComments: Alaska digging in Cut A4 min.delays-primary fill-site @3.42 for leak&pipe layout
ExtendedComments: At this point the AK has completed approximately 50% of Cut A4 despite the delays that have been encountered (i.e. replacing MP liner dealing w main PLC failure(s) and periods in which the fill-site required to drain containment area). Overthe past 24hrs the AK has encountered denser material andor methane pockets win cut as notable shaking has occured in areas - Cpt. Scott Gilikin supports above notions. AKdigs from BOS taking lifts of 32 40 and 45.5 and averages

BriefComments: AK moved to Cut A1 mid-day as weather approached. Third pass being made with BOS @ 45.5ft.
ExtendedComments: Leaving Cut A4 having only taken two lifts from BOS(32&40ft) AK intentions are to take a third lift in Cut A1 (45.5) to allow for the use of both surge tanks

BriefComments: Dredge moved to A1 to fill cells 1&2. Digging final pass at 46'
ExtendedComments: Dredge digging only in cut A1 after ring dike in need of additional repairs. Fill crew rearranged pipe configuration to pump into cells 1&2. Digging at 46'. Fill Site Delays 8.58hrs down patching ring dike 4.67hrs moving to cut A1 to pump cells 1 and 2 1.42hrs patching leaks on fill 0.08hrs switching valves.

BriefComments: Alaska digging final lift from A1. Long delays draining water from cells 1&2
ExtendedComments: Alaska digging final lift in A1 with BOS at 46' filling cells 1&2. Fill site delays:12.5hrs for water to drain from cells 1 &2 from 0215-1445 0.08hrs switching valves 0.58hrs for shoreline leak 3.67hrs for water to drain from cells 1 &2 from 2020-2400. Filling cells 1&2 as repairs continue to ring dike

BriefComments: Dredge moved to cut A2 and pumped on ring dike for 1.5hrs
ExtendedComments: Dredge digging final pass in cut A1 with BOS at 46' finished cut A1 at 0715 and moved to cut A2 to pump on the ring dike. Dredge digging only 1st pass in A2 saving the 2nd and 3rd passes for the ring dike. Pumped on the ring dike for 1.5hrs before needing to pump into cell 4.

BriefComments: Dredge down 7.5hrs for large ground swells. Swells cauing cutter amps to spike
ExtendedComments: Dredge digging in A2 with BOS at 32'40'46'.Dredge was pumping only the first pass in the morning and set back in at 0645 to dig 2nd and 3rd lift at the ring dike. Weather then came through delaying start up until 1600. The dredge pumped at the ring dike for 1.42hrs before spending the rest of the day pumping into cell 4.

BriefComments: MP rpm reduced to 310 due to vibration and high thrust bearing temp
ExtendedComments: Dredge digging in Cut A2 with BOS @ 32'40'46' pumping into cell 4. At 0800 reduced MP rpm by ~30rpm due to vibrations being felt and increased thrust shoetempurature. At 310rpm no vibrations felt and shoe tempurature normal. Fill site delay for piping up and change cut for pulling back for additional passes

BriefComments: Dredge down for cam rollers at 1335. Moved to SJ 081
ExtendedComments: Dredge digging in Cut A2 with BOS @ 32'40'46' pumping into cell 4. MP turned down ~30rpm due to vibrations being felt and increased thrust shoe tempurature. At 310rpm no vibrations felt and shoe tempurature normal. Fill site delay for piping up and moving y-valve. Down due to cam rollers having manufacturing defect where metal casing peels off the rollers. Number 10 on the port engine is the cam that failed and 2 and 4 on the starboard side are showing signs of the same problem

BriefComments: Cam rollers fixed @ 1230 and dredging resumed in A2@1250. Delay reported SJ081
ExtendedComments: Dredge digging in Cut A2 from BOS taking lifts at 3240ft. Material is still being pumped into cell 4. Repairs were made to cam rollers on port side. While down deteriorated walkways on ladder were replaced and new steal for stern anchoring system installed.

BriefComments: Started digging at 12:10PM in SOBA Cut A2 w BOS @ 32 and 40
ExtendedComments: Alaska digging both passes before moving forward on anchors. 3.5HR Delay for fill site fixing leaks at the Wye Valves. Alternating pumping between Cells 3 and 4 slowing down when fill site switches valves over. 0.42HR Delays for fill site stopping minor leaks and switching valves. Velocity between ~14 and 14.5FPS; material composition based on visual inspection of previous sand samples.

BriefComments: Frequent delays for the material settling and fixing leaks on fill site
ExtendedComments: Digging in Cut A2 w BOS @ 32' and 40'; moving anchors forward after digging both passes. Delays for fill site: changing valves (3x 0.33Min) fixing leaks (3x 0.50Min) and waiting on the fill site (1.83Hrs). Also had a leak in gasket on the air valves by the riser (2.00 Hrs) changed cutter motor gear box (1.5Hrs). Leaving ~34 - 35' of material.

BriefComments: AK digging Lift 1 @ 33' & Lift 2 @ 42' then moving anchors ahead. Dump delays total10.17h
ExtendedComments: AK digging at 32' up to station 406+50 dredge was moved back within Cut 2A and began Lift 2 at 40' from station 409+00. Fill site caused 10.17 hours for delays (0.25 hrs pipe leak and 9.92 hrs for pipe workwaiting on water level to drop). Ladder depth dropped to 42' after the long fill site delay (16:50 start back up). Cutter was cleaned once (rope and cable debris) for 0.33 hrs. A new eye was rolled in the port swing wire after it was cut at night (1.92 hrs). ~18' dig face removed between the two lifts.

BriefComments: Low TE:water draining at fill site (6.33 hrs) & blown piece of float line (6.08 hrs)
ExtendedComments: Fill Site delays included: 8.08 hrs for water levels 0.17 hrs shore pipe leak 0.17 hrs total for slowing dredge for valve changes x2. The failed piece of float line blew apart in the middle of the piece. The shredded pieces were unbolted and the line rebolted back together without a replacement piece available (6.08 hrs). The Captain speculates the cause due to internal wear. Vel @ 14 fps swing speed @ 50 ftmin setting 4-6 ft.

BriefComments: Broken breast wire (7.58 hrs) Broken swing wire (4.17 hrs)
ExtendedComments: AK continued digging in Cut 1A until 21:15. At this time AK shifted back and began digging Cut2A (red toe). TE suffered due to breaking PORT breast wire in the early am then breaking the STBD swing wire (swing friction not releasing - ram replaced) in the afternoon. Texas Jr facing load sharing problems beginning at 17:00 and continuing throughout the night. Dozer 674 left site due to repairs to tracks. Bedding in line with booster at lower RPMS (225).

BriefComments: Booster load sharing issues fixed (faulty sensor and water in fuel)
ExtendedComments: To prevent bedding while booster was operating at low RPMs a 1.3 density was targeted. This density target proved difficult to maintain because any slight changes in dig pattern would load up the line very quickly with this heavy material. MiscOther delays for washing the line out during bedding situations. Texas Jr held 225 RPM until load sharing issues were resolved. Relatively good TE and digging in higher face then previous days resulted in good production day.

BriefComments: Low TE bc weather & broken wire. Dredge cleanup then change cuts to 2B wface~3.5'
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK was down from 0:00-11:00 due to rough seas. Upon startup dredge dug spotty cleanup material in Cut 1A w avg face ~1.6'. At 12:30 dredge moved to Cut 2B (1.75 hours to change cut) to resume digging outbound in ~ 3.5' face avg cut width 200'. BOS held @ 53.5' throughout the day. Swing speed ~50 fpm taking 4-6' sets gave digWH close to estimate with 1180 CYWH. TE fell when STBD breast wire broke (4th broken wire to date) causing delay from 20:00 thru the remainder of the day.

BriefComments: Good coverage- 250' wide cut w approx. 3.7' face. Channel current limits swing width
ExtendedComments: Dr. Alaska experienced good coverage but low TE. Navy submarine caused 12.42 hrs of delay for channel traffic (scheduled to pass at 0830- did not pass until 1500). Dredge dug outbound swinging 250' wide taking 4-6' sets into ~3.7' of face. Dredge was still unable to complete the full cut with each swing as the current between tide shifts puts a heavy load on the dredge (too many wires have broken to date bc of this). Mat'l is less coarse with less shell and more fine sands allowing high vel ~24 fps

BriefComments: Good TE w 2 dredge moves. Avg cut width 215' low face ~3'
ExtendedComments: Dredge swung 250' wide outbound the red side of the channel digging 3' face before she pulled back 900' to dig low face in the North Settling Basin. BOS was raised to 50' in this cut as grade is 46'+1'. Avg. Swing speed 50 fpm give hourly coverage of 12059 sfWH. Once completed with the NSB Cut dredge pulled back 500' to dredge green side of channel in a narrow cut approx. 160'. wide w BOS dropped back to 53.5'. Leverman taking 4-5' sets consistently throughout entire day. Shift Anchors 14x

BriefComments: Low TE- installed 2500' subline. Move dredge into narrow cut low face
ExtendedComments: At 1:40 AM the dredge ran out of slack in the line in order to continue cut moving forward. Crew waited until slack tide during daylight hours (heavy current) to install 2500' of subline in order to complete remainder of the cut (14 hrs delay). Unexpected rocky material was experienced briefly when BOS was then raised to 51.5' to lower the load in the line. Avg swing speed 50 fpm gave hrly coverage 10300 sfWH not as good as previous days due to narrow cut of 140' width. Dig face remains 2-3' with BOS @ 53.5'

BriefComments: Good TE- Dredge swung 250' outbound red side of channel in 3.4' of face
ExtendedComments: Good weather permitted a consistent day of digging. Travel 837' with 11 anchor moves. Hourly coverage near 10000 SFWH. Crew shut down for 2.17 hours for routine maintenance on cutter gearbox and cutter head along with greasing the ladder. Dredge washed out 3x as velocity dropped below 20 fps although material was found to consistently be medium sand.

BriefComments: Dredge taveled 310' until weather delayed work from 11:45- 23:59
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging the red side of the channel swinging 250' wide into average face of 3-3.5'. Material consisted of medium grain sand but survey crew on beach reported a few pockets of clay. At 11:45 the dredge washed the line out to prepare to move out of the channel as the seas became very rough later in the day. Rental tug got trapped on top of the float hose so crew had to break the rubber line off to patch up a tear on the outside of the hose. Dredge remained down for the rest of the day.

BriefComments: Good TE. Heavier mat'l- washout line 4x (2 hours). Swing 250' wide w ~3.2' face
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK resumed digging outbound the red side of the channel in Cut 2D. She maintained a swing width of 250' walking towards the centerline of the channel. Digging to a 49.5' contour (Grade= 49' + 2') BOS @ 53.5' was raised to 53.0' when dredge experienced heavier material which reduced velocity below 20 fps. AK washed out the line 4x which explains the 2.00 hours of delay under Other. Shifted anchors 10x for travel of 690'. Swing speed of 44 fpm gave hourly coverage of 9550 sfWH

BriefComments: Dredge AK completed final cut at 9:52 AM. Good TE w heavy mat'l in Cut 2D.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska made good TE to finish the project in Cut 2D. She continued to swing 250' wide into approx 3.5' face of heavy sand material. Major delays were for washing out the line 3x (counted as Other in delay breakdown). BOS was raised from 53.5' to 53.0' to reduce the load in the line and to maintain a velocity above 20 fps when digging. Leverman reported more problems with the Hoffer Valve Hose (.5 hours delay). Once the final cut was complete at 9:52 AM the dredge towed to Kings Bay inlet.

BriefComments: Low face is causing us to be under estimate
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK digging in Cut 01 with BOS @ 18' taking 4'-5' steps. Low uneven face causing poor production on port side.Trouble with lifter in main generator caused 4.17 hr delay.Positioning computer went down @ 23:40 for 0.33 hrs.

BriefComments: Weather caused primary delay
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK digging in Cut 01 with BOS @ 18' taking 4'-5' steps.Weather prevented dredging from 12:30 on.Hard object hit on STA 2610 @ Range 620. Delays include: Clean Cutter (1.0 hr.) Move Stb breast and swing anchors 1x (.25 hr) Move Port breast and swing 2x (0.5) Move stern anchor 1x (0.17).

BriefComments: cut 01 with BOS @ 19.5'
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK digging in Cut 01 with BOS @ 19.5' taking 4'-5' steps with 6'-7' of face and SS of 55 fps.Primary delay from 00:00 to 16:30 due to weather.

BriefComments: cut 01 with BOS @ 19.5'
ExtendedComments: Digging in cut 01 with BOS @ 19.5 with 8'-9' of face taking 4'-5' steps with Swing Speed of 55 fps.Dredge shut dow from 05:30 to 12:00 due to IIF Launch Meeting.

BriefComments: Digging in cut 01 with BOS @ 20'
ExtendedComments: Digging in cut 01 with BOS @ 20' with 8' of face taking 4'-5' steps.Face increasing as stations decrease.Moved swing anchors 6x.Moved breast anchors 6x. Swing speeds have been increased to 70-90 fpm and production has increased.

BriefComments: Digging in cut 01 with BOS @ 20' with 8' of face taking 4'-5' steps
ExtendedComments: Digging in cut 01 with BOS @ 20' with 8' of face taking 4'-5' steps. Moved BOS to 20.5' @ STA 10+60.Double Swinging at swing speeds from 70-90 fps. Moved Swing anchors 2x (0.34 hr).Moved Breast anchors 2x (0.34 hr). Moved Stern anchor 1x (0.25 hr).

BriefComments: Widened range on STB side
ExtendedComments: digging in cut 01 with BOS lowered to 20.5' having 10'-12' of face.Swing Speed 63 fps.Widened range to 565' on STB side @ STA 08+67.Moved Swing anchors 4x.Moved Breast anchors 4x.Moved Stern anchor 1x.Beginning to pick up trash.

BriefComments: Trash around bridge causing majority of delays
ExtendedComments: Nearing the end of cut 01 with BOS @ 20.5' with SS @ 65 fps.Raised BOS to 19' at STA 04+36 and began to narrow cut.Raise BOS to 18' at STA 03+47. Moved Swing Anchors 2x Breast Anchors 2x Stern Anchor 1x.Several delays due to trash around bridge.Trash in air valve @ 03:30.Rock in main pump @ 16:55.Tires in cutter @ 09:15 and 17:20.

BriefComments: Digging Under Bridge (Several inboundoutbound shifts due to pilings)
ExtendedComments: Digging in cut 01. Raised BOS to 15' @ STA 350.Raised BOS to 14' @ STA 300.Moved to cut 02.Began digging @ STA 12+48 moving inbound.Broken swing wire from 19:30 to 24:00.

BriefComments: Rough seas shifting anchors. Swing 2x into 11' face 200' wide in Cut 2 w heavy current
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging inbound Cut 2 from GLDD station 11+79 to 8+88. Shallow water and rough seas in the AM delayed the dredge for shifting anchors forward (4.75 hours- weather). The miscother delay was from a gasket blowout on the rubberline. Dredge is double-swinging 200' wide into heavy current in order to clear 11-12' of face. Slight production drop from over-swinging into Cut 1 to ensure no shoals are left in between cuts. Leverman is taking 4-5' sets in order to clear grade.

BriefComments: Cut 2- 200' wide double-swing into 11.5' face. Slight daylighting in port corner
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued digging inbound Cut 2 swinging ~200' wide. Levermen were alternating single and double swings taking 4-5' sets in each corner. A third cleanup swing was necessary at times when levermen would see density remaining over 1.3 after second swing. BOS held at 20.5' gave an average leave-depth of 16.8'. Cutter is encountering a lot of trash near the bridge- dredge shut down 4x to clean the main pump. Shift anchors 8x to give 3.25 hours of delay. All teeth on cutter remain good.

BriefComments: AK dug into Cut 23 widener double-swinging 250'+ into 11' of bank for good production
ExtendedComments: Dredge made good coverage yesterday with rough seas traveling 622' with 12 anchor moves (4.68 hours shift anchors as primary delay). Cut was wider than before as dredge is digging a channel widener overswinging toe of channel 10' to clear all slopes. High bank of medium sand mat'l with avg 11' face allowed good production.

BriefComments: Low TE due to weather good production in Cut 3 w high bank at toe of channel.
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK remained down due to weather rough seas until she started back up at 8:10 AM. She finished Cut 2 @ 12:50 then pulled back to dig inbound Cut 3 at the channel toe widener. Good production in Cut 3 w dredge swinging 190' wide into high bank of material on her STBD corner.
