Levermen holding cutter at 20.5' in high bank corner to let mat'l run in and consistently double-swung each set clearing grade with 1 pass. Cutter is still picking up several tires causing delay 2x to clean cuttersuction.

BriefComments: Cut 3- High bank w med. sand mat'l. 200' wide double swing BOS @ 20.5' = Good production.
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK dug inbound Cut 3 double-swinging 200' wide with high bank of med. sand mat'l on her STBD corner. Levermen continue to hold BOS @ 20.5' while targeting a consistent density over 1.2. Taking 4-5' sets in each corner when necessary. Shift anchors 13x yeilds 6.58 hours delay. Wire came off stern anchor once causing 2.67 hour setback. 'Other' delay for washing out line and dump crew piping up and changing wye-valves. Lots of tires caught in cutter- 2 teeth were replaced. CYWH above estimate bc high face

BriefComments: Cut3-high face med. sand. 200' wide double swing BOS@20.5' pockets of shell
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK dug inbound Cut 3 double-swinging 150' wide with high bank of med. sand mat'l on her STBD corner. Encountered pockets of shellgravel also finding lots of debris. Levermen continue to hold BOS @ 20.5' while targeting density over 1.2. Taking 4-5' sets in each corner when necessary. CYWH above estimate due to productive face. Moved anchors (2x) for 1.33 hrs.Other delays for pulling back 0.25 hrs and cleaning suction mouth (0.25 hrs).

BriefComments: Complete east side of Cut2 2 small cleanup areas dredged encountering heavy debris
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK dug inbound Cut 3 and then cleaning up high spots out bound on Cut 2 double-swinging 150' wide with high bank of med. Levermen continues to dig BOS @17.5 on first cut and BOS @ 20.5 at final cut while targeting density over 1.2. Taking 4-5' sets in each corner when necessary.Moved anchors (4x) for 1.73 hrs.Other delays for pulling back 0.16 hrs and cleaning suction mouth (0.66 hrs).

BriefComments: Complete bridge side of CUT 2 2 Dredge digging last cut encountering heavy debris
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK dug out bound on CUT 2 double-swinging 150' wide with high bank of med. Levermen continues to dig BOS @17.5 on first cut and BOS @ 20.5 at final cut while targeting density over 1.2. Taking 4-5' sets in each corner when necessary. CYWH above estimate due to productive face. Moved anchors (4x) for 2.6 hrs.Other delays for fixing leak in float hose Flange 0.9 hrs hrs).

BriefComments: Digging CUT 2 single pass BOS @ 20.5' 7'-8' face targeting 1.2 density
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK dug outbound on CUT 2 digging single pass BOS @ 20.5 targeting density over 1.2. Taking 4-5' sets in each corner. Heavy seas prevent tugs from moving anchor. As dredge works outbound into less protected waters this is becoming more of an issue. Moved anchors (2x) for .2 hrs. Other delays for fixing leak in float hose (1.92 hrs) and replacing roller in starboard engine (1.75 hrs).

BriefComments: Digging outbound on Cut 2 single pass BOS@ 20.5 7'-8' face targeting 1.2 density
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK is digging outbound on Cut 2 digging single pass with BOS @ 20.5 with 7'-8' of face. Targeting a density of 1.2. The dredge Hit a hard object at station 27+75 damaging 9 of the cutter teeth. Digging outbound on Cut 2 leaves the dredge more exposed to rough seas and weather elements. Bad weather and rough seas stopped the dredge for 3.66 hrs. Moved anchors (1x) for .5 hrs. Other delays for fixing leak in float hose (1.58 hrs).

BriefComments: Digging outbound on Cut 2 single pass BOS@ 20.5 8'-9' face targeting 1.2 density
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK is digging outbound on Cut 2 digging single pass with BOS @ 20.5 with 8'-9' of face. Targeting a density of 1.2. The dredge is digging at approximately 1490 prodhr. Digging outbound on Cut 2 leaves the dredge more exposed to rough seas and weather elements. This has lowered the dredges production and has cost hours in delays in the past week.Moved anchors (4x) for 1.42 hrs. Mechanical pipeline delays for air valve on riser pipe leaking.

BriefComments: Cut 2 BOS@ 19.0 7'-8' face. AS 2 and 3 BOS @ 19.5 3'-4' face targeting 1.2 density
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK finished digging out bound on Cut 2 with on a single pass with BOS @ 20.5 and 7'-8' of face. Dredge then moved inbound to finish clean up cut on AS 2. AS 2 was dug on a single pass with BOS @ 19.5 and 3'-4' of face. The dredge then moved into AS 2 with same cut pattern as AS 3. The production is low due to low face in AS 2 -3 as well as obstacles such as bridge pilings in the cuts forcing the dredge to make short passes. Delays include moving anchors (2x) for .75 hrs.

BriefComments: Cleanup Dig Cut1- AS2. Re-dredge low face single cleanup swing low CYWH
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK moved over to AS2 to cleanup a spot in Cut 1. Production was lower than estimate due to the cleanup sweep with low face. (Note- AS2 had already been accepted cleanup sweep was for additional pay that had accumulated). At 0840 dredge completed cut then washed out line pulled out of way for USACE to AD survey. The dredge did not de-mob for the remaining 15.33 hours of the day as an emergency job was requested in the inlet. Dredge AK now standby to re-mobilize short project in Oregon Inlet.

BriefComments: Dredge AK began work at 0715 then shut down for NCDOT surveys & mat'l settlement
ExtendedComments: Dredge operations in subjob 040 began at 0715 AM. Dredge dug for a total of 6.92 work hours during the day however all work hours are charged on rental rate. After pumping ~15000 CYs the dredge then shut down to let material settle and allow surveyors on site to obtain data of the disposal area at Bonner Bridge.

BriefComments: AK completed dredge ops. @ 2205 after 30000 CYs where she then began demob on job
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging the Bonner Bridge Emergency project throughout the majority of the day. She completed digging the contracted 30000 CYs for the disposal area at 10:05 PM. At this time the dredge then began demob on site for the emergency project for the remainder of the day.

BriefComments: Dredge AK using a single lift BOS @ 23.0 moving to a 2nd lift14.5 then dropping BOS @ 2
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK started up at 08:30 on Monday morning. Digging inbound on Cut 1 digging a single lift @ 23.0' and moving to a double lift with BOS @ 15 and 24.0'. Material is very fine and siltly making the dredge dig deeper that planned on account of the material falling back into to the Cut. Delays include moving anchors (2x) for 1.16 hrs. Other delays include .25 hrs. to Tightedn Stbd. swing friction. Also .25 hrs. to pull back dredge on Cut 1.

BriefComments: Dredge AK dug inside jetty in Cut 1 with BOS@ 20.6 then dug in Cut 2 with BOS@ 20.5
ExtendedComments: The Dredge AK finishe Cut 1 inside of the rock jettys. they were short low face swings and this lowered production for day. They then moved back out and set anchors in Cut 3. The dredge then dug inbound in Cut 3 with the BOS@ 20.6 and high face. The dredge pulled back four times on this cut for 2nd lifts. Dredge moved anchors (1x) for .42 hrs. Other delays include .33 hrs. for a leak in the gear box and .25to stop working. and . 30 hrs. to pull back on Cut 3.

BriefComments: Dredge AK dug inbound in Cut 2 w 2-passes. 1st pass @ 23' 2nd pass @ 15' to grade
ExtendedComments: The Dredge AK dug inbound in Cut 2 making 2 passes in order to clear grade at 2 different depths. The first pass the dredge held BOS @ ~23' then pulled back to dig an angled channel section w BOS @ 15'. The angled section had a different channel depth design which is why BOS changed. Multiple delays this day to pull back and change cut. Dredge moved anchors (2x) for 1.19 hrs. Other delays include .25hrs. to change strainer in the gear box and .25 hrs. to pull back on Cut 2.

BriefComments: Dredge AK dug inbound Cut 2 Cleanup Cut 1 then completed last cut at 13:45
ExtendedComments: AK began the day digging inbound Cut 2 for its 1st pass. BOS was held at 15.0' in order to clear grade at the shallow channel depths near the jetty. The dredge then pulled back and made her 2nd pass in a narrower Cut 2 with BOS held at 23' in order to clear grade to a lower depth. Upon completion of Cut 2 the dredge then made a cleanup pass inbound Cut 1 along with another small spot left behind in Cut 2 when she finally completed all dredge operations at 13:45. Primary delays were for changing cutspull back

BriefComments: Cut 1A BA-B. Low face- BOS raised due to bad mat'l. Low TE- STBD winch repairs
ExtendedComments: Dr. AK dug in BA-B Cut 1A Swinging 250' wide at 54 fpm. She experienced bad material digging siltclay so BOS was raised 1' (Digging 9-10' deep instead of 11' deep) in search of better material. Low TE for the day due to repairs on the STBD winch drum (7.92 hrs) and hydraulic positioning computer kept freezing upcutting off gauges (1.41 hrs). Hourly coverage and travel near estimate at 9353 SFWH. Fill site and dredge consistently monitor the change in mat'l. Ladder calibration was performed by engineers.

BriefComments: Low TE: Wx 4-6' Seas. BOS @ 7'-8' depths w approx 4~5' face. Good coverage & travel.
ExtendedComments: AK continued digging in BA-B Cut 1A Swinging 250' wide at swing speed 58 fpm. Bad material (clay) was encountered in the cut so dredge raised BOS 3x in order to get better mat'l. BOS mostly dug at ~7'-8' depths yet managed to still get 4-5' face for avg production near estimate. Rough seas delayed the dredge from 11:40 thru the remainder of the day w 4-6' sea swell. Hourly coverage better than current estimate at 11273 SFWH. Swing amps high bc of rough seas & velocity was low w long line & heavy mat'l.

BriefComments: Dredge was down most of the day (17.89hr) due to main generatorelectrical problems.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska continued digging in borrow area B cut 1A. Swinging 250' wide cuts at 54 fpm taking 4-5' sets. The fill site encountered unsuitable material at 05:35 so we raised the BOS to 44.0 at station 18+44 to. The material improved and the BOS was lowered at station 19+17 to 45.0. Generatorelectrical problems contributed to low TE. Average velocity was 14.6 with the main pump average rpm at 339.

BriefComments: The Dredge Alaska encountered low velocities which resulted in a low cywh for the day.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska encountered low velocities (average of 11.7 fpm) in borrow area b cut 1a (bos 41-44) which forced the leverman to take smaller sets (2-3') and slow the swing speed. This resulted in a low cywh for the day. The elbow on the beach was taken off to help raise velocity. While breaking the elbow out of the line the fill crew reported an abundance of shell in the line. Average velocity for the day was 11.7 with the main pump rpm at 340. Average main pump dishcharge pressure was 178.

BriefComments: The dredge dug in cut 1a in the morning and shifted to cut 2a by the afternoon.
ExtendedComments: The Alaska continued to encounter low velocities in ba b cut 1a in the morning the air valve and vosta connection was disconnected then inspected and shells in the line were cleaned out of each. At 10:00 the dredge began to move to cut 2a in bab (station 5+30) in search for better material. The fill site reported better material and the dredge velocity was higher than in the previous cut (1a) two 14 tires were also reported on the fill site. Average velocity was 13.9 (dis pres 211).

BriefComments: The dredge was down the majority of the day due to rough seas (15.00 hrs)
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska was down the majority of the day due to bad weatherrough seas. At 15:00 she started back up continuing to dig in borrow area b cut 2a at station 11+33. The fill site reported unsuitable material so the dredge picked the bos up to 41.0'. The dredge continues to take smaller sets and is digging less face to help keep the velocities high. The average velocity was 13.5 fps with a discharge pressure of 223.

BriefComments: The dredge continues to dig low face and small sets due to low velocities.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska's dig quantity was below the estimate in borrow area b cut 2a due to low TE and velocities forcing the leverman to raise the bos (42-41')and dig low face (2.85') take small setsdouble swing to keep the velocity as high as possible. 16 cutter teeth were changed and the fill site reported clay and shell on the beach. Average velocity for the day was 12.6 with a discharge pressure of 214. The kong pressure sensor was send through the line and sucessfully retrieved on the fill site.

BriefComments: Low TE-wash out line. Low Density 1.1 w small sets. Double swings BOS @ 42.5
ExtendedComments: The Dredge AK dug eastbound on Borrow area B cut 2A. Good materialmedium to fine sands. BOS @ 7 foot depth from existing. Misc Delays (8.24 hrs.) for low velocity and washing out line. (1.58 hrs.) for moving anchors. Small sets to reduce load in pipeline and to maintain velocity around 14-15 FPS. Small cut width with narrowing cut creates limited production. At STA 21+67 BOS dropped to 43.5 feet.

BriefComments: Low TE. Wash out line 4x to maintain velocity above 15fps. Target line density of 1.10
ExtendedComments: Dr. AK continued to dig in BA-B Cut 2A swinging 250' wide. Levermen made double swings in the cut and shortened the step size to from 5-7' to 4'. Dredge BOS was raised to 42.5' - 43' in hopes of maintaining velocity above 15.0 fps. Target a maximum density of 1.10 in order to reduce the load in the line. Total 24700' + pipeline length continues to limit dredge production. Main pump RPM is ~340 with a constant discharge pressure ~210 psi. Velocity and kong tests were performed and showed gauges were correct.

BriefComments: The Dredge Alaska recommenced digging in borrow area b cut 3a at 14:30.
ExtendedComments: After several unsuccessful attempts to install the Booster Reggie over the past week the submerged line was re connected and the plugs installed. Two pressure sensors where sent through the line with one successful retrieval. The Dredge Alaska recommenced digging at 14:30 in borrow area b cut 3a. The dredge started the cut with the bos at 45.0 the fill site reported clay on the beach so the ladder was picked up to 44.0' and then 43.5'. Major delays were moving anchors 5 times (1.32 hrs).

BriefComments: The Dredge Alaska started back digging at 09:10 in borrow area b cut 3a.
ExtendedComments: The rough weather delay continued onto 0216.By daylight the crew had towed out a replacement air valve assembly and was installed the dredge started back digging at 09:10 in Borrow Area B Cut 3A with the BOS at 43.5'.At station 11+48 the cut started to decrease in width resulting in the leverman not swinging a full 250' cut most of the day.

BriefComments: The Dredge Alaska had low TE due to the amount of delays (16.23 hrs total).
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska had low TE due to the amount of delays (16.23 total). Early in the day the dredge moved from cut 3a to 1a in borrow area b. While in the process of changing cuts the Tug Trident had problems with the drum on her stern winch which added to the delay. Once the problem was resolved the Alaska starting digging at 09:25 in cut 1a at station 25+10 with the bos at 44.0. Soon after the leverman picked the ladder up to 42.0' at station 25+45 due to low velocities. MP RPM 341 average pressure of 225.

BriefComments: Low production due to wash out delay(7.42 hrs). BOS @ 37.5 with 3.5 ft face.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Ak finished cut 1A with minimal face at 3.5 ft. BOS @ 37.5 with a single swing. It then pulled back to STA 2487 on Cut 2A were it continued to dig with BOS @ 37.7 and 3 ft. of face. Production is low due to extended down time and low velocity. Multiple delays due to low velocity and washing out of the line of ( 7.92 hrs.). Moved Anchors for (.59 hrs.)

BriefComments: AK made decent TE w good coverage. Change Cuts 3x. Low face w silt mat'l.
ExtendedComments: Levermen began the day digging with BOS @ 40.5'. They were instructed to raise the ladder up twice in search of better material as the fill site reported soft silt at the discharge. Dredge was able to maintain velocity ~15 fps with no delays to wash out the line. Dredge was able to pump mat'l with no problem maintaining velocity and density. Levermen taking 6-8' sets improving coverage but with average density ~1.2. Dredge changed cuts 3x before moving to borrow area B- Cut 3B.

BriefComments: Dredge AK on Cut 3B. Digging with asingle pass with low face(3 ft) BOS @ 40.5.
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK is almost out of slack in float hose. Weather is to bad to break subline and advance dredge will continue to dig on cuts were she can reach. Cut 3B is not great material mostly fine sand and silt. To keep porduction up the dredge is digging low face of 3 ft. and single swing and ~4' steps. The BOS @ 40.5 makes for low face but keeps production up without having to wash out the line.

BriefComments: Dredge AK dug Cut 3B. Pulled up Ladder 4x clayshell ending BOS @ 39 ft 3.5 ft of face
ExtendedComments: Dr AK dug into Cut 3B until it had no more line to advance. Dr dropped the ladder where BOS @ 44' but began to encounter clay so the BOS was raised accordingly. LM tried to maintain 1.2 density & a swing speed of 50 fps while taking 4' sets. The weather delay was caused by dense fog which prevented the crew to see if there was any slack in the float hose.

BriefComments: Maj. Delays: Faulty spud hoist(8.92) Take out 2000' of subline (6.83)
ExtendedComments: @ 0355 the float hose ran out of slack so the Dr began pumping water. Crew took out 2000 ft of subline which helped increase velocity from 13 fts to 15 fts. Dr began pumping material again at 1210. Dr dug at 42 ft but experienced clay so the leverman picked up the BOS to 40 ft in order to find better material. At 1505 Dr went down due to what appears to be spud hoist motor faults. Seas became too rough to install 2000' subline onto line #2. Avg SS 50fps 4-5' sets

BriefComments: Dr began priming up @ 1300 & digging @ 1335
ExtendedComments: Dr primed up @ 1300 & began digging @ 1335. The Dr finished Cut 3B at 1420 and was moved to Cut 4B (2.33 hr delay). In Cut 4B the leverman encountered clay with the bottom of suction at 45 ft so he gradually raised the BOS a few feet in an attempt to find better material. Eventually the leverman found suitable material later in the cut and was able to drop BOS back down to 44 ft. Velocity:14.3 fts Line Density:1.18 Dr MP is operating at max. RPM & is pump limited.

BriefComments: Misc. Delay: Wash out line for pig test(2.17hr) run pig test(0.67hr)
ExtendedComments: At 0720 the Dr began finished the cut and began washing out the line in order to perform a pig test (2.17hr delay). The pig was placed in the line at 0930 and was retrieved on the beach at 1010 (0.67 hr delay). After the test was completed the Dr was moved to Cut 5B. The Dr was down from 1010 to 1500 when the crew had to change a stranded stern wire (4.83hr delay). The Dr started pumping again at 1630 after being set in position (1.25hr delay). Vel: 14.4 fps Line Den: 1.16

BriefComments: Moved to Cut 6B soupy material @ end of 5B good material @ beginning of 6B
ExtendedComments: @ 1155 Dr finished Cut 5B moved to Cut 6B and was set in place at 1500. Dr remained down from 1500 to 1650 when the crew had to change cutter teeth & inspect the MP for wear. Towards the end of Cut 5B Dr encountered very soft silty material. Cus 6B ran along the No Dredge Zone so the crew was careful not to disturb this zone with the Dr or anchors. Vel: 13.5 fps Line Den: 1.16

BriefComments: Good TE good travel due to 140' wide cut Dr encountered silty material
ExtendedComments: The crew is also taking their time to not disturb the No Dredge Zone when setting anchors. The Dredge spend most of the day in a 140 ft wide cut and travelled 633 ft in the cut. Dredge experienced silty material as well as clay in some areas which caused the leverman to raise the BOS to avoid the clay. Leverman are focusing on maintaining a density of 1.20 and a velocity over 14 fts. Actual: Density-1.12 Velocity-13.5 fts

BriefComments: Good DigWH Dr encountered silty material weather delay@1545-2400
ExtendedComments: The Dredge beat the estimate for DigWH. Delays included moving cuts from 0000 until 0305 (3.08hrs) and from 0840 until 1015 (1.58hrs) moving y-valves on the beach (1.67hrs) and rough seas from 1545-2400 (8.25hrs). Dredge experienced silty material as well as clay in some areas which caused the leverman to raise the BOS from 44' at the beginning of the cuts to 41' near the end. Vel.-13.0 fts Line Den.-1.16

BriefComments: Decent TE rough seas in the morning found good mat. in cut move Dr @2205
ExtendedComments: Dr was down for weather from 0000-0130. MP & UWP maintenance (clean and fix oil leak) from 0550-0740. @ beginning of cut Dr encountered bad mat. w BOS @ 44'. Leverman raised BOS to 43' &found quality mat. BOS raised to 41' further in the cut to avoid bad mat. Dump moved y-valves from 1340-1535. Dr stopped digging @ 2205 mid-cut to pull back & dig the smaller adjacent cut. Dr taking 4-5' steps & swinging at 50 fpm. Vel.-14.0 fps Line Density-1.15

BriefComments: Beat DWH Estimate Poor TE do to rough seas found good mat.
ExtendedComments: Dump piped up from 0055-0255. Dr finished cut @ 0925 & moved to continue the cut they were in yesterday. Dr was down for rough seas from 1300-2400. Leverman kept BOS @ 41' to maintain good material. Dr taking 3-5' steps & swinging at 50 fpm. Vel.-14.4 fps Line Density-1.15

BriefComments: Beat DWH Estimate Poor TE do to rough seas finding good mat.
ExtendedComments: Dr was down for rough seas from 0000-1255. Dump piped up from 1500-1710. Dr finished cut @ 2400 & moved to the next parallel cut in BA B3. Leverman kept BOS @ 39' throughtout most of the cut but had to raise the BOS to 38' for the last 40' to maintain quality material. Dr taking 4-5' steps & swinging at 54 fpm. Vel.-14.3 fps Line Density-1.17

BriefComments: Dredge AK dug on Cut 3C with BOS @ 42.2. with medhigh face. Towed in due to weather.
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK dug on Cut 3C with fairly good material. Digging medhigh face with BOS @ 42.2. Dredge DigWH was ~1469 for fairly good production due to good material. Major delays include moving achors (1.58 hrs) and Changing cuts from 2C to 3C for (4.67 hrs.). At 16:30 dredge began to wash out line to be towed into to Charleston Harbor due to weather conditions offshore.

BriefComments: Dredge AK began digging at 1600 on Cut 9C. Dredge BOS @ 38 ft. with 4 ft of face
ExtendedComments: Dredge Ak began digging with BOS @ 39 ft. at STA 1700 picked up to 38 ft. due to reported clay on dump. Dredge dug with medium face with high production. Dredge is digging cut 3C and dug from 16:00 to 23:40 for our highest CYWH thus far.

BriefComments: Dredge AK digging Cut 9C. BOS @ 39.5 for 6 ft. of face. Good material High production
ExtendedComments: The Dredge AK is currently digging Cut 9C a new cut. Yesterday 5 pieces of submerged pipeline were removed from the existing line to be used in the second subline. Dredge BOS @ 39.5 for 6 ft. of face. With shortend pipeline and good material dredge was able to do 1910 CYWH our second best day on project. Major delays for breaking back pipeline (7 hrs.) and fill site requested stops for (2.25 hrs.)

BriefComments: Dr AK digging in Cut C9.BOS @ 39.5 ft. with 6 ft. of face. single swing and step.
ExtendedComments: Dr AK digging on Cut C9 with a sing swing and step. Dredge is maintain good velocity and has not had to wash out line often. Good material and WH have made for good production. Dredge is digging with BOS at 39.5 ft. and 6 feet of face. Dredged finished cut C9 and moved to C4 at 21:10 where it stayed the rest of the night. Dredge changed out 20 cutter teeth only keeping 8. Primary delays include Fill Site piping up for (6.67 hrs.) and Changing cuts for (2.25 hrs.)

BriefComments: Dr AK digging in Cut 4C Single Swing BOS @ 37.5 Velocity 16.6 Swing 50 ftmin
ExtendedComments: Dr AK digging in borrow area B Cut 4C. Dredge dug all day with minimal delays for our highest CYWH yet. Dredge is digging with a single swing with swing speed at 50 ftmin. BOS @ 37.5 for 6 ft. of face. Average velocity is 16.6 with a density of 1.23. Dredge steps 5 ft. on cut swing and 3 ft. on back swing. Dredge pulled back at the end of Cut 4C and resumed digging on Cut 5C in the afternoon. Primary delays are Move Anchors for (2.72 hrs.) and Changing Cuts for (2.42 hrs.)

BriefComments: Fair TE beat DWH estimate encountered bad material
ExtendedComments: Broken shackle on a stern anchor from 0000-0110. From 1000-1050 crew cleaned the MP & check the cutter. Moved to the next parallel cut in BA B3 from 1435-1915. @ 1935 the port breast wire needed to be repaired but the seas were too rough to perform repairs so the Dr remained down until 2400. Leverman kept BOS @ 38' throughtout most of the cut but had to raise the BOS in 1' increments to avoid poor material. Dr taking 4-5' steps & swinging at 53 fpm. Vel.-15.8 fps Line Density-1.25

BriefComments: Fair TE beat DWH estimate moved ahead 3x to avoid mudsilt
ExtendedComments: Dr down from 0000-0715 due to rough seas. Changed port breast wire from 0715-1240. Started digging @ 1255. Dr moved 3x to avoid mud & silt material (1405-1420 1535-1640 1900-2040). Leverman kept BOS between 32-35' throughtout most of the cut but but was able to lower the BOS to 38' near the end. Dr taking 5-6' steps & swinging at 62 fpm. Vel.-14.0 fps Line Density-1.23

BriefComments: Low TE (Fill site pipe up 5x) beat DigWH Est.
ExtendedComments: Due to the fine material and narrower berm width the fill site used just one discharge line during the day to give the material a larger area to stack up in. This led to the fill site having to pipe up 5x. Misc. delay was when the crew had to work on the strbd swing brake. Leverman kept BOS between 38' until STA 8+33 when the BOS was raised to 35'. Dr taking 4-5' steps & swinging at 54 fpm. Vel.-16.0 fps Line Density-1.23

BriefComments: Low TE (Fill site pipe up 5x) beat DigWH Est.
ExtendedComments: Due to narrower berm width the fill site used just one discharge line during the day to give the material a larger area to stack up in. This led to the fill site having to pipe up 5x. Dredge moved cuts @ 1500 in order to leave 250' in the cut so that we can make one cut perpendicular. BriefComments: Constant adjustment of BOS cont. to slow coverage cutter still tripping
ExtendedComments: Dr finished Cut 8B & moved to 9B @ 0100. Dig face remained between (3.5-4') for most of the day until the last 200' feet (5' of face). The cutter motor continued to trip but only occurred 10-12x. Constant changing of the BOS & the cutter motor trips continue to hinder coverage but efforts are being made to minimize these factors. 4-6' sets. Swing speed-61 Den-1.12 Vel-21.8 Today's pay is greater than the dig due to material washing in to the beach template from the recent storm.

BriefComments: Improvement on the DigWH; Constant ladder depth change limits production
ExtendedComments: Yesterday at 0700 the dredge finished its reach in Cut 9B and pulled back to begin digging in Cut 10B (3.75 hour move).In Cut 9B the dredge was digging 3.5 feet of face. There has been more improvement on the digWH as we have found about 4 to 4.5 feet of face in Cut 10B.The constant changing of ladder depth and the stalling of the cutter head continues to hinder production.

BriefComments: Improved DigWH; Constant change of ladder depth hinders production.
ExtendedComments: The dredge was digging in an average face of 3.9 feet yesterday.The DigWH is still increasing every day with our estimate almost being matched.The constant changing of ladder depth and the stalling of the cutter head continues to hinder production.

BriefComments: Changed Directions in Cut; Southern end has higher dig face and better DigWH
ExtendedComments: Yesterday the dredge switched directions in Cut 10B and began digging southbound.In this southern stretch of the cut the dig face is much larger than the northern end.For the time they were in the southern end the DigWH was calculated to be 2537.This is a large improvement to the small face in the northern end.This larger available face is also in Cut 9B at the same stationing.

BriefComments: Great DigWH; major weather delay in SubJob 72
ExtendedComments: Yesterday the increase in dig face greatly increased our DigWH.We are now in an average of 5 feet of face towards the end of this cut.The major delay on the day was for the Port breast brake band eyebolt.It broke and the wire had to be changed out.At 2145 the dredge shut down for weather and will likely be shut down for the majority of the following day as well due to the heavy ground swell.

BriefComments: 12 hours Major weather in subjob 072; poor digging due to weather
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued to dig in cut 10B.During this short time they were digging during the day the production was hindered by the rough sea state. There were 4-5 foot ground swells throughout the day.They dug 40.5' - 39.5' of depth on the stbd side of the cut and 40.5' - 38.5' on the port side of the cut.This morining (91014)the dredge will be moving back to Cut 9b and begin digging south in the cut starting at station 21+50 (weather permitting).

BriefComments: Low CYWH due to rough seas. Shutdown at 8:30 due to swell
ExtendedComments: Moved the breast and swing wires for 0.92 hours.Finished Cut 10B and tried to move dredge into Cut 9B.Poor weather of rough seas and heavy swell prevented repositioning of the dredge in Cut 9B.Shutdown due to weather at 08:30.SS 72 BOS 45.7 Den 1.07 Vel 20.2.

BriefComments: Split RH w072 wx delay- Broken wires produced low TE. Low CYWH due to swell
ExtendedComments: Delays include 10.33 hours to position dredge in Cut 9B due to broken stern wire repair and 4.75 hours due to a broken breast wire and move of all anchors.BOS 42.5 SS 71 Den 1.09 Vel 21.6.Heavy swells generated lower than average CYWH also breaking wires due to the excessive dredge movement.In order to remove 4' of face the cutter is being held approximately 5' below the existing bottom.

BriefComments: Split RH wSJ072 WX. Improved CYWH due to improved sea state.
ExtendedComments: Delays include 7.25hrs replacing starboard breast wire (no wire in rack night time and sea state generated a lenthy delay) and 2.26 hrs total moving anchors (two instances where anchors would not set in the material and had to be reset).Heavy swells caused the dredge to shut down at 23:30.BOS 42.4 SS 64 Vel 20.2 Den 1.12.

BriefComments: DR AK finished completed the job at 17:00 and departed for Norfolk.
ExtendedComments: Delays include moving the anchors 3 times for a total of 0.51 hours and replacing the broken starboard swring wire for 1.92 hours.Dredge was down until just after 7am due to heavy swells.BOS 39.4 SS 76 Den 1.1 Vel 20.0.Dredge took more face than allowed for (over 5' as opposed to 4.5') due to heavy swells making it diffifult to maintain a depth.Taking more face improved production generating 2130 CYWH.

BriefComments: Dredge AK began digging @ 07:25
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK began digging @ 07:25 had to dig into cut and create enough water for her to have floatation at low tide.Borrow area depths ~8.0' MLLW. Digging Cut 01 (250' wide) BOS @ 18.0' 3'-4' steps each corner. Delays mostly to move anchors 3 sets of anchor moves.Misc delay to replace riser gasket (1.00 hrs).

BriefComments: Continued digging Cut 01 BOS @ 18' good face high TE
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continue digging Cut 01 (250' wide) BOS @ 18.0' MLLW.Good face high efficency.Total of 4 sets of anchor moves. Survey delay to conduct dye test. Dredge reading showed 20.4 fps tested showed 20.3 fps no adjustments made.Also standerdized the density gauge.

BriefComments: No major delay high face high efficency shorter line good production
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued digging Cut 01 (250') BOS @ 18.0' MLLW 3'-4' sets both corners average swing speed 59 fpm. No major delays.Move anchor sets 4 time total 3.14 hrs. Minor fill site delay to switch valves (0.42 hrs).Good face (9' - 10') high efficency shorter line length and good leverman resulting in high production.

BriefComments: AK completed Cut01 moved to Cut01A
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK completed digging Cut 01 (250') BOS @ 18.0' MLLW 3'-4' sets both corners average swing speed 61 fpm. Began Cut 01A. Major delay to move cuts (3.42 hrs). Move anchor sets 2 time total 1.33 hrs. Minor fill site delay to switch valves (0.08 hrs).Good face (9' - 10') high efficency shorter line length and good leverman resulting in high production.

BriefComments: AK completed Cut 01A moved to Cut 02A. 9'-10' of face
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK completed digging Cut 01A (250') BOS @ 18.0' MLLW 3'-4' sets both corners average swing speed 61 fpm. Began Cut 02A. Major delay to move cuts (2.08 hrs). Move anchor sets 3 time total 1.64 hrs. Also greased ladder & changed teeth.Good face (9' - 10') high efficency shorter line length and good leverman resulting in high production.

BriefComments: AK completed Cut02A moved to Cut02. Good production due to high face.
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK completed digging Cut 02A (250') BOS @ 18.0' MLLW 3'-4' sets both corners average swing speed 61 fpm. Began Cut 02A (250'). Major delay to repack MP (4.17 hrs) move cuts (2.42 hrs). Move anchor sets 2 time total 1.24 hrs. Also greased ladder & 3 changed teeth.Good face (9' - 10') high efficency and good leverman resulting in high production.

BriefComments: Dredge started back up at 345 digging in cut 2.
ExtendedComments: After the bearing was repaired the dredge began digging in cut 2 with BOS at 18' taking 3' to 5' steps in both corners and double swinging when necessary. The dredge is taking an average of 7' of face and leaving 15' of water this gives us a spillage of 30%. The dredge continues to exceed the estimate. The leverman stated that the cutter motor has been preforming much better and is able to swing at 64 fpm. Delays due mostly to shifting anchors (3.10 hrs)

BriefComments: Dredge continued digging in cut 2
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging in cut 2 with BOS at 18' taking 3' to 5' steps in both corners and double swinging when necessary. The dredge is taking an average of 7' of face and leaving 15' of water this gives us a spillage of 30%. The dredge continues to exceed the estimate. Delays due mostly to shifting anchors (2.19 hrs). A survey will be conduted as soon as the weather subsides.

BriefComments: Alaska was down for 12 hours awating tug repair
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging in cut 2 with BOS at 18' taking 3' to 5' steps in both corners. Dredge Alaska went down at 525 due to running out of line slack. No tugs were operable so the anchors could not be moved. Once the Lady Theos engine was repaired the Alaska started back up in Cut 2 at 1725.

BriefComments: Alaska completed Cut 2 moved to Cut 3
ExtendedComments: At 0200 Dregde Alaska finished digging in Cut 2 washed out the line and began shifting to Cut 3. The Alaska began digging in Cut 3 at 730 and dug without any major delays. Dredge continues to dig with the BOS at 18' taking 4' to 6' steps in both corners and double swinging when necessary.

BriefComments: Continued digging Cut 03 BOS @ 18'
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continue digging Cut 03 BOS @ 18.0' MLLW.Good face high efficency. Alaska shut down at 910 to check the main pump for ware and change cutter teeth (1.83 hrs). The pump showed minor ware and the Alaska resummed digging at 1100. Other major delays included shiffting anchors (2.41 hrs)

BriefComments: Dredge AK completed digging Cut 03
ExtendedComments: After completing Cut 03 Dredge Alaska went down at 2100 to wash out the line and move to Cut 04. Dredge Alaska did not resume digging until 0800 on the morning of 115 due to having to move from Cut 03 to Cut 04 with only 1 tug boat.

BriefComments: Dredge remained down till 0800 began digging in Cut 4
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK was down from 0000 to 8000 moving from Cut 3 to cut 4 with only one operable tug boat. Dredge AK dug the rest of the day (BOS @ 18.0' MLLW 3'-5' steps in both corners average swing speed 65 fpm.) without any major delays (shifting anchors 1.46 hrs). Tug Mary Virginia arrived on site yesterday to take the place of the Lady Theo.

BriefComments: Dredge AK dug in Cut 4
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 4 with BOS at 18' taking 3' to 5' steps in both corners and double swinging when necessary. Dredge Alaska experience 2.30 hrs of delays all for shifting anchors.

BriefComments: Dredge Alaska completed Cut 4
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska completed digging in Cut 4 at 1210 she then went down to move back to Cut 5. After changing cutter teeth(15)Dredge AK began digging in Cut 5 at1845 and dug without any major delays. Clean main pump delay - the crew checked the pump for ware it was no worse than the last time it was checked.

BriefComments: Dredge Alaska dug in Cut 5
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska contiuned to dig in Cut 5with BOS at 18' taking 3' to 5' steps in both corners and double swinging when necessary. Primary delay - shifting anchors (1.51 total hrs) Misc delay - clean underwater pump (0.33) check hooper valve (0.17)

BriefComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging in Cut 5
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued digging in Cut 5 with BOS at 18' taking 3' to 5' steps in both corners and double swinging when necessary. Dredge AK dug without any major delays. Primary and only delays were shifting anchors (3.13 total hrs)

BriefComments: Dregde completed Cut 6A Moved to Cut 7A Xmas tree broke
ExtendedComments: Dredge ALASKA completed Cut 06A at 16:30 and washed out to move to Cut 07A. Dredging operations resumed at 20:30.The dredge went down at 22:30 due to the Xmas tree breaking downthe dredge remained down for the rest of the day.The dredge is currently being prepared to tow inside to start repairing the xmas tree.

BriefComments: Dredge AK cont work offshore heavy seas caused for down time and lower production
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued working offshore Tybee Island Cut 07A w BOS @ 18.5' 3'-4' steps each corner.BOS lowered to take more material to ensure enough material to finish north section on Subline 01.Heavy seas caused for increased downtime and lower production.Pipeline delay for fixing air valve for total of 5.42 hrs.

BriefComments: AK continued digging Cut 08A BOS lowered to 18.5'
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued digging Offshore Borrow Area Cut 08A.BOS lowered to 18.5' leverman increased step size to 5'-6' swing speed average throughout the day 59 fpm.Production per work hour incresed.Engine Room delay for stbd breast wire not holding (2.25 hrs).

BriefComments: Dredge Alaska completed Cut 08A and began digging in Cut 09A
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued digging Offshore Borrow Area Cut 08A and Cut 09A with the BOS at 18.5' taking 5'-6 steps. Major delays include fixing the leverage arm on stbd spud drum (3.17 hrs) and the engine room cleaning the cooler on the gearbox (2.08 hrs)

BriefComments: Dredge AK dug in Cut 09A10A11A completed North end of beach
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK resumed digging at 03:35 in Cut 9A until she ran out of float hose at STA 26+50. Dredge AK then move back to cut 10A where she dug until 20:10 with minor delays. Dredge AK then moved to Cut 11A at 20:10 and dug till 5:25 this morning completing the North end of the beach.

BriefComments: Dredge made tow to offshore borrow area resumed digging at 1455

BriefComments: Digging in Cut 7A Completes subjob 041 shuts down due to leak in pipe
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued to dig in CUT 7A. Dredging AK was working in Subjob 042 (backside river) until 0320. At 0320 Dredge AK began working in subjob 041 (STA 75+00 - 135+00) until 1130 when she switched back to Subjob 042 until 1550 to complete the backside stations. Dredge AK shut down at 1550 due to a leak in the subline sea conditions are to rough to repair the leak.

BriefComments: Reapir subline Dig in Cut 7A
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska remained down until 1140 due to a leak in the subline. With favorable weather conditions the crew was able to repair the subline. Dredge AK began digging in Cut 7A (Subjob 41) at 1140 and dug without any major delays.

BriefComments: Dredge AK completed Cut 07A
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska completed digging in Cut 07A at 0030 Dredge AK then move to Cut 08A and resumed digging at 0530. At 0845 Dredge AK shut down to allow the dump to move up the y valve (2.25 hrs). Dredge AK then dug the rest of the day without and major delays.

BriefComments: Dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 08A completed Cut 08A at 2320
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued to dig in Cut 08A with BOS at 18.3' taking 4' to 6' steps in both corners and double swinging when necessary. Primary Delays were shutting down to wait for the Dump to move up y valves. Other than having to shut down for the Dump Dredge AK dug without any primary delays. Dredged AK completed Cut 08A at 2320 and started move to Cut 09A.

BriefComments: Dredge moved to Cut 09A dug without and primary delays shut down for weather
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska continued moving to Cut 09A until 500. Dredge AK dug (with BOS at 18.2' taking 4' to 6' steps in both corners and double swinging when necessary) without any primary delays until going down for weather at 2220. It was too rough for the tug boats to move the anchors as the Dredge had run out of anchor wire slack.

BriefComments: Dredge AK working Cut09A heavy fog and rough seas caused lower production.
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued working in Cut 09A with BOS @ 18.5'.Heavy fog and rough seas caused lower production.Major delay caused by the weather in the AM

BriefComments: AK continued work in Cut9A & 10A High downtime due to broken wires and stern brake
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued work in Cut 09A and moved to Cut 10A (4.50hrs). BOS @ 18.5' but lifted to 17.0' throughout the day due to clay in material. Mechanical delay for repairing stern hoist brake (5.25hrs) also replaced port swing wire (3.42hrs) and began replacing stbd breast wire at end of day (0.33hrs).Survey delay due to positioning computer shutting down (0.42hrs).

BriefComments: AK continued work Cut10A BOS @ 18.5' Long delay due to stbd breast wire replace
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK continued operations in Cut 10A digging with BOS @ 18.5'. Available face approx 8.0' to 8.5'.Minimual delay once the dredge resumed work after completing stbd breast wire replacement.Brest wire replacement took longer then normal due to rough seas.

BriefComments: Alaska continued to dig in reach 1 pulls back and digs in reach 2
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska was down until 4:15 due to the float-hose falling down on the riser. Dredge AK resumed digging in Reach 1 lift 01 @ STA 31+40 BOS @ 37' taking 5' steps. Dredge AK reached sta 43+00 and ran out of anchor wire. The anchor could not be moved due to unfavorable weather conditions. Dredge AK then pulled back and began digging lift 2 at STA 3935. Dredge AK primary delays were the float hose (4.25 hrs) and shifting anchors (5.42 hrs).

BriefComments: Dredge AK continued digging in reach 1 lift 02 @ STA 41+76 BOS @ 44' taking 5' steps
ExtendedComments: Alaska reached STA 43+32 at 1:55 AK went down at 01:55 till 8:15 due to not being able to move anchors. The Tugs were unable to move the anchor because it was a full moon low tide there were high winds from the North and the current is very strong. Once the anchor was able to be moved Dredge AKmoved back to station 25+16 and began digging in Cut 02. Dredge AK was able to dig the rest of the day without and primary delays.

BriefComments: AK completed digging in lift 02 BOS @ 44' 5' steps. Began digging lift 3 BOS 48'
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska resumed digging in Reach 1 lift 02 @ STA 33+00. AK dug from STA 33+00 to STA 42+00 without any primary delays until pulling ahead to STA 4332 and completing lift 02 at STA 44+68. Dredge AK then pulled back to STA 25+00 and began digging lift 03.Subline installation across the channel went very well yesterday. We have confirmed that the pipeline is below navigation depth.

BriefComments: Dredge AK resumed digging in Reach 1 lift 3
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska resumed digging in Reach 1 lift 03 @ STA 26+43 BOS 48'. AK dug without any primary delays.

BriefComments: Digging outbound in Reach 2 Lift 1 with BOS @ 37' taking 6' sets.
ExtendedComments: At 05:55 the riser fell around in the current (1.75 hrs). The dredge had to move anchors at 11:15 to allow a USCG cutter to move Red Buoy #12 (5.08 hrs).The USCG was unable to move the buoy.

BriefComments: Continued digging in high face with favorable material in BH Reach 1&2
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging outbound in BH Reach 2 with BOS @ 37' before setting back and digging the same area with BOS@ 44'. At 10:05 subline was added and the delay continued until 23:10 for installation. At startup the dredge pulled back to STA 16+88 and began digging with BOS @ 37'. 5' Sets are being taken in each corner. Average Swing Speep: 64 ftmin. Average Density: 1.12

BriefComments: Decrease in production due to low face in the area.
ExtendedComments: The low face and fine material allowed for increased travel. The dredge dug 3 lifts in Reach 1 BOS was 37' 44' and 47'. The change cut delay is the dredge pulling back for each new lift (2x for 6 hrs). Misc. delay was due to the port spud friction slipping (0.17 hrs). Average swing speed: 63 ftmin. Average density: 1.10.1902

BriefComments: Production continued to be low due to the low face.
ExtendedComments: Travel is high due to the mine material and low face. The swing and breast anchor were fouled up with net and wire from 14:30 to 23:40; this is under the Misc. delay for 9.17 hrs. The dredge had 2 anchor moves and the traffic delay was for 2 passing ships. The dredge is digging lift 3 with a BOS @ 47' taking 5' sets in each corner. Anerage velocity: 18.7 ftsec. Average density: 1.08. Average Swing Speed: 70 ftmin.

BriefComments: Production was high while digging new material in SI with high face.
ExtendedComments: The dredge moved move to Smith Island in the early morning. Submerged pipeline still needed to be placed and was done so at first light under Misc. Delay for 7.5 hours . Digging operations in Smith Island began at 15:30 Starting at STA 04+71. The main engine cluched out twice for 1.33 hours.

BriefComments: Production lower due to lower face after the cut change.
ExtendedComments: The dredge shifted to the red side of the borrow area to continue digging outbound. The USACE changed the limits of the borrow area and the dig plans area being reassessed. Digging BOS 44' taking 5' sets in each corner. Average Density: 1.17. Average Swing Speed: 57 ftmin. Average Velocity: 18.6 fts

BriefComments: Continued digging red side of borrow area to 44' with low face limiting production.
ExtendedComments: Once the dredge finished out the pass it moved to STA 15+00 at 13:25 to dig new passes inbound on the green side of the dig area. This area is a shoal with shallow water between 5-10 feet MLLW. This first pass is being dug to a depth of 27'. 5' steps are being taken in STBD corner. Mechanical Delay for fixing air leak on ladder. Average Density: 1.15. Average Swingg Speed: 62 ftmin. Average Velocity: 18.5 fts

BriefComments: High production is due to the high face in the area.
ExtendedComments: The dredge is digging inbound on the green tow in Smith Island. The dredge hit a shell pocket resulting in a pump shell bolt leak(1.08 hrs) and having to wash out the line twice (1.25 hrs). There was an air valve leak on the ladder for 1.33 hrs. High face is expected to continue as the dredge digs the first lift of the shoal on the green toe. Average Velocity: 18.5. Average Density: 1.26. Average Swing Speed: 61.

BriefComments: The dredge is digging inbound on the green tow in Smith Island BOS @ 27'
ExtendedComments: Dredge Alaska remained down due to weather until 605. Dredge AK resumed digging inbound on the green tow in Smith Island. High face is expected to continue as the dredge digs the first lift of the shoal on the green toe. Misc Delay - Wash out line due to shell. Mechanica Delay - Shut down to check Hoffer Valve Hoffer Valve flapper is bent. Engine Room Delay - Dredge lost power to generator.

BriefComments: Completed first inbound pass pulled back to STA 15+00 began digging second pass
ExtendedComments: The Alaska completed the first pass at 08:00 and pulled back to STA 15+00 to begin the second pass. The dredge is digging the second pass with BOS at 36' and swinging 95' past the green toe limit to box cut the slope. This plan has the dredge digging 45' beyond the slope due to the high face.

BriefComments: Completed second inbound pass pulled back to STA 15+00 began digging third pass
ExtendedComments: Based off survey data the over swing on the port side was brought in 30'. The change took place at STA 500 and AK was then over swingging 55' from the slope65' from the channel toe with the BOS @ 36' for the remainder of the second pass which was completed at 1800.The dredge then pulled back to STA 1500 to begin the third pass. The pass calls for an over swing of 50' from the slope60' from the channel toe with the BOS @ 44'. The STBD range constantly changes based on the contour line. Avg step size 6' Avg V 19.0.

BriefComments: Production high due to favorable material. BOS@44'. 5' sets in each corner
ExtendedComments: Continuing to dig the 3rd pass in Smith Island after this pass is completed the dredge will pull back to STA 15+00 and dig the final pass with a BOS of 48'. The STBD breast wire broke at 05:25 causing a 6.33 hours delay. The dredge will be down on 128 to install the booster Jack in line and replace the STBD idler sheave. Average Density: 1.23. Average Swing Speed: 65. Averave Velocity: 19.8.

BriefComments: Dredge AK completed lift 3 pulled back to STA 15+00 began digging Lift 4 cut 1
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK completed lift 3 @ 1:30 and then pulled back to STA 14+85 to begin lift 4 cut 1. Lift 4 Cut 1 call of BOS at 46.6'. The PORT range constantly changes based on the contour line 45' contour. Lift 4 is being broken down into two cuts as the width of the cut is too great for just one. Lift 4 Cut 1 is a low face pass in the center of the channel with not much face above grade. Dredge Alaska dug the remainder of the day with out any delays closing out at STA 1+30. Avg step size 6' Avg V 18.6

BriefComments: Started and completed Lift 4 Cut 2 began to pull back to STA 15+00 to dig outbound
ExtendedComments: Dredge AK begin digging lift 4 cut 2 with BOS @ 47 at 3:20 starting at STA 14+80. Dredge Alaska dug the remainder of the day with out any major delays before completing lift 4 cut 2 at 23:00. The dredge started to dig clay so the ladder was brought up a half foot. Dredge AK then began to pull back to begin digging outbound from STA 15+00. Avg Step Size 6' Avg velocity 18.1. Engine room mechincal delay was due to the oil lined gear box busting.

BriefComments: AK started digging out bound Completed Cut 1A pulled back to STA 1500 and began Cut 1B
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Alaska began digging in the Smith Island Channel Lift 1A from STA 14+50 to 21+97. Lift 1 called for BOS @ 20' and over swing 120' from the channel toe (green side). AK completed Lift 1A at 1400 and then pulled back and began to dug Lift 1B from STA 14+66 to 17+93. Lift 1B calls for BOS @ 31 and over swing of 80' from the channel toe (green side). Avg velocity 16.8 Avg step 6' double swinging when necessary to reach the corner.

Dredge Alaska shut down due to rough weather at 0525 and was down until 1515. The slack tide allowed the anchors to be moved and the dredge was able to dig until 1610 before again having to shut down due to weather. AK was able to resume digging at 2215 and finished the day at STA 24+09. Avg velocity 15.9 Avg step 6' double swinging when necessary to reach the corner.

The Dredge pulled back to STA 15+00 to begin lift 2 (without the Booster being used) BOS @ 41' overswinging 50' from the channel toe. AK ended the day digging lift 2 at STA 19+00. Avg velocity 17.9 Avg step size 7'

BriefComments: Production was higher due to favorable material in the area.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging the 3rd pass outbound in Smith Island. The booster Jack was added at 14:40 to test production numbers of only the dredge vs the dredge and the booster. BriefComments: Production down due to low face.

After the dredge pulled back the Booster Jack was bypassed after no change in production was seen.

BriefComments: Production down due to low face.
ExtendedComments: The dredge began outbound in Smith Island Channel. Production was low due to low face. After the dredge pulled back the Booster Jack was bypassed after no change in production was seen.

BriefComments: Continued digging the last lift in Smith Island. BOS@48' taking 5-6' sets.

The UWP kept tripping off and had to be checked. Crews were putting together subline and the dredge had to wait fro a tug to be free to move anchors. Average Swing Speed: 57 ftmin. Average Density: 1.22. Average Velocity: 18.1 ftsec.

BriefComments: Production high due to high face on the green side of the dig area.

The MG Set kicked off twice (0.08 hrs). The swing wire was cut and replaced (1.33 hrs). Average Swing Speed: 58 ftmin. Average Density: 1.23. Average Velocity: 18.2 fts
