Forecast Wx for 129:E winds 20 to 25 kt...diminishing to 10 to 15 kt early in the afternoon then becoming W 15 to 20 kt late. Seas 8 to 10 ft and subsiding to 5 to 7 ft by late afternoonevening.

BriefComments: 8hr Wx delay cont. inbound Cut 6 travel 596' in 12WH.
ExtendedComments: Digging inbound of Cut 6 with BOS at 10' below the bd making 280' swings in the cut. Continuing to dig 6.5-7' of face supported by survey cross sections conducted on 121013.Making 4-6' steps.Changed out 15 teeth and grease up during downtime.1hr delay for tightening belt on stern connection.

BriefComments: Completed Cut 6 Wx delays for 13.92 to start in Cut 7
ExtendedComments: Completed Cut 6 at 0025.Heavy seas while changing to Cut 7 delayed crew ability to set anchors. Commenced digging in Cut 7 inbound at 1300.At 2240 tugs could not get to port side to move anchors and delayed due to Wx.Making 3-6' steps with average swing speed of 81 fpm. Avg Cutter Amps at 1134 yet continue to spike up to 2230 while digging and consequently the cutter speed avg of 27 will decline with increase in amps.

BriefComments: Wx dly: 3.25hrs RH: 13.75hrs Major Mech dly: 7hrs
ExtendedComments: From previous day til 0315 night crew could not set anchors due to heavy seas on port side.Generator on anchor barge wouldn't run and required maint. Anchors were set and recommenced digging in Cut 7 inbound at 0500. 3x shots of water for dump for .83hrs delay.Down from 1135-1400 for wash out line move Y-vlv and break float hose around dredge grease ladderhauling gear and change 2 teeth.At 1700 liner bolt blew out and dredge was under tow to Shinnecock Inlet for maintenance.

BriefComments: Commenced digging Cut 8 outbound at 1255.
ExtendedComments: Under tow from Shinnecock Inlet at 0730 after major mechanical delays. Making 4-6' steps with average swing speed of 78 fpm. Avg Cutter Amps at 795 with Avg Cutter Speed at 29.Total delays after 1255 start time for production totaled .75hrs.Dump - shot of water (x1) for .17hrs and shifting anchors for .58hrs.

BriefComments: Completed digging in Cut#8 outbound shifted to Cut#9.
ExtendedComments: Total travel 879'. Making 3-6' steps with average swing speed of 87 fpm. Avg Cutter Amps at 926 with Avg Cutter Speed at 29. Total Delays for production totaled 5.00hrs.Dump - shot of water (x3) for 1.17hrs. Shifting anchors for 1.17hrs. Change Cut beggining at 1440 for 2.67hrs.

BriefComments: Finished Dredging Cut 9. Dredged Cut 10 stations 700-712
ExtendedComments: Total travel 881'. Making 3-6' steps with average swing speed of 89 fpm. Avg Cutter Amps at 825 with Avg Cutter Speed at 29. Cut 9 was completed at 2200 before dredge moved to station 700 at cut 10 moving outbound. Total Delays for production totaled 6.58hrs.

BriefComments: DR continued digging BA2 cut 11 outbound.
ExtendedComments: The Illinois continues digging outbound in Cut 11. Three pieces of 780' subline were towed out of the inlet and sank offshore near BA3 with anticipation to set on location during daylight hours on 010914. The air compressor broke down while towing out the subline. Plan to move to Cut 10 digging outbound before towing the dredge in for anticipated weather. Dump delays include shots of water(11x) adding pipe and valve moves. Average velocity of 18.2 and swing speed of 88 for the night leverman & 64 for day.

BriefComments: Towed to inlet at 11:45 for anticipated weather.
ExtendedComments: Continued digging Cut 11 outbound until 0815 then moved to Cut 10 digging 100' before towing into the inlet for anticipated weather. Pump RPM's are remaining high at 337 with falling velocities represent pump limitations based on the 15071 ft of line. Velocity averaged 17.3 fts for the daytime leverman and 18.4 fts for the nightime leverman. Delays for dump include washing the line (7x) moving y-valve and adding pipe. 1.75hr delay to put ladder in hangers and check cutter box for leaking.

BriefComments: Towed out @ 10:00. Began digging BA2 Cut 12 outbound @16:00
ExtendedComments: Towed out of Shinnecock Inlet once the sea state was calm enough at 10:00 arriving at location at 13:40. Digging began at 16:00 once anchors were set and float hose was attached. While digging making 4-6' swings with average swing speed of 75. Avg Cutter Amps at 816 yet continue to spike up to 1114 while digging and consequently the cutter speed avg of 28 will decline with increase in amps. Once digging commenced the fill crew began to place material on STA 81+00. Dump delay for one shot of water.

BriefComments: Towed to BA#2 to commence digging
ExtendedComments: Towed out of Shinnecock Inlet at 0700 arriving at location at 1110. Digging began at 1345 once anchors were set and float hose was attached. While digging making 4-6' swings with average swing speed of 77.Avg Cutter Amps at 655 yet continue to spike up above 1500 while digging. Average velocity of 22.0 and swing speed of 92 for day & 67 for night leverman.Once digging commenced the fill crew began to place material on STA 81+00. Dump delay for 2 shots of water; and to fix pipe at the dump.

BriefComments: Completed digging in Cut#12 outbound shifted to Cut#13
ExtendedComments: 10.5hr delay due to tugs unable to move anchors 2 separate attempts made. While digging making 4-6' swings with average swing speed of 81.Avg Cutter Amps at 987. Average velocity of 17.6 and swing speed of 85 for day & 75 for night leverman.Once digging commenced the fill crew began to place material on STA 76+00. Other delays for wash out line and tighten friction starboard sway wires and to shift to Cut 13.

BriefComments: Completed move to cut 13 began digging outbound.
ExtendedComments: Leaking air valve caused dredge to go down for 5.08 hrs repaired and continued digging.Washed out line (2x) for the dump moved anchors (1x). Daytime leverman 53 fps swing speed nighttime leverman 77 fps swing speed.

BriefComments: Digging cut 1 at 0750 completed at 2300. Strn anchor broke while moving to cut 2.
ExtendedComments: IL rode out ground swell and crew set stb swing anchor and attached float hose.During the move to cut 2 an air line broke on the anchor barge it has been fixed.Avg. swing speed 76fps velocity 20.8fps cutter amps 1125 cutter speed 27rpm. Digging single swings with 4-6' steps.BOS at 10' below BD.

BriefComments: Leaking air line on anchor barge and broken anchor delayed 9.08hrs.
ExtendedComments: A new anchor was brought from the supply barge to replace the broken anchor.Other delays include moving from cut 2 to cut 3 (2.42hrs) and moving anchors (1x - 0.50hrs).Daytime leverman swing speed 76fps nighttime leverman swing speed 71fps.Average velocity 18.8fps cutter amps 1012 cutter speed 28rpm.Digging single swing with 4-6' steps.BOS at 10' below BD.

BriefComments: Compl'd cut 2 moved to 3 digging outbound. Port swing wire broke delayed 1hr
ExtendedComments: 3.92hrs of delay to wash out line (9x).Once to break back and move y-valve remaining 8 to switch y-valve. 1.92hrs to move from cut 2 to cut 3. 1.58hrs to move anchors. Nighttime leverman swing speed 77fps daytime leverman 79fps.Average velocity 18.8fps cutter amps 969 cutter speed 28rpm.Digging single swing with 4-6' steps.BOS at 11' below BD.

BriefComments: Completed cut 3 fog delay 6.08hrs moved to cut 4 digging outbound.
ExtendedComments: Two dump delays for shots of water to roll the y-valve for 0.50hrs of delay.Moved anchors twice for 0.92hrs of delay.Nighttime leverman swing speed 68fps daytime leverman 80fps.Average velocity 18.7fps cutter amps 1082 cutter speed 28rpm.Digging single swing with 4-6' steps.BOS at 11' below BD.

BriefComments: Moved cut 4 to 5 digging outbound in BA3. Stb friction drum adjusted 0.50hrs delay.
ExtendedComments: Washed out the line 7x for the dump to switch y-valve for 1.25hrs of delay. Moved anchors 2x for 1.50hrs of delay.Changed cuts 3.08hrs.Nighttime leverman swing speed 77fps daytime leverman 71fps.Average velocity 18.0fps cutter amps 997 cutter speed 28rpm.Digging single swing with 4-6' steps.BOS at 11' below BD.

BriefComments: Finished cut 5 moved to cut 6. Washed out at 08:50 and towed into Shinnecock Inlet.
ExtendedComments: 1.33hrs of delay to move the dredge from cut 5 to cut 6.0.25hrs of delay for shots of water to switch y-valve (2x).Nighttime leverman swing speed 68fps daytime leverman 82fps.Average velocity 18.6fps cutter amps 880 cutter speed 29rpm.Digging single swing with 4-6' steps.BOS at 11' below BD.

BriefComments: Under tow from Inlet commenced digging BA#3 Cut#12
ExtendedComments: The dredge began tow to BA3 cut 12 at 0710 yesterday morning and began digging outbound at 1225.Digging stopped once to move anchors for 0.67hrs of delay.

BriefComments: Con't & completed Cut 12 Wx delays tugs unable to move anchors and shift cut
ExtendedComments: Dug to end of Cut 12 at 1020 and went down for weather delays.

BriefComments: Cont. digging Cut 11 outbound for 17.33hrs with 5.5hr wx dly
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging outbound in Cut 11 until 0735 due to a ground swell from the SW. Digging resumed at 1305 resulting in 5.50hrs of weather delay. Water was pumped 4x to switch the y-valve for 0.67 hours of delay and anchors were moved once for 0.50 hours.

BriefComments: Towed out to BA6b Cut 3 digging inbound @ 10:55. Beach landing at STA 10+30.
ExtendedComments: Dredge was towed out to borrow area at first light followed by the float hose. Began digging on station 06+40 at 10:55 with BOS at 32ft. Estimated 5.3ft of face on starboard corner and 9.5ft of face on port corner. After digging 220ft and conducting a CND survey data showed we were leaving material at 28ft It was decided to lower the BOS to 34ft. While digging cutter amps spiking frequently with max of 2230 Velocity of 18.8fps for daytime leverman & 23.1fps for nightime leverman.

BriefComments: Cont digging Cut 3 inbound travel 154' before towing to inlet @ 0930 for incoming wx
ExtendedComments: Delays for the dump include adding pipe (3x) and washing line (1x). While digging the nighttime levermen began making shorter swings to the center of Cut 3 in order to collect the material fallilng from the high bank. The shorter swings were incorperated every other pass. Digging inbound in Cut 3 stopped at 0930 so the dredge could flush the line and begin towing into the inlet. While inside the inlet the crew removed the front door in preparation to replace the shell for MP.

BriefComments: Towed to BA6b & began digging inbound @ 09:00. Cable & other debris in cutter while digging
ExtendedComments: The dredge was towed out of the inlet this morning and began digging at 09:00 in Cut 3 at station 11+70. 28 teeth were replaced on the cutter and the float hose was towed out by the night crew in preparation. Since startup the dredge has had to clean cable from the cutter 2x. Two pieces of subline were raised from 15393 Southampton borrow area 2 and brought into the inlet. Midnight beach station 8+00.

BriefComments: Finished Cut 3 @ 0830 moved to Cut 2 began digging @ 1210. Clean cutter 4x
ExtendedComments: Cable had to be cleaned from the cutter 4x and 17 teeth replaced. After moving anchors at 03:20 the stern anchor had been fouled and required additional attention until 04:55. Once the dredge moved to Cut 2 a CND survey was performed on Cut 3. Based on the survey it was decided to lower BOS an additional 2ft from 35ft to 36.5 - 37ft as well as reducing the step size from 4-6' to 2-4'. Based on beach surveys conducted in the afternoon fill to pay has been reduced to 1.02.

BriefComments: Cont digging Cut 2. Beach pass stations 11+00 - 0+0. Elbow flipped pumping westward.
ExtendedComments: Beach crew finished pumping east of the land to station 0+00 passing all stations. The elbow was flipped and pumping began westward at 18:25 on the beach. Delays for the dump include flipping the elbow (0.83hrs) and adding pipey-valve(1.08hrs). Cable continues to get caught in the cutter causing delays. BOS remains at 36.5' - 37' making single passes with 2-4' steps. Avg velocity of 19.8fps.

BriefComments: Cont digging Cut 2. Clean cutter 3x. Beach pass stations 12+00 - 13+00.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in Cut 2 from STA 13+37 to STA 18+50. Upon completion of Cut2 the dredge will move to Cut 3 STA 17+10 in order to finish the remaining 170ft in cut. Cable continues to get caught in the cutter causing delays along with changing teeth. BOS remains at 36.5' - 37' making single passes with 2-4' steps. Average velocity of 21fps.

BriefComments: Complt'd cut 2 and 3 digging in cut 1. Clean cutter 1x. Change packing in MP.
ExtendedComments: The dredge moved 2x for 3.5hrs of delay.Cleaning cutter for 0.25hrs of delay and replaced 8 cutter teeth for 0.50hrs of delay. Anchors were moved once for 0.67hrs of delay.BOS remains at 36.5' - 37' making single passes with 2-4' steps.Average velocity 20.7fps average density 1.23.

BriefComments: Con'd digging inbound in cut 1 until template filled at 2225.
ExtendedComments: Anchors moved once for 0.33hrs delay cutter cleaned and 1 tooth replaced 0.33hrs of delay 9 teeth replaced for 0.83hrs of delay dump delays 8x to add pipe switch y-valves or catch up the fill operation for 6.08hrs of delay.An additional dump delay of 1.58hrs after the beach crew believed the template had been filled and no further pumping was required.Exst'g material outside the template was used to push into the template and now needs to be replaced by approximately 3400CY.

BriefComments: Dredge IL began digging BA-B Cut 1B @ 16:40
ExtendedComments: After repairing the cutterhead the Dredge IL performed a velocity and ladder calibration.The IL began digging with BOS @ 55.0' dig face increasing to stbd.Delay for fill crew to adjust landing pipe (0.75 hrs) dredge clean main engine air filter during this time. Engine room report avg discharge pressure of 115 and avg velocity of 15.6 fps.

BriefComments: Dredge IL continued digging BA-B Cut 1B. Varying BOS from port to stbd.
ExtendedComments: Dredge IL continued digging BA-B Cut 1B with varying BOS from 58.0' (port) to 56.0' (stbd) dig face increasing to stbd. Avg swing speed 62 fps. Engine room report avg discharge pressure of 120 and avg velocity of 17.2 fps. Delay for fill crew to adjust landing pipe (1.75 hrs) dredge greased ladder during this time electrical delay for main generator trip out (1.00 hrs) survey delay to standardize density gauge (0.08 hrs) moved anchors 4x (2.76 hrs).

BriefComments: Dredge IL continues digging BA-B Fill Site complete pad add elbow & y-valve
ExtendedComments: Dredge IL continued digging BA-B Cut 1B with varying BOS from 58.0' (port) to 56.0' (stbd) dig face increasing to stbd. Completed Cut 1b @ 0845 and continued to Cut 11B. Avg swing speed 62 fps. Engine room report avg discharge pressure of 120 and avg velocity of 17.8 fps. Delay for fill crew to add pipe & yvalve (2.75 hrs) electrical delay for main generator trip out (0.75 hrs)mechanical delay to service water line (0.67 hrs) moved anchors 3x & shift in cut (1.83 hrs).

BriefComments: Dredge IL continues digging BA-B. Material issues limit dig face.
ExtendedComments: Dredge IL continued digging BA-B Cut 11B with varying BOS dig face varies thru cut. Completed Cut 11B moved to Cut 12B. Material issues caused the ladder to be raised through out the day leaving less face and causing lower production. Avg swing speed 61 fps. Engine room report avg discharge pressure of 110 and avg velocity of 16.8 fps. Delay to move cut grease ladder & change teeth (3.25 hrs) moved anchors 2x (1.25 hrs) changed cutter teeth (0.50 hrs) and port friction motor issues (0.50 hrs)

BriefComments: Dredge IL continues digging BA-B. Dig face limited based on USACE survey.
ExtendedComments: Dredge IL continued digging BA-B Cut 12B with varying BOS dig face varies thru cut. Completed Cut 12B moved to Cut 11B completed and moved to Cut 3B. Avg swing speed 62 fps. Engine room report avg discharge pressure of 101 and avg velocity of 16.7 fps. Replaced first 3 teeth on each cutter vein with pick teeth to help cutter dig unseccessful.

BriefComments: Dredge IL cont dig Cut 2B into 3B MP rpm lowered to reduce velocity on short shoreline
ExtendedComments: Dredge IL continued digging BA-B Cut 2B with varying BOS dig face varies thru cut. Moved into Cut 3B. Avg swing speed 55 fps. Engine room report avg discharge pressure of 105 and avg velocity of 16.5 fps. Pick teeth on tip of cutter were unseccessful switched back to all paddle teeth. Lowered MP speed to decrease discharge velocity while on lower shoreline.

BriefComments: High TE.Fine material is being taken out of the borrow area.
ExtendedComments: The cutter head RPMs have been spiking up to 2000 then dropping down to 400 hindering our production.The cutter has been a limiting factor for the project thusfar.Subline investigations have shown no leaks to date. Profile lines are being run behind the dredge to check the amount of face being taken.

BriefComments: Dug cut 3B and moved to 4B at 2100.Remain cutter limited.
ExtendedComments: 1.57 hours were spent moving dredge anchors the dredge move took 1.55 hours changing the teeth took 0.95 hours and greasing lasted for 0.02 hours.Cannot achieve high swing speeds due to being cutter limited which lowers our hourly coverage in production.With a lower available face we are staying at a low volume.Rough sea conditions (5' sea swells) made it difficult to maintain steady bottom suction.BOS 53.4SS 58.Holding BOS 5.5' below surface to remove 4' face.

BriefComments: Cut 4B pull back 3000' to 3B. Incr vel & RPMs increased CYWH. Ctr amps spiking.
ExtendedComments: 3.07hrs to move dredge 2.57hrs to move anchors 0.38hrs to grease and 1.92hrs for the dredge engine (lost generator stbd main overheat cutter tripped and check fields on cutter motor).There was a test conducted on the dredge motor where the RPMs were increased and observations were made. Cut width of 250-260'.BOS 54.5 SS 59.Removing 4' of face by holding BOS 5.5' below existing.Increasing velocity wconstant density increased production by 100-200 CY max.Broken breast wire at 23:30.

BriefComments: Dug cut 3B. Low face on stbd side led to short swings.Low TE. Ctr amps spiking- low SS.
ExtendedComments: 10.5hrs repairing the stbd breast wire 3.15hrs ladder drive motor down 0.83hrs moving anchors.There was an area of low available face which had the dredge digging only the port side of the cut (130' swing vs 260'). Slow progress was made through the borrow area due to repairs. BOS 46.7' SS 67fps.Holding cutter 5.5' below existing face in order to remove 4' of face.Average velocity while digging is 18fps with a density of 1.135.

BriefComments: Dug cut 3B and 4B. Low SS due to tripping cutter. Broken port breast wire- repairs.
ExtendedComments: Delays include 5.2 hours repairing the broken port breast wire and 1.48 hours to move anchors 2x.Digging velocity averaged 18.1 fps with a density of 1.13.PS sides of cut have different dig depths causing the ladder to be raised and lowered constantly while digging.BOS 46' SS 62. Illinois is swinging slower than desired to avoid tripping the cutter when the cutter amps spike (from approximately 200 to over 2500).

BriefComments: 7.52RH due to wx delay. Low face-- low CYWH. Slow SS- try to stop tripping cutter.
ExtendedComments: Delays include 1.33 hours moving anchors and 16.48 hours due to Tropical Storm Bertha.Utilizing low SS to try and avoid tripping the cutter.BOS 45.5 SS 55.Low density of 1.11 shows low available face.Velocity of 16.9.While on wx delay the port breast wire broke at 0915 and will need to be repaired prior to resuming operations.Holding bottom of suction 5.5' below existing bottom in order to remove 4' of face.

BriefComments: Dr down for weather til 0913 finished Cut 4B good TE
ExtendedComments: Dr remained down until 0913 due to rough seas delaying breast wire repairs. Chris Slimmer was on board to oversee repairs to the cutter head motor. The leverman continue to remove ~4 ft of face by adjusting the BOS as they swing through the cut. @ 2221 Cut 4B was completed & the Dr began pulling back to the beginning of Cut 5B. Swing speed-65 Den-1.11 Vel-18.7

BriefComments: Good TE DigWH. Maj. Delay: could not swing with fuel barge along side
ExtendedComments: From 0600 to 0930 the Dr slowed the velocity to make the material more manageable for the fill crew as they filled the North taper. @ 1013 the Dr stopped digging to take on fuel. Digging did not resume until 1414 because the ground swells were larger than forecasted & the Dr could not swing safely with the barge tied along side. Swing speed-67 Den-1.14 Vel-16.9

BriefComments: Dig in area of high available face increased dig and prodWH.
ExtendedComments: Moving the dredge from 5B to 6B took 3.72hrs moving anchors for a total of 2.01hrs greasing up for 0.53hrs and adjusting the stbd breast wire due to friction for 0.08hrs.The dredge was pulled back in cut 5B 300' earlier than anticipated to avoid making the move in the middle of the night & to keep dredge away from the subline swing radius when we move the line to better service the remainder of the BA.BOS 46.7 SS 62 Vel 17.3 Den 1.17.

BriefComments: High production values due to high available face.TE well above estimate.
ExtendedComments: Delays include shifting anchors (3x) for 2.3hrs losing the generator (3x) for 2.27hrs greasing for 0.38hrs and changing roto seal on clutch (0.47hrs).Production numbers are high due to digging in an area of high available face.BOS 44.1 SS 62 Vel. 17.6 Den. 1.23.Hold cutter 5.5 feet below existing bottom in order to remove 4 feet of face.

BriefComments: Shell in line dropped velocity- flush. Cutter still limited decr SS.
ExtendedComments: Change from 6B to 5B- 1.82hrs move anchors (5x)- 1.91hrs clean main pump- 0.37hrs move Y valve- 2.4hrs clean pipeline due to accumulation of shell decreasing velocity- 1.03hrs lost main gen- 0.33hrs and main pump engine not clutch in and change roto seal on clutch- 0.77hrs. BOS 49 SS 65 Vel 16.7 Den 1.15. At BA B Cut 6 sta 50+95 fill site picked up silt 50+00 @ 51' picked up clay balls 49+70 @ 50' change 7 teeth 48+20 @ 53' clay balls. Gravel pumped onto fill at 35+00-37+00 from BAB 5B 48+18 @ 53.5'

BriefComments: Dr in wx delay until 0316 swung subline encountered some clay
ExtendedComments: Dr was delay for weather until 0316 in SJ 070. @ 0722 the Dr washed out the line so the crew could swing the subline. She commenced digging at 1339. The main generator went down 3x causing 0.95 hrs delay. Dr encountered some clay yesterday & had to raise the BOS 1'.

BriefComments: Great TE & DigWH Dr finished Cut 5B
ExtendedComments: Dr IL finished digging Cut 5B @ 1744 & pulled back to finish Cut 4B. She commenced digging at 2033. Dr encountered mud & clay in Cut 5B at STA 42+00. The Dr was picked up 1 ft. Main generator went down once for a 0.15 hr delay.Misc Delay: wash out line. 5-7' sets. Swing speed-56 Den-1.23 Vel-17.1

BriefComments: Great Digwh down wcutter motor fuses (4.13hr)
ExtendedComments: Dr IL continued Digging in Cut 4B up to Sta 31+37. We may have hit something at sta 40+40 and that was when the cutter went out. Cutter Motor Fuses delay 6.17hr. 0.63hr Delay changing 5 teeth. 2.02hr. Moving Anchors. 5-7' sets. Swing speed-57 Den-1.22 Vel-17.9

BriefComments: Good TE Dig WH Dr finished Cut 4B & moved to Cut 6B
ExtendedComments: Dr finished Cut 4B @ 0310 & moved to Cut 6B. Digging resumed @ 0633. @ the beginning of Cut 6B the Dr found clay & had to adjust the ladder 1 ft. Dr went down once for 0.78hrs to clean the cutter head of clay. 5-7' sets. Swing speed-52 Den-1.17 Vel-18.1

BriefComments: Good te & digwh finished cut 6B moved to start of cut 7B
ExtendedComments: Dredge was digging in cut 6B untill station 30+33 before moving to cut 7B starting up at 14:52 @ Sta 52+63. During the move to cut 7B 5 - 38DS teeth changed checked the ladder depth reading and dredge took on fuel. 2.45hr delay shifting anchors throughout the day.

BriefComments: Great TE day with lower CYWH due to less available face
ExtendedComments: The dredge dug between stations 48+52 and 35+77 in cut 7B with great TE throughout the day.There has been lower CYWH due to lower available face relative to previous days.1.8 hours of delay to move anchors 4 times throughout the day.During the 0.53 hr delay to grease up the ladder 8 teeth were replaced.

BriefComments: Great TE day with few delays involving moving anchors (5x) and a Y-Valve move
ExtendedComments: The dredge dug between stations 35+57 and 25+56 in cut 7B with great TE throughout the day.During the 1.75 hour delay to advance the Y-Valve on the beach three cutter teeth were replaced.Ancors were moved 5 seperate times during the day totaling in 2.48 hours of delay.

BriefComments: Remain cutter limited.TE remains high despite long dredge move delay
ExtendedComments: Delays include moving anchors twice for 1.25 hours greasing for 0.37 hours and moving from Cut 7B to 8B for 3.58 hours.Remain cutter limited. BOS 44.9 SS 51 Den 1.19 Vel 17.3.Cut 7B was completed as far as the current subline setup would allow and we moved to the beginning of Cut 8B. 2 teeth were replaced while the dredge was moving.The cutter is being held 5.5' below the existing bottom in order to remove 4'.

BriefComments: Lower CYWH due to less face avl in Cut 9B. High TE despite changing cuts
ExtendedComments: Delays include 1.7 hours moving anchors 3.15 hours changing cuts 0.6 hours greasing 0.17 hours due to a leak on the beach and 0.83 hours to repack the main pump.BOS 46.3 SS 56 Vel 17.3 Den 1.15.The dredge moved from cut 8B to 9B in order to dig the Northernmost portion of the BA prior to the subline move.As planned the subline move will allow the IL to dig the remainder of BA B without interruption.High sea state generated spikes in the cutter amps.

BriefComments: RH split wSJ070 for wx. Dredge digging 1 foot shallower to aleviate overdig
ExtendedComments: Delays include 1.13 hours to move Y valves 1.31 hours total to move anchors and 3.03 hours due to the generator switching gears.Dredge shutdown due to weather at 23:10.While down for weather the ball broke off the air valve and will have to be repaired prior to startup.BOS 46.3 SS 51 Vel 17.6 Den 1.2.Pump RPM reduced to target a velocity of 16-17 fps on the new shorter subline.

BriefComments: Split RH wSJ080. Resumed work from mech delay.
ExtendedComments: Delays consisted of 0.71 hours for calibrations 0.43 hours to shift anchors 1.49 hours due to a leak on the booster 2.3 hours due to cleaning the line and 1.08 hours to repair a leak in the pipeline.BOS 41.5 SS 52 Vel 17.9 Den 1.2.A good deal of shell hash was encountered in BA-A resulting in flushing the line in order to raise velocity.Ladder was raised in an effort to locate better material and improve production.

BriefComments: Pipeline Gland Seal Pump repair; Clean Lines (3x); Better Material @ STA 66+78
ExtendedComments: The Dredge IL continued digging in Borrow Area with the booster Jack.The dredge moved anchors twice amounting to 0.91 hours of delay.Dredge didn't meet the estimated production due to hitting shell hash material in this cut.This required us to clean the line three times yesterday in order to bring up velocity. The depths were adjusted yesterday in order to find better material digging through this cut.At station 66+78 they reported to be pumping goodbetter material to the beach.

BriefComments: Cut8a encoutering shell hash in the cut lowering production.
ExtendedComments: encoutering shell hash material in this cut causing the velocity to drop and having to clean the line. 2.29hr was spent leaning the line on a total of three occasions. Booster Jack down for 6.03hrs repair its gland seal pumpThrough out the day the ladder was lowered and rasied in order to try and find material that contained less shell fragments. STA 65+06 (11:30) the BOS lowered 1ft from 51' to 52' then at STA 63+68 (17:45) ladder raised 1ft from 52' to 51. Bstr Avg. (In-33 Out-112 Rack-84 P.RPM-298)

BriefComments: Change cuts 8a to 1b finding better material with less shell increased production
ExtendedComments: Dredge IL start morning diging in Cut 8A at 7:00 the BOS was raised from 50' to 48' in order to try and reduce shell content. At 8:07 dredge washed out the line and prepared to move to a West to East Cut 1B in order to try and find material with a lower shell content. During the move changed 4 teeth and the shore crew moved the Y-valve. The dredge started up again at 12:57. Less shell in cut 1b Cut 8A = 1321CYWH Cut 1B = @ 2884 CYWH. Bstr Avg. (In-35 Out-115 P.RPM-308)

BriefComments: Cut 1B production dropping off as head towards cut 8a will move to cut 2B
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued to dig in Cut 1B. Production dropped off as we approached cut 8a with the higher shell content. Dredge had to go down for 3.1hrs in order to repair a leak in the pipe near the riser. CF Production: 14026 @ 2280 CYWH. BSTR(In-33Out-102Rack-101P.RPM-287)

BriefComments: Moved Cuts 1B to 2B Production increased once moved cuts
ExtendedComments: Dredge started the morning in Cut 1B before washing the line and moving to Cut 2B at 8:33. Once the dredge primed up a pressure sensor was sent down the line but was unable to be recovered on the beach. The dredged start digging agin at 12:33. Cut1B - 16835 @ 2186CYWH Cut2B - 31600 @ 2816CYWH. (BSTR = In-28Out-93Rack-102P.RPM-290)

BriefComments: Cut2B Great TE swell limited production in the afternoon
ExtendedComments: cut 2B as the day progressed a swell formed causing a drop in the dredges production. Though she was able to keep on digging through out the day. The dredge shut down at 6:19am on the 99 due to weather and is currently shut down pumping water. It is most likely she will remain down for the remainder of the day.BSTR(In-33Out-106Rack-103P.RPM-294)

BriefComments: Cut2B Production reduced due to swell. 13.23hrs down with weather
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued in Cut 2B during the early hours of the yesterday morning. Before Shutting down for weather at 6:19. Production was heavily effect by a strong swell that had formed. Reducing travel from around 55-60ftwh to approx 30ftwh. As the weather subsided around midday the dredge moved into cut 1C. The dredge started up and dug for approximately 37mins before it snapped its STBD swing wire the dredge stopped for weather and the swing wire replaced. BSTR(In-31Out-100Rack-100P.RPM-297)

BriefComments: Dr. began digging SW with BOS @ 50.5 ft taking 5 foot steps.
ExtendedComments: Digging began at 12:30. Thespud barge is still not working properly. We can push the Dr. forward but needs to be manually reset slowing production. The dredge began digging BOS @ 51 ft but the ladder was picked up 0.5 ft to try to get less gravel. The dredge is working off predicted tides while the tide gauge is being replaced. We are expecting to get better production to increase as we start pumping again with equipment at the fill as well asl the higher face moving forward.

BriefComments: STBD Swing wire broke at 05:30. Narrow beach hampering mobility causing delays.
ExtendedComments: The progress on the fill site continues to be slow due to fitting pipe around the corner of the beach. Only one line is still being used in the narrow area hampering mobility and adding to the delay. The pipe this morning is around the corner and delays for fitting pipe and moving baskets should start to be less. The ladder still at 49 ft to try and avoid less gravel however we are still encountering small pieces.

BriefComments: Continuing to use 1 shore line due to narrow beach; extending delays.
ExtendedComments: The spud motor on the dredge burnt out at 1600 hours. The delay was getting the jacking motor set to lift the spud. We will be using the ladder to anchor the dredge while the spud caqrriage is being reset. Production increased some as the ladder was lowered in the cut to increase the face. At this time we believe the dredge is pump limited. The plan is remove 1000' submerge pipe soon.

BriefComments: The Dr. is digging outbound taking 5ft steps in the borrow area option one.
ExtendedComments: The fill site is still pumping on one line. We are only running with one dozer the other is down due to hydraulicissues creating longer delays when adding shore pipe and changing out baskets. Two more dozers will be arriving on site today and tomorrow. The booster discharge pressure is low but cannot increase it without pulling on the dredge. We believe the dredge is pump limited at this time and we plan on removing submerged pipe between the dredge and booster in the coming days when the weather allows.

BriefComments: The dr. stopped digging downstream at STA 257140 and turned around to dig upstream
ExtendedComments: The plan is to continue digging upstream to STA 254+500 before removing 2000 ft of subline and continuing to dig upstream. 7 shore pipe were added yesterday the fill site is continuing to pump on one line. The dredge was digging with BOS at 50.5 taking 3 ft steps. The spud began having electrical problems at 23:00 and continue through this morning. Chris Slimmer should be on site by midday to aid in repairs. Production is expected to pick up as we enter an area with higher face.

BriefComments: The electrical problems with the spud continued from yesterday.
ExtendedComments: The dredge was down for a total of 6.97 hours due to the spud and was using the jacking motor until Chris Slimmer could aid the crew. The dredge is continuing to dig upstream which is slowing our swing speed due to the width of the cut and the current. The plan is to continue digging upstream STA 254+500 before taking out 2000 ft of subline and continuing to dig upstream. The fill site is still running one line due to the narrow beach prolonging normal delays.

BriefComments: Dredge is digging upstream with BOS@50.5' taking 4-5ft steps swinging ~50ftmin.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued to dig upstream but production was suffering due to the length of pipeline. The dredge is pump limited and this morning we will be removing 1500 ft of subline moving to STA 253+300 and digging downstream. The fill site installed a Y valve to run a second line on the beach. This is used to wash out as we add shore pipe.

BriefComments: Dr. Illinois digging downstream with BOS @ 50.5' taking 4' steps.
ExtendedComments: To increase production the dredge moved to station 253+300 and took out 1500 feet of subline between the booster and the dredge. 9.36 hours were spent washing out line moving the dredge and taking out subline. The dredge will now be digging down stream. Production was significantly better after the dredge moved and took out the subline from 811 CYWH to 1861 CYWH.

BriefComments: Dr. Illinois digging downstream with BOS @ 50.5 ft taking 4 ft steps.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge completed operations in subjob 040 at 09:24 and began subjob 045 traveling a total of 313 feet. The booster had problems with the pump engine spaning 3 delays. The fuel injector was replaced for the main pump engine. The beach advanced roughly 400 feet with 3 delays.

BriefComments: Dr Illininois digging downstream with BOS @ 50.5 ft taking 4 ft steps.
ExtendedComments: There was a long delay in the morning while using the second line to add pipe the area was over filled and material had to salvaged reworked and graded. 9 pipe was added on the fill site. The cutter needed to be cleared of cable at 22:51.We are to continue digging downstream to 255+600 we will then remove 1500' of subline and move the dredge back to Cut 3.

BriefComments: Dredge digging with BOS @ 50.5 for 3 ft. of face. Swinging 524 ft wide swing.
ExtendedComments: The Dr Illinois is digging around 3 ft. of face in this section of the cut with the BOS at 50.5 to keep form overdigging material in the borrow area. Dr dug for good production even with the low TE. Most Delay time acruded to fill site for adding shore pipe and Changing Baskets. Dr also does its daily matenance when the dredge is down for the fill such as (grease ladder clean cutter change teeth ect..) Velocity at 16.9 with a density of 1.18. Dredge digging wide cut with a swing speed of 101 ftpm.

BriefComments: Dr. BOS @ 50.5 ft. for 3 ft. of face. Booster delay for Port Main Engine
ExtendedComments: The Dr. Illinois continued to dig outbound in the Delaware River with BOS @ 50.5 for 3 ft. of face. Dredge incurred extended delays due to Booster Jessie patch front door of MP as well as port main engine problems. Dredge swinging at 77 ftpm taking 4 ft. steps in the toe. Average density at 1.13 with a velocity of 15.7. Dredge incountering minor traffic delays and other delays are attributed to the booster and fill site when adding shore pipe.

BriefComments: Dr. digging with BOS @ 50.5 for 3.5 ft. of face. 4' steps of low TE due booster delay
ExtendedComments: Dr. digging with BOS @ 50.5 for 3.5 ft. of face. The dredge had low travel and TE due to delays on the fill site for adding shore pipe and welding the Front Door liner of the Booster Jessie. The dredge is swing a 500' cut and taking 4' steps in each toe. In the evening the dredge got into siltier material letting it run further down the beach. Dredge pumping with an avg. Velocity of 15.5 and a Density of 1.16

BriefComments: Several delays due to fill site adding shore pipe. BOS @ 50.5 for aprox. 3 ft of face.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued to dig in Cut 2 trying to advance as much a possible to tie in of our last cut. We have seen a steady decline in our production the last couple days. We plan to take out 4 pieces of submerged pipe Sunday morning and moving the dredge in Cut 4 digging outbound. We believe a shorter line will help the dredge's production. Dredge is digging with a velocity of 15.8 and a average density of 1.1.

BriefComments: Stiff material and rock causing low production. Welded hole in Dr clean out for 6.9
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued to dig in Cut 4 headed oubound in the Delaware River. Dredge is stuggling with material in this cut. We have run into some stiff clay and rock in this section and with the cutter screen the dredge is experienceing cavitation of the UWP. At 20:00 the dredge shifted forward 100 ft. in the cut. We continued to run into stiff material after the move. Dredge dug with BOS at 50.0 for 3 ft. of face. We had to weld on the cleanout box 2 times for at total of 6.9 hrs.

BriefComments: BOS @ 51 Inconsistent material across swing some clay and rocks.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued to dig in Cut 3 because we are volume limited with the material in the borrow area. The material was inconsistant throughout the cut and the dredge did run into some clay.We incurred a delay for welding on the liner of the dredge MP and spud issues as well. We are digging with BOS @ 51 with lower face of 2.5 ft. Average Velocity is16.7 with a density of 1.07. We expect the material to contue to get better as we work our way down the cut.

BriefComments: The dredge began digging at 11:11 with BOS @ 50.5 ft taking 4 ft steps.
ExtendedComments: The Cutter was replaced at first light. The new cutter head has a screen with a tighter fit against the wall to prevent rocks from reaching the beach. The booster pump engine shut off as the dredge was starting up. Mechanics believe that the problem is caused by the check valves and they will be replaced in the coming days as the parts arrive. Density: 1.05 Swing Speed: 55 ftmin Velocity: 21.1 ftsec.

BriefComments: Dredge Illinois is digging downstream in Cut 3 with BOS @ 51' taking 4' steps in corners
ExtendedComments: The dredge moved into an area with a lot of clay the clay was clogging up the cutter and hurting production. In an effort to move out of the clay get better production and find more favorable material the dredge moved farther into the channel by ~40 ft. CYWH while the dredge was digging clay was 687 CYWH after the dredge moved at 15:55 was 813. The booster received new check valves for the pump engine and the old ones were replaced at 11:35. Velocity: 14.9 Average Density: 1.1 Swing Speed: 61

BriefComments: The dredge continued its modified cut from yesterday with BOS@51' taking 4' steps
ExtendedComments: The dredge is still digging in the borrow area 100 feet short to port and 80 feet past to STBD with the spud 40 feet off center cut line. This allows enough room for traffic so the dredge does not have to move for every vessel. The dredge advanced 210 feet. On the beach the crew fitted shorepipe 6 times for a total of 12 pipe and advanced 480 feet. Velocity: 15.5 Density: 1.11 Swing Speed: 67

BriefComments: The dredge has moved back to cut 3 after moving to the center of the channel on 126
ExtendedComments: The material in the cut has moved from mostly clay back to mostly medium and fine sand and production reflects that up from 767 CYWH on Sunday to 1002 and 1011 CYWH yesterday and today. We expect this production to increase as we progress further down the cut into areas with higher face. BOS is at 51' taking 4 foot steps in the corners. Velocity: 15.5 Density: 1.13 Swing Speed: 70.

BriefComments: The Illinois is continuing to dig downstream in cut 3 BOS 51' taking 3' steps
ExtendedComments: The material is loading up the pipe so the dredge is taking smaller steps in the corners to avoid over loading. Production is down and the leverman believe it is because the material is getting heavier in the area. Welding was done on the main pump on the booster Jessie after wear to the liner was found. The cutter on was changed while welding to the booster was being done.

BriefComments: Dredge digging downstream in Cut 3 BOS 50.5' taking 3-4' steps.
ExtendedComments: The Illinois continues to experiene heavy material on this long line. To avoid overloading attempts were made yesterday to help; adjusting the ladder and swing speed but no positive results. Site management is discussing a plan to move The Booster Jessie approximely 5000' closer to the beach tomorrow. This move is atleast 1.5 days delay time. Velocity: 15.8 Density: 1.07 Swing Speed: 50.

BriefComments: Dredge still experiencing heavy material in cut. BOS 50.5' taking 3' steps
ExtendedComments: It was decided the booster Reggie will be brought in and placed between the booster Jessie and the beach. Today the booster Jessie will undergo a pump job after wear was found yesterday. While the pump job is being preformed crews will begin to prepare the submerged pipe between the beach and the Jessie for the booster Reggie to be installed. Velocity: 15.4 Average Density: 1.06 Swing Speed: 69

BriefComments: The dredge is continuing to dig downstream in cut 3.
ExtendedComments: We have approximately 150 feet left in this cut the dredge will then move over to the green side of the channel and continue to dig outbound. This move should take place tomorrow morning. The dredge picked the ladder up 1.5' after surveys showed overdigging. Velocity: 17.1 fts Density: 1.11 Swing Speed : 83 ftmin

BriefComments: The dredge is continuing to dig downstream in cut 3. BOS @ 49' taking 4' steps
ExtendedComments: The dredge traveled 291 feet yesterday and this morning reached the end of the cut. There dredge will moved outside the cut to what was previously known as option 2 in the borrow area. Durring this delay welding will be done on the booster Jessie and the fill site will add shore pipe. Afer the move dredge will then continue to dig downstream until it reached the limit of the float hose before setting back. Velocity :17.4 Density: 1.11 Swing Speed: 73

BriefComments: The dredge is continues to dig down stream. BOS @ 50ft. Taking 5ft steps.
ExtendedComments: The Illinois reached the end of cut 3 in the morning and shifted to the green side inside of the borrow area. Material is favorable in this location creating high production and travel. She is digging 13 of the channel from range 545 to 780. Because of the dredge location in the channel she needs to move out of the way for all traffic. During traffic delays the fill site is adding shore pipe to reduce down time. Velocity: 17.4. Density: 1.19. Swing speed: 98

BriefComments: The dredge continues to dig down stream in the modified cut on the green sidechannel.
ExtendedComments: Material continues to be favorable allowing the dredge to swing faster and to take bigger steps. The dredge met the end of the hose limit this morning and is moving back to station 251+500 to continue digging this modified cut. While moving welding will be done on a pin hole in the liner on the Booster Jessie.

BriefComments: The dredge then moved back to STA 251+967 and continued digging downstream on channel.
ExtendedComments: The Illinois reached the rubber hose limit while digging the modified cut in the morning reaching a final station of 254+226. As a result of heavy traffic and low face production dropped considerably. The dredge took fuel yesterday while waiting for traffic. Additionally the fill site had a down time of 3.55 hrs after blowout on the line.

BriefComments: The dredge continues to dig down stream in the modified cut on side of channel.
ExtendedComments: The material continues to be favorable. TE below estimate due to traffic delays. As we move down to cut face increased resulting in higher digwh.

BriefComments: The dredge continued digging down stream in the modified cut with a travel of 182ft
ExtendedComments: Digging operations were suspended due to two major delays: adjustments on the Booster Reggie (By pass) heavy traffic with minor delay factors increasing percentage on TE. As of now final detail of production will be completed with the assistance of Booster Jessie.

BriefComments: Digging operations concluded for the Dredge Illinois at approximately 21:00 hrs 1222.
ExtendedComments: She stopped digging on station 253+046 in the Modified Cut. A CND survey will be conducted by T.I. Coastal later today in order to provide more accurate data.

BriefComments: Dredge Illiniois began digging in cut IL-18 at 1259.
ExtendedComments: Dredge IL is digging NW in cut IL-18 and taking 5' steps in both corners. The cutter BOS is at 56' NAVD wtih a 275' cut width.Engineers calibrated the ladder depth velocity guage and density meter.We are using the sand cutter with a new cone screen and mouth piece.The dredge will continue this cut until it runs out of slack line on float hose then move to cut IL-17.The dredge was down for delays for a total of 5.27 hours.Primary delays include an oil line leak in the Engine Room. Bstr Jack at 7000ft.

BriefComments: Dredge Illinois continues digging in cut IL-18
ExtendedComments: Dredge IL is digging NW in cut IL-18 and fluxuating between 3' and 5' steps in both corners.The dredge will continue this cut until it runs out of slack line on float hose then move to cut IL-18.The dredge was down for delays for a total of 10.09 hours.Primary delays include fill site not being able to keep up adding shore pipe and moving anchors.The teeth on the cutterhead were changed. Pumping through bstr Jack at 7000ft.

BriefComments: IL continues digging in Cut IL-18.BOS raised to 54'
ExtendedComments: Due to the dense fog and the inability to determine the amount of slack on the float hose the IL intended to shift to the Cut IL-17. But due to low visibility and malfunctioning guages the DR couldn't see the surge tanks. This delay lasted 5.12 hours.Post dredge hydro surveys revealed the Illinois was overdigging. The Leverman was contacted and raised the ladder so BOS is 54'.The Illinois was running off predicted tides and will be switched tide guage first thing tomorrow. Pumping through bstr Jack at 7000

BriefComments: SL leak at riser connection. IL finishes cut IL-18 and sets up to begin 63cut IL-17.
ExtendedComments: The IL shut down yesterday afternoon for due to a leak where the subline connects with the riser.The bull gang removed the 500 piece of SL and reset the line.While the Riser connection was being repaired the IL moved to the beginning of cut IL-17.When the IL went to start back up at 23:50 the booster had an electrical short betweenthe generator and the circuit board. Pumping through bstr Jack at 7000ft

BriefComments: Started Cut IL-17.Dredge BOS lowered to 55'.Starter changed on Booster Jack.
ExtendedComments: The dredge began digging in cut IL-17 at 10:59 after the booster's starter was swapped out.The IL pumped continuously for the remainder of the day with the exception of two delays totaling 0.75 hours.The dredge BOS was lowered down to to 55'.Dredge is taking 3'-5' steps. Pumping through bstr Jack at 7000ft

BriefComments: Digging in Cut IL-17.BOS 55'.Main Pump Leak - 0.55 hour delay.
ExtendedComments: The dredge is taking steps in each corner 3'-5' each.All delays for the day total 3.72 hrs.A leak on the back door liner bolt of the main pump caused a delay of 0.55 hrs.A new gasket was put on and bolt was tightened.Moving achors (x3) caused a delay of 1.75 hours. Jack rpm: 325 JackSuction: 82 JackDisch: 185.

After DR had been moved and was in position to start digging in cut IL-16 eight teeth were changed on the cutter head. The dredge resumed digging at 1643. In both dig areas the dredge was digging low face (7.5ft average dig face); single swinging the bottom pass BOS @ 55' taking 5ft steps in each corner. Vel: 17.5 Den: 1.21 CS: 29 SS: 66. Jack rpm: 271 JackSuction: 62 JackDisch: 133.

ExtendedComments: DR dug in cut IL-15. Average face around 6.5ft. BOS @ 56' single swinging and taking 5' steps. Major delays for the day included shifting anchors (x3) due to our good travel of 607ft and waiting on the booster water pump to start back up after experiencing issues. While DR down to move anchors at 0906 until 0948 the ladder was greased and the line was washed out. Time efficiency for the day continues to be high at 85%. Due to the heavy material swing speed has decreased to 55 ftmin. The major delays for the day include welding on a patch on the subline-discharge side of Booster Jack (near the riser) to fix a leak and shifting anchors.The time efficiency for the day continues to be reletively high at 73%

BriefComments: Remains digging in cut IL-15 with BOS @ 56'. Reduced velocity. TE=88%
ExtendedComments: The dredge continued digging in cut IL-15 from STA 50+21 to 53+92.The material that the IL is currenlty encountering is heavy.This combined with the length of the line is resulting in a slower swing speed and a reduced velocity.Both the dredge and booster are maxing out their rack %. The leverman has been forced to keep the density under 1.25 to avoid plugging the line. Three cutter teeth changed.

BriefComments: Change to cut IL-10 for finer material.BOS @ 56'.
ExtendedComments: IL began day digging in cut IL-15 with low face single swinging and BOS at 56'.Since the beach was only getting 34 of pipe with the DR and booster maxing out their rack % it was decided to switch to cut IL-10 in search of finer material for the remainder of the N end of UT.While in cut IL-15 the digWH was 810 cyWH.After switching into cut IL-10the digWH went up to 2342 cyWH.The IL and booster rack % are no longer maxed out.

BriefComments: Continued digging in cut IL-10. Fine material.Cutter BOS lowered to 57'
ExtendedComments: The IL dug all day in Cut IL-10 traveling from STA 39+21 to 44+37. Afternoon surveys of Cut IL-10 revealed a considerable amount of material is still being left behind in this cut (roughly 2'-3' above BOS) despite thte cutter BOS being at 56'.As a result the ladder was lowered one foot to cutter BOS at 57' and will be carefully monitored.The IL recieved 95370 gallons of fuel.The delays for the day include shifting anchors (x2) briefly stopping to allow the crane to make some lifts and cleaning

BriefComments: Dredge shut down and towed to Cape May to replace a bearing on stbd side of cutter motor.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge digging in Cut 1. Delay for moving anchors and dump. Telemetry fixed.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 1 single pass at 57'. Removing ~9' of face. Increasing face on the port side. Plan to move to Cut 2 before weather arrives. Material noted as stacking well on the beach. Mainly medium sand and some fines. Cutter amps spiking. Delay to move anchors and move ahead on the dump. Misc delay to wash line. Wire delay continued from previous day. Booster Reggie; 331 RPM 122 IN 266 OUT. Booster Jack; 325 RPM 114 IN 211 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Continued digging in Cut 1 move to Cut 2 at 13:35. Down 19:35 for Jack thrust bearing.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 1 then moved to Cut 2 ahead of the weather and to avaoid finishing Cut 1 at midnight and not be able to move until morning. Dredge went down at 19:35 due to the Jack's thrust bearing needing replacement. Decreased production due to digging into Cut 2 and not removing enough face at the end of Cut 1. Swing speeds might need to be decreased on the roll swing. Booster Reggie; 329 RPM 120 IN 234 OUT. Booster Jack; 328 RPM 108 IN 180 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge began in Cut 2 pumping thru Jack. Major delay for stbd breast anchor line.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 2 single pass at 57'. Trying to keep densities around 1.2. Densities spiked when a swell drove the cutter too far into the bank. Luckily while the dredge was pumping water the Booster needed to repack their pump (2.92hs). Other delay for continued weather delay (4.25hrs) and a tangled float hosefloat hose anchors (3.08hrs) a broken stbd breast anchor (6.75hrs). Booster Reggie: 314 RPM 113 IN 193 OUT; Booster Jack: 105 THRU.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge continued in Cut 2. Jack removed from line 13:00. Down for weather at 18:00.
ExtendedComments: Dredge dug in Cut 2 for 7.66hrs until the Jack was removed from the line. Pipe connection was unable to be made due to the RL encountering rough seas on tow. TE of 78% improved total dig to slightly above estimate while the DigWH suffered due to a now solved tide issue. Densities held around 1.1-1.25 with velocity at 14-15fps. Booster Reggie: 338 RPM 161 IN 312 OUT; Booster Jack: 167 THRU.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge digging Cut 2. Dense material port corner. Misc delay to wash lineair valve.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 2. Shell was noted in the log on the port corner. Densities would spike in the port and leverman had to wash the line twice to regain 14fps velocity. Leverman slowed swings down to attempt to maintain velocity and travel suffered. Planning to move to 'contingency' cuts where material is lighter and face is even across the cut. Booster Reggie: 335 RPM 144 IN 287 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dig in Cut 2 in AM move to Cut 2A @ 0745. Dig finer mat'l; incr. densityvelocity
ExtendedComments: The dredge Illinois continued to dig in Cut 2 between the hours of 0000 and 0745 before switching to Cut 2A and resuming operations at 1200.The switch to Cut 2A was made to have the dredge dig finer material in hopes of increasing line density and velocity and increasing overall production. Booster Reggie: 338 RPM 151 IN 299 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dig in Cut 2A; weather delayed breast wire repair; prod. increased from cut 2.
ExtendedComments: The dredge continues to dig in cut 2A where finer material continues to produce a greater digWH than seen in cut 2. The limiting factor on digging continues to be maintaining densities at 1.2 due to the long line length with only one booster. Weather is forecasted to pick up in the next few days with seas becoming 3-5ft and winds 15-20kt. Booster Reggie: 342 RPM 150 IN 295 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 2A. Avg. 6' of face avg. density 1.2avg vel of 15 ftsec
ExtendedComments: The dredge Illinois continued digging North in Cut 2A between Sta. 38+25 and 43+00.The dredge was able to travel 475 feet on this day while maintaining BOS @ 57'.High production on this day due to few delays and finer material is being pumped causing velocity to increase over past days. Swing speed was decreased to ~70 fpm down from ~85 fpm also causing increased line densityproduction.Approx. 400 feet remain in Cut 2A before dredge will shift West to Cut 1A.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Another great TE day. Cont to dig in Cut 2A w constant ~6.5' of face. 120' togo in 2A
ExtendedComments: The material in the contingency cut remains lighter than seen in cut 2 with an average velocity of 14 fps with a target density of 1.2 swing speed of 70 fpm.Approximately 120 feet of travel remain in cut 2A before switching over to Cut 1A starting at Sta 34+00.Anticipating low to no material change between cuts.Will try to dig to a density of 1.25 in 1A and determine how it affects velocity.Will keep swing speed around 70 fpm.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Finish digging in Cut 2A start in Cut 1A @ 1030. Misc dly: Wash lineslow velocity
ExtendedComments: The dredge Illinois finished digging in Cut 2A at 0620 reaching Sta. 48+59 before shifting to Cut 1A starting at Sta. 34+00 and digging North in the borrow area.Low production between Sta. 34+00 to 35+00 due to cut overlapbank left behind when digging in Cut 1 on March 14.Few minormiscellaneous delays to wash out the line due to velocity drops caused from loading pipe with densities between 1.25 and 1.3. No close bore-holes in Cut 1A but material digging similar as Cut 2A possibly finer

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Cont. to dig Cut 1A. No major delays. Hard mat'lcutter lim'td avg dens. 1.15
ExtendedComments: The dredge Illinois continued to dig in Cut 1A between Sta. 36+47 and 42+50 heading North.No major delays on this day.The material in became while travelilng in Cut 1A became more compact as the sand became more fine in composition casuing the cutter amps to frequently spike while digging. Leverman having having a hard time mataining densities >1.2 in the pipeline but average velocity was 14.5 ftsec. Minor delays to move anchors check screen and wait on boosterengine room.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Cont. do dig Cut 2A less travel due to increas. dig face. Mjr dly: fuel leak
ExtendedComments: The dredge Illinois continued to dig in Cut 2A between Sta. 42+50to 45+62 digging North.There was less travel on this day due to the water becoming more shallow causing increasing dig face and slower swing speeds.The material seems to have changed to a more medium sand that is easier to pump and at times the dredge is pump limited instead of cutter limited no frequent spikes in cutter amps.Major delay: fuel leak in engine room; minor delays: move anchors and checkgrease cutterhead

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge cont'd in Cut 1A. Misc delay to wash 780' of line from Cape May. Good TE.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued in Cut 1A and is expected to move to Cut 7 when the float hose limit is reached. Dredge has been successful at pumping the finer materials however decreasing face near the end of the cut has limited the production slightly. Misc. delay was to wash a section of subline from Cape May that was clogged with sand. Other delays for moving anchors and an air valve on the Reggie. Booster Reggie: 343 RPM153 IN 306 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Changed from Cut 1A to 7. Delay 5.08hrs. Material mostly hard packed fine sand.
ExtendedComments: Dredge finished digging in Cut 1A and moved to Cut 7 after reaching float hose limit. Velocities held around 14.2 with a density of 1.13 - 1.2. Material expected in Cut 7 is similar to that of Cut 1A and 2A. Mostly dense fines with medium sand some shell possible. Pipeline delay due to a pontoon pipe gasket and float hose connection leak. Misc delay to was line (0.91hrs) 5.08 hrs to change cuts. Booster Reggie: 343 RPM 153 IN 306 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge continued in Cut 7. High WH and TE. Misc delay for unloading crane barge 1.25hrs.
ExtendedComments: Dredge digging in Cut 7. Material was mostly dense fines with 30-40% medium sand. Leverman were controlling the velocitydensity by slowing down the swing speeds when the velocity began to drop. Avg velocity was 13.3 and densities ranged from 1.12 - 1.20. Good day of high TE. Cutter screen was checked 3x with no MEC reported. Misc delay to unload crane barge and wash the line. Booster Reggie: 343 RPM 157 IN 311 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge moved from Cut 7 to 8. Pea gravel in last stations of Cut 7. Engine delay 4.25hrs.
ExtendedComments: Dredge moved from Cut 7 to 8 to avoid having to move in rough weather. Started up in Cut 8 at 15:35 then went down for engine room problems with airlinesclutch. Cutter screen was checked 2x with no MEC reported. Pea gravel was reported in latter stations of Cut 7. Ladder was picked up to 57' at 42+71. Planning to move to higher face cuts upon the Jack's return. Avg velocity 13.1 densities 1.1-1.17. Booster Reggie: 343 RPM 148 IN 299 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge in Cut 8. Heavier material. Decreased available face. Misc delay to wash line.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued in Cut 8. In an attempt to maintain density the ladder was raised to 57' at 40+50. Material is spotty with pockets of dense fines bogging down the cutter. Large swells have also caused spikes in the cutter amps. Screen was checked 2x with no MEC reported. Wire delay to adjust port swing friction 2x. Misc. delay to wash line and regain velocity. Booster Reggie: 343 RPM 152 IN 306 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge in Cut 8. Weather delay assoc with stern rubber line. Misc delay to wash line.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued to dig in Cut 8 with BOS at 58.5' in an attempt to pull in additional material. Dig pattern was adjusted as needed by the leverman as far at set size and when to double swing to try to keep velocities up and density under 1.25. When the cutter was checked it was noted that 2 vanes had cracks. At 13:55 the stern rubber connection blew out and the weather was too rough to initiate repairs. Booster Reggie: 343 RPM 155 IN 308 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Tow out to borrow area @ 06:40 resume dig in Cut 9 Sta. 30+00 @ 12:05

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Cont dig in Cut 9; misc delay due to washing linelow velocity; target den 1.2.

Large swells continued out of the East through the day making it difficult to keep a steady line density. Booster Reggie: 344 RPM; 154 IN; 307 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR

Booster Reggie:RPM 341; IN 137; OUT 278.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Remain in Cut 2 low prod. due to seasground swells.15.5 hrs of weather delay

Only other delays were to shift anchors while digging.Both boosters are running at full RPM average velocity ~16 ftsec avereage density 1.21.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge continued in Cut 2. High bank in Port side. MediumCoarse sand some gravl

Booster Reggie: 326 RPM 132 IN 273 OUT. Booster Jack: Running at full RPM.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge continued in Cut 2. Switch from 1 pass to 2 back to 1. Cutter limited from seas

Dredge switched back to single pass due to high seas causing excessive cutter amp spikes. Leverman was double swinging when necessary. Material remained mostly medium sand with some coarsegravel. Booster Reggie: 340 RPM 120 IN 250 OUT; Booster Jack: 330 RPM 125 IN 220 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge continued in Cut 2. Went down for hole in subline at 11:30.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 2. Taking one pass single and double swinging at 58.5'. Dredge is leaving arounf 54.5'. Some bank falling in behind the cutter but is picked on the second swing. Dredge went down to repair a leaking float hose connection and a subline leak was detected. Dredge down for repairs to subline at 11:30. Booster Reggie: 341 RPM 111 IN 260 OUT; Booster Jack: 324 RPM 109 IN 212 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Subline repaired. Dredge resumed digging in Cut 2 with one pass at 58.5'.
ExtendedComments: Dredge cont'd digging in Cut 2 at 13:15. Decreased prodcution in early stations was due to the dredge digging back into the cut. Leverman double swinging at 58.5 once the high face was encountered. 15' of available dig face across cut. At 22:50 the dredge went down for a blown turbo. Other delay was for slow engine speeds and moving anchors. Booster Reggie: 322 RPM 131 IN 274 OUT; Booster Jack: 304 RPM 128 IN 218 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Tow to borrow area continue in Cut 2. 150' of overlap when starting up. Dly: STBD wire
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois towed to borrow area after weatherturbo repair delay and resumed digging at Sta. 20+50 at 12:45.Minor delays to put new eye on STBD swing wirebreast anchor.First 150' of digging were overlap due to high banksettlement during weather delay; bank as high as 20' in some areas on center-line but decrease to 13' on STBD side.Continue to dig only 1 pass BOS & 58-58.5'.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 2 avg. 14' of face mat'l running from sidesfront of cutter.
ExtendedComments: The dredge Illinois continued to dig in Cut 2 between Sta. 18+40 and 16+59 with face up to 15 feet.Continue to make only 1 pass with BOS at 58-58.5' while material is running into cutterhead from in front of and approx. 50' in both corners.Leverman taking 1-2' steps in each corner and occassionally double swing while able to maintain densities of 1.3. Delays: Repacking main pump on booster Jack main engine tripped shifting anchors.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Resumed digging after weather delay; large swells caused decreased production.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois resumed diggingWest in cut 2 at 16:00 hrs. Misc 0.25 hr delay due to washing out line 2.50 hr delay due to fixing rubber line 0.33 hr delay due to engine trip out. Seas of 4-6' continue to cause decreased production and weather forecast predicts similair conditions for the next few days. Digging only 1 pass with significant material running in from cut 3.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dig in Cut 2 until 07:15 before shut down for weather swells hindering production
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued digging in Cut 2 until 07:15 when 5-6 foot ground swells caused the dredge to stop operations.Swells continue to hinder production digging at 58' and keeping cutterhead on bottom without tripping cutter motorMaterial continues to run in front of cutter and approx. 50 feet on the Port side in Cut 3.Reggie: 343 RPM 124 PSI intake 273 PSI disch; Jack: 328 RPM 124 PSI intake 230 PSI disch.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge continued in Cut 2. Digging one pass at 58.5'. 3.33 hrs delay for high seas.
ExtendedComments: Production was decreased in the first few hours of digging due to the dredge pulling back in the cut for rough weather. Dredge digging 14' of face with additional material running in from adjacent cut. Leverman is double swinging to try and maintain a 1.2 without the velocity dropping off. Sets are closer to 2' if at all. Wire delay associated with the stbd breast brake and eye bolt. Booster Reggie: 339 RPM 123 IN 267 OUT; Booster Jack: 332 RPM 116 IN 225 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge in Cut 2. Booster delay for oil line leak and air valve (2.84hrs). Good TE.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 2. Double swinging when needed with the BOS at 58.5'. Average density above 1.20 with velocities 13-17fps. High bank is falling into cutter from port side. Material has improved since moving past the cap of heavier sand. Booster delay for oil line leak (1.92hrs) and air valve (.92hrs). Engine room delay for starboard rotor seal. Booster Reggie: 342 RPM 134 IN 284 OUT; Booster Jack: 317 RPM 135 IN 234 OUT

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge moved from Cut 2 to 3. Delay 4.92hrs. Decreased face increased travel. 1 pass 58.5'
ExtendedComments: Dredge moved from Cut 2 to Cut 3 to coincide with a delay to move valves on the beach. Dredge digging one pass at 58.5' setting ahead in each corner 3'. Cut was moved 50' SE to prevent daylighting the cutter when digging in the starboard corner. Other delay for checking cutter (2x no MEC reported) and moving anchors. Booster Reggie: 342 RPM 135 IN 283 OUT; Booster Jack: 329 RPM 133 IN 238 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Digging into shoal heavy material. Delay for Jack (.83hrs) Reggie (2.00hrs).

Dig pattern was kept at one pass in an attempt to mix good and bad material from the cap of shellgravel with the fines below. Delay for Jack was for a hole in an air tank Reggie delay was for the starter. Misc delay was to wash the line when moving ahead. No MEC reported. Booster Reggie: 341 RPM 137 IN 283 OUT; Jack: 332 RPM 133 IN 238 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Heavy material. Delays pump H2Omove (7.67hrs). Booster Jack leak (1.42hrs).
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued to encounter heavy material and gravelshell hash. Multiple delays to wash line and move dredge. Cut width was reduced to avoid poor material port side. Dredge moved ahead ~1000' and slide closer to Cut 2. MEC was reported on the dump and cutter screen was confirmed intact. Booster delay for water leak on the Jack. Booster Reggie: 339 RPM 134 IN 273 OUT; Booster Jack: 329 RPM 126 IN 255 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge in Cut 2. Delay for Booster (1.08hrs) Move dredge (1.83hrs). Improved material.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued to struggle with heavy material in Cut 3. Dredge was moved into Cut 2 and production increased dramatically. Delay for Booster Jack was for pump packing (1.08hrs). Misc delay was to wash line before moving cuts and clear gravel from the line. Material is noted as stacking well on the beach. Booster Reggie: 340 RPM 131 IN 275 OUT; Booster Jack: 330 RPM 130 IN 234 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge in Cut 2. Great TE day. Material has greatly improved. Eng Room delay - pump packing.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 2. Material as remained consistently good. Minimal loss reported by the beach. Velocities occasionally drop off when additional bank falls into the cutter. Leverman has been double swinging when necessary to bring velocities back up and to maintain densities. Engine room delay for pmp packing. Misc delay to wash line. Booster Reggie: 341 RPM 136 IN 287 OUT; Booster Jack: 335 RPM 135 IN 246 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge digging in Cut 2. Engine room delay (2.5hrs) Wash line (.92hrs).
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 2. Approximately 16' of available dig face. Dredge has been leaving 54' taking one pass at 58.5'. Engine Room delay was continued from yesterday. Misc delay was to wash the line and delays for slowing when the fuel barge was ties alongside. Booster Reggie: 341 RPM 134 IN 280 OUT; Booster Jack: 333 RPM 133 IN 240 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge digging in Cut 4 after 2000' of subline removed. Heavy material.
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued digging in Cut 2 until subline removal began at 8:00. Subline work finished at 14:30 and the dredge was moved the the start of Cut 4 station 5+25. Misc delay was to wash the line from heavy material encountered and to maintain velocity. Material is falling in to the cutter and skewing the dig face due to the volume and area reported. Booster Reggie: 336 RPM 141 IN 280 OUT; Booster Jack: 333 RPM 131 IN 236 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Switch to 2 pass 51'58'. Heavy on top. Wash line 7x (4.26hrs). Surge tank 2.67hrs.

Material was heavier on the first pass and as a result the dredge washed out 7x (4.26hrs). Bank had been falling into the cut from all sides. Booster Reggie: 342 RPM 160 IN 308 OUT; Booster Jack: 338 RPM 149 IN 258 OUT.

ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Dredge moved from Cut 4 to 12. Production increase of 250WH. Lighter material.

At 18:30 the OPC hub went down and leverman lost telemetry screens. Survey responded ASAP but still resulted in 2.00hrs delay. Other misc delay was to wash line of heavy material (1.67hrs).
