ProjectName: BARNEGAT INLT.TO LITTLE EGG - BEACH RENR
BriefComments: Finish digging @1300 while digging in Cut 11. Begin demob process
ExtendedComments: The dredge Illinois finished digging at 13:00 after reaching Sta. 30+01 in Cut 11 and washed out for 4 hours to ensure all material was removed from subline.Low digpay ratio due to losing a lot of material on the beach caused by pumping directly into the slopes in order to pass the final station of the project; beach has no taper.Reduced production caused by ~5 feet of dig face combined with 3-4 foot sea conditions.Begin demob process (subjob 029).

BriefComments: Dr. Ill. continued digging entrance channel.IIF from 0700-1300.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois continued digging the entrance channel to the Delaware City Refinery.@0700 the job was shut down for the IIF meeting.The dredge got back to work at 1300 after the IIF meeting.The dredge was delayed for the IIF meeting (6.0 hrs) move anchors 5x (4.84) and for traffic 2x (3.66 hrs).@ STA 134+70 after seeing the survey the ladder was raised to 30' and leverman instructed to take 6' steps.This should minimize the overdigging.

BriefComments: Dredge continued digging entrance channel.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois continued digging the entrance channel.Surveys showed we were not clearing the toes so we pulled back and dug cleanup and the adjusted our dig pattern to a 15' box cut and 30' dig contour.Delays to change STBD swing wire (2.25 hrs) add 1500' subline (2.25 hrs) traffic 3x (4.5 hrs) shift anchors 5x (4.25 hrs) and move dredge to survey the toe 2x (2.42 hrs).The first survey delay was to see how far back to move the second was to see how the clean up was doing.

BriefComments: Dredge continued digging Delaware City Refinery Entrance Channel.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois continued digging the entrance channel to the Delaware City Refinery.The dredge made good progress during the day.The dredge was delayed to calibrate the density guage (survey delay) (0.33 hrs) move out of the channel for traffic 2x (3.42 hrs) add 3-780's of subline (2.67 hrs) shift anchors 6x (4.75 hrs) and wash out the line to add pipe (0.50 hrs).

BriefComments: Dr. covered STA 10904-10054 Main delay wires 2x (4hrs).
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois continued digging the Delaware City Refinery Entrance Channel from STA 109+04-100+54 BOS @ 29.5'.Late afternoon surveys showed over digging on the toes so the dig instructions were adjusted and leverman instructed to swing 5' less into each corner.Main delays for traffic 3x(4.33 hrs) move anchors 4x (2.41 hrs) Engine Room fuel leak (0.42 hrs) re-spool port breast wire (2.67 hrs) and change port swing wire (1.33 hrs).

BriefComments: Dr. dug STA 10054-8974.Major delay for traffic 2x (5.59 hrs).
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois continued digging the Delaware City Refinery Entrance Channel from STA 100+54-89+74 BOS @ 29.5'.Digging 10' box cut on green toe and 15' box cut on red toe.Main delays for traffic move anchors R&R air valve on ladder and lift swing wire into rack.During the first traffic delay the crew also changed the port swing wire and can on stbd swing wire.During second traffic delay crew also moved anchors ahead. Prorated pay (not dig)- pay reflects shoaling in channel.

BriefComments: Dr. dug STA 8975- 8140.Major delay for traffic and move anchors.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois dug from midnight to 0440 when it had to move anchors and add an additional 2340' of subline. More delays occurred due to incoming channel traffic which caused the dredge to move anchors and position itself out of the channel. At 1220 the dredge moved out of the channel once again due to channel traffic. From 2105-2150 the dredge reset port swing anchor and then continued to dig for the rest of the day.

BriefComments: Dr. dug STA 8140-7292.Major delay for move anchors.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois dug from station 81+40 - 72+92. CY Dig WH is relatively low compared to previous days due to a reduced swing speed and a lower step as well as a lower cutter suction depth. These changes allowed for the dredge to dig conservatively without leaving material above grade. The CY Dig WH is still above the estimate for the sub job and time efficiency has risen to above 70%. Channel traffic and moving anchors remain the primary delays.

BriefComments: Dr. dug STA 7292- 6512.Major delay for move anchors.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois dug from station 72+92- 65+12. Upon encountering gas the dredge cut back on swing speed and then set size in the high bank to get all the overdepth and clear channel toes. This change hurt the distance traveled along with full moon tides which caused the stern anchor to slip causing inconsistent sets and further slowing travel. An additional 1000' of subline was put in place for the remainder of the project and 7.5 hours of delay was logged for traffic and moving anchors.

BriefComments: Dr. dug STA 6500-5400. Completed dredging at 1815. High digpay due to low face
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois dug from sta 65+00 to the end of the project.The higher digpay is due to low face combined with a narrowing cut as the dredge moved closer to the last station.The dredge completed dredging operations at 18:15 and was pushed outside the channel.Major delays today include traffic for 4.17hrs and moving anchors for 3.58hrs.

BriefComments: Major delay to set ahead to next shoal 2x and clean cutter 3x.
ExtendedComments: We are running into lots of trash and rocks that is getting caught in the cutter and newly added suction mouth bars.Most of the trash is old tires ropes and steel cables.Lever man have been able to step on avg 5-6 ft but must periodically slow down or stop swinging when densities get too high limiting our overall travel rate.With booster inline suction pressure sometimes drops below 0 creating a vacuum but leverman are watching for it and reacting accordingly.

BriefComments: Major delay to set ahead to next shoal 2x and clean booster pump 4x.
ExtendedComments: We continue to encounter trash and rocks that are getting caught in the cutter. We are also stopping frequently to clean the booster pump. Lever man avgs 5-6 ft steps. Velocity average is 23fps through the period lever man is attempting to keep the velocity above 20fps to prevent plugging the pipe. Average swing speed is 71 Fpm and the denisty is averaging around 1.06. The booster is averging 243 RPM and discharge pressure is 113 PSI.

Average swing speed is 83 Fpm and the denisty is averaging around 1.06. The booster is averging 237 RPM and discharge pressure is 111 PSI.

The MP RPM were high in order to drop velocity to desired 18fps leverman will decrease MP PRMS by 20 begining am 926. Lever man avg 4-6 ft steps. Average swing speed 63 Fpm denisty is averaging 1.04. ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois continued digging cut 9.Dredge was delayed for booster 4x traffic 8x to clean the cutter 4x and to move anchors 3x. The dredge was digging to contours that were much narrower than the optimal cut width for the dredge.This resulted in above average travel per WH. The dredge was digging good sand but could not get production very high due to the low face that we are encountering averaging around 1.6 feet.

The miscother delay stopped the dredge so that the fuel barge could come along side. Booster Stats:BP RPM 243 Pressure in 41 Pressure out 88 Impeller 74.

In cut 11 step size was stretched back out to 5'-6' due to better material mostly mudsilt with some sand soft clay and rocks. Cut 11 is narrow and there are jumps between the shoals so dredge had to move anchors more than normal. Booster Stats:BP RPM 250 Pressure in 29 Pressure out 79 Impeller 74.

ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois started up today at 1440 digging outbound in cut 1 with BOS @ 19' and 4' steps in each corner. She used a double swing when encountering more than 8' of face. The first swing was with BOS @ 14' and the second swing BOS @ 19'.

ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued digging outbound in cut 1 to STA 56+70. She traveled 420 ft while continuing to use a double swing in areas with greater than 8' of face. On the first swing the BOS is @ 14' and on the second swing BOS is @ 18'. The total swing width of this cut is 208 ft. The TE was a low 52.42% today mainly due to a 5hr delay on the dump that carried through from yesterday to this morning. Other delays include traffic adding shore pipe and anchors.

The BOS on the fisrt pass is @ 14' and BOS @ 18' for second pass. When she swings a single pass the BOS is @ 19'. Total swing width is 208' (swinging 12' past each toe of cut). TE is at 69% for the day. Longest delay for Generator shutting down. Note when the generator shut off it rest the gyro and the leverman had to wait for it to settle.

ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois started out the day digging outbound in Cut 1. She finished the cut at 03:45 and began to prep and set up for Cut 2. At 09:45 she began digging Cut 2 outbound with BOC @ 18' and a swin width of 208' or to the 14.5' contour. The beginning of cut 2 had low face ~ 4'. As the dredge moved forward the face increase. The BOS was put @ 19 for face > 9' BOS @ 18.5' for face > 6' and BOS @ 17.5' for face < 6'.

ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois began the day digging in Cut 2 @ STA 58+10 with BOS @ 19'. She finished the cut at approx. 14:55 and began prep for Cut 3. The Dredge starting digging in Cut 3 @ 18:00 with BOS @ 18' and a swing width of 208' (12' past each toe). This is the Final cut for the base work (sub 040). The seas are calm to day but bad weather approaches and we expect high seas tomorrow.

ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued digging Cut 3 outbound with BOS @ 18.5 - 19' and a swing width of 208'. She finished digging Cut 3 at 16:20. After finishing the cut she proceeded to move into inlet to protected waters in preperation for hurricane Sandy. While she was digging the only delays she had were for moving anchors X3 (2.34hrs).

ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois started out the day digging inbound in Cut 6. She finished the cut at 19:10. Dredge dug Cut 6 digging inbound with BOS @ 17.5' and a swin width of 255' digging to the 14.25' contour. As face increased cutter was lowered to 18.5'. She began digging Cut 5 inbound with the BOS @ 17.5. The BOS was put @ 18.5 for face > 6' and BOS @ 17.5' for face < 6'. Dredge taking 4' steps.

ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued digging inbound in Cut 5. Digging with the BOS @ 17.5' and a swin width of 255' digging to the 14.25' contour. Dredge taking 4' steps. Dredge encountered a significant amount of trashhurricane debris resulting in the TE of 38%.

BriefComments: Move Dredge Shift anchors 3x Clean cutter and check MP
ExtendedComments: Moved dredge to new cut shift anchors 3x clean cutter and check MP Miscellaneous survey delay. Shallow bank forcing shifting anchors at higher tides.

BriefComments: Electrical breaker repair Fill site y-valves Shift Anchors Clean cutter

Due to the earlier down time for electrical repairs an addiitonal 0.33 hours were spent waiting for the dredge gyro to reset. Total delays for the day: electrical (6.33) dump (3.50) shift anchors (1.67) and clean cutter (0.75). Cut width approx 225 feet. Dredge digging through the material well. Difficulties shifting anchors at lower tides due to shallow water along the channel edge.

BriefComments: Single pass BOS @ 18.5. Delays: Wash out line Clean main pump clean cutter ancho

The high dp is due to the great difference in face of the port and starboard side of the swing. Delays: Clean cutter x4 (3.83hrs);Clean main pump x2 (3.5hrs);Wash out line (3.33hrs);Move Anchors x3 (2.84hrs);Position computer restart (0.33hrs).

Higher cutter amps bc swells. Night lvman swung slower (60-80fpm) than Day shift lvman (70-100 fpm). No surveys performed bc rough seas. Lvman is double swinging. DP: set 0'p5-6' stbd steps. Vel: 21.9 fps. SS: dig 65 roll 80 fpm. Cutter: 30 RPM. Dens: 1.26.

While the Dr was down crew replaced 8 teeth & serviced the ladder. Dump piped shoreline to eastern side of the breach. Lvman is double swinging. DP: set 0p'5-7' stbd crn steps. Vel: 19.5 fps.SS:dig 63bk 72fpm. Dens:1.17

ExtendedComments: Digging southbound in Cut 2 Moriches Inlet. Mtrl caved in from port crn once dr passed Sta 2300 mtlr is falling from both crns but still higher on port side (waves & current action?). Lvmn triple swung sometimes.DP: set 0's4-5'p steps. SS: d 75bk 80 fpm. Vel: 21.1 fps. Dens 1.2sg.

From 1500 lvman was limited to step by stbd breast anchor he could not move bc shallow water he changed dig patt to max mtrl. DP: set 0'4-6's steps mainly. Vel: 20.5fps. SS d 83 bk 90 fpm. Dens: 1.18

Lvrman dble and trple swing to pick up as much material as possible. Digface after survey ~ 10'. DP: Set 4-6' stbd0' p steps. Vel. 18.3fps. SS dig 60bk 80fpm. All plant tranfered from 070

Initailly gravel was reported on the beach but throughout evening gravel turned into rocks 2' in diameter.Cut2 was finished at 2230. Dr. is currently moving into Cut3 to dig inbnd.

BriefComments: Dr. Il dug inbnd Cut3 w delays moving to Cut3 cleaning cutter & anchors.
ExtendedComments: Began digging inbnd in Cut3 @ sta2+90 @ 0850 after being towed from Cut2. Delays were due to moving achrs and to clean cutter. Riser has sprung leak. BOS was lowered to 29'. Gasket was replaced but riser is still leaking. Dr. will cnt. to dig with riser leaking. No rocks have been dug in Cut3 unlike in Cut2.

BriefComments: Dr. Il digging inbnd Cut3. Delays to wash line due to gravel material.
ExtendedComments: Dr. Il continued digging inbnd in Cut3 traveling 560'. Morning delays were due to moving anchors and changeing the bell gasket. Pea size gravel caused the Dr. to go down at 1230. Dr. had to wash out during the afternoon and didn't start up again until 1730. There are two leaks 1 in the riser and the other on the Stbd Connection. Avg. Vel. is low @ 17fps due to material and leaks in the pipeline.

BriefComments: Dr. Il able to dig 350' til swell delayed moving achrs and replacing pipeline
ExtendedComments: Dr. Il cnt. to dig inbnd in Cut3 until late in the afternoon. Dr. could not move achrs due to swell & could not replace section of pipe that needs to be repaired. The line had to be washed several times due to pea gravel.

BriefComments: After pipeline was fixed subjob 080. Dr. began to dig in Cut1 @ 1580 inbnd
ExtendedComments: Dr. Il moved to Cut1 after pipeline had been repaired. Cut one does not have any instatnces of digging pea gravel. Dr. spent majority of the day in subjob 080 for 16.5 hrs. and has dug for a total of 6.25 hrs. and traveled 220' in Cut1.

BriefComments: Dr. Il dug inbnd in Cut1 until finished project at 20+50
ExtendedComments: Dr. Il dug inbnd in Cut1 from 18+34 to 20+50. Dr. finished the project at 1245 and moved inside the Shinnecock Inlet. The miscother delay for 2.92 hours was for washing out the line. Dredge is currently being prepared to move to New Jersey.

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound in access chn.STA 10+00 dropped BOS to 22.5. IIF meeting in am
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued digging inbound in the access channel. At approx. sta 10+00 the BOS was dropped to 22.5' due to increasing face. At 0630 all operations stood by for safety and all the available employees proceeded to attend the IIF meeting. After the meeting the dredge continued digging at 1420. The material is very hard. Combined with high face makes it difficult to swing the ladder accross the cut. The material is running fast on the beach and it is suspected to be running behind the dredge.

BriefComments: Cont. dig inbound access ch. Dropped BOS to 24.5'. 8hr delay for tide to move anchor
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued to dig inbound in the access channel today to STA 13+80. Due to Heavy Fog hydro survey have not been preformed. A lead line was dropped behind the dredge and found a leave depths of 16.5'. After this discovery the BOS was dropped to 24.5' to dig the rest of the access channel. Swing width 275'. Material is undug and thus very hard. Reported that mateial is running on the beach. SSBS: 6070 fps. 8 hr delay to wait on tides to move anchors under Misc delay.

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound to 18+17. BOS @ 23'. BA limits offset 25' more. no mj. delays
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued to dig inbound in Cut 1 making it to sta 18+17. An AM lead line showed that we were leaving about 20.5' so the BOS was picked up to 23'. This depth gave us good production and it was deep enough to keep the cutter buried in the hard material. Surveys showed that the slopes were holding a 1:3 to ensure we do not dig outside of the BA limits the BA dig boundaries were offset an additional 25' for a total of 50' from the CORE supplied BA limit. Only delay were for screen and anchors

BriefComments: Cont. Dig inbound Cut 1. BOS @ 23'. Swing width 275'. Digwkhr = 3103cyhr
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued to dig inbound in Cut 1 with BOS @ 23' and a swing width of 275. She is swinging 50' inset of the BA limits to prevent any digging outside of the limits (assuming material falls on a 1:3 slope). Production is good with the high face (11-13') but material is running on the beach. The driving factor for production in this BA is good TE. The dregde is able to consistantly dig right around 3000 cywkhr. There were no major delays on this day.

BriefComments: Dr. Il cont. digging inbnd in Cut1. @ 1900 BOS dropped to 25' near Sta 26+00
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued to dig inbound in Cut1. The BOS was lowered from 23' to 25'@ 1900 near Sta 26+00 with a swing width of 275'. Delays for the day included moving anchors checking the MEC screen cleaning cutter and greasing cables.

BriefComments: Finished Cut1 & was towed to Access Cut where digging continued.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig inbound in Cut1 with a BOS of 25' and a swing width of 275'. Dr. finished Cut1 at 0935 at Sta 29+25. Dr. was then towed to Access Cut so that it could make way to dig in Cut2. Dr. began digging at 1400 at Sta 3+25. Dr. had to dig down to meet the BOS of 25' due to the high elevation of material. The Dr. had an average swing speed of 82 fpm and is consistently digging just 2800 cywkhr.

BriefComments: Cont. digging Access Cut w BOS @ 25' & SS of 88fpm. Minor delays due to moving achrs.
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging in Access Cut from Sta 5+05 to Sta 8+03. BOS was kept at 25' and an average SS of 88fpm was maintained. Dredge attempted to move to Cut 2 but could not due to tides and prop damage to the Vol. Delays in the afternoon were due to the RL not being able to move anchors during low tide (2.75 hrs under misc delays).

BriefComments: Began digging in Access Channel at 1420 with BOS at 25' and SS of 85fpm
ExtendedComments: Operations cont. at 1420 digging in Access Channel. Dr. was able to travel 139' in 9hrs. Wx calmed down and Dr. was able to begin digging after Misc. delay due to weather that lasted 14.33.

BriefComments: Cont. digging Access Cut with BOS @ 25' and a SS of 88fpm. Delay in PM to wait on tide.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig in Access Cut with a BOS of 25' and SS of 88fpm with an average pump velocity of 16fps. Dredge finished Cut at Sta 12+20 at 1835. Dredge was delayed moving to Access Cut 2 due to the inability to move anchors with the low tide. Misc Delays were due to checking the MEC screen and checking the gear box as well as 5.42 hr delay to wait on tides to move anchors and dredge.

BriefComments: Down for majority of the day began digging in at 1730 w BOS of 26' and SS of 92fpm
ExtendedComments: Dredge was down for the majority of the day to wait on high tide to move to Acces Cut 2 (17.25 hrs in misc delay). Reason for prolonged delay was the projects low draft tugs were off project for repairs. Dredge began digging in Access Cut 2 at 1730 with a BOS of 26' and SS of 92fpm. SW was at 275' and Step Size was at 4.5' STBD corner.

BriefComments: Cont. Digging inbound in Cut 2 . No Mj delays. BOS dropped to 26'. trace of silt in material
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued digging inbound in Cut 2. In the morning the BOS was dropped to 26' to ensure we get all the material we can. Dump is reporting traces of silt in material (as noted in boring logs). No major delays today resulted in good TE and ultimatley good production. TE is the driving factor for production in this BA. LL = 17700' as line is increasing MP is reaching pump limit. DSBS = 7297 fps. Actual Swing width = 287'. travelwh = 15.6'.

BriefComments: Cont. diggin inbound in Cut 2. BOS @ 26'. No major delays. SSBS ~ 5790. Some clay
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued digging inbound in Cut 2 with the BOS @ 26' and a cut width of 275'. No makor delays today allowed the dredge to achieve a TE of 81% which was the driving force behind the good production. Leverman dug with SSBS ~ 5790 fpm and an average density of 1.32. Cutter speed of 30 rpm. Backswing effeciency is 63%. Some clay balls were reported on the beach abt around 13:00 (sta 25+75). The clay material did not last long and digging cont. unchanged. Leaving ~ 19.5' water

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound cut 2. Finished Cut 2 @ 11:40 @ sta 30+29. Move to Cut 3. BOS 26'
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued to dig inbound in Cut 2. She finished cut 2 @ 11:40 @ sta 30+29 when she ran out of float hose. The dredge was then moved to Cut 3 to start diggin inbound at sta 18+40. She began diggin in Cut 3 at 16:15 with BOS @ 26.6' due to high face. DSBS ~ 5690 fps. Swing width of 275'. Avg line density ~ 1.3. Longest delay was 4.58 hours to move to cut 3 other than that no major delays. Good TE continues to drive production.

BriefComments: Cont. digging Cut 3 traveling 376' w BOS @ 26.5' and SSof 70fpm and BS of 91fpm
ExtendedComments: Dredge cont. digginginbound in Cut 3. Dr. has not been completing a full swing to the port side in order to prevent overdigging due to low face in Cut 2. Dr. has been approximately 20' short on port side. BOS was raised to 26' due to muddy material being reported on fill. Delays were due to moving anchors 2x and replacing the Stbd. swing wire.

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound in Cut 3 w BOS @ 26' SS of 79.5fpm and BS of 98.5fpm
ExtendedComments: Dr. dug inbound from Sta. 24+00 to 27+49. Dr. cont. with short swing to Port to avoid the absense of material that is being taken due digging from the previous cut. Dr. had a Misc. Delay of 4 hours waiting for confirmation from USACE of payment for the extra option that had been presented during which time the the line was washed out. The Dr. was also delayed 1.42hrs. due to the fill site 2x for moving the Y-valve.

BriefComments: Dr. began diggin inbound in Cut 4 @ 0330. BOS was @ 25' SS of 61.5fpm & BS of 86.2fpm
ExtendedComments: Dr. began subjob Base 040 at 0330 diggin inbound in Cut 4. The dredge was able to travel a total of 208'. The Dr. lowered BOS TO 25.5' to prevent overdigging the cut. Delays included 4.67 hours to wait on tide to move anchors 3 hours to wait on fill site operations and 1.17 hours to grease and check MEC screen.

BriefComments: Dr. cont. digging inbound in Cut 4 w BOS of 25.5'. Dr. Completed project @ 2050.
ExtendedComments: Dr. dug inbound in Cut 4 w BOS of 25.5' SS of 72.6fpm and BS of 93.9fpm. Dr. was delayed for 1 hour to clean out MP due to excess amounts of sea weed and shell. Shell amounts increased in Cut 4 compared to other areas in dig parameters. Other delays included being down for 5.91 hours due to large swell 1.08 hours to replace gasket under Misc Delays. 0.5 hours to check MEC @ 0700 & 1430. Dr. finished Brigantine Beach @ 2250 and began demobilization.

BriefComments: Dr. cont. to dig inbound in Acc. Cut w BOS of 21' SS of 3500fcywh & BS of 2204cywh
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued to dig inbound in the Access Cut covering 400' of travel. BOS was kept at 21' and material had less amounts of mudsilt than the previous day 70% med sand. Average density of material was 1.21. Dredge is using surge tanks for anchors. Minor delays throughout the day a majority of the delays due to moving pipe and equipement on the Fill Site. Down four times to check MEC under Misc Delays at 0150 0700 1455 and 1905.

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound in Acc Cut w BOS of 21' SS of 4259cywh BS of 2437cywh
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig inbound traveling 470 ft in the Access Cut. Matrial changed to a mixture of fine and med sand. Face has begun to decrease coming to the end of the Access Cut. Delays due to Fill crew preparing beach site with pipe and dredge moving anchors. Dredge had to avoid red buoy with breast anchor which caused minor delays.Misc Delays were due to MEC screen checks at 0010 0730 1400 2240.

BriefComments: Finished digging inbnd in Acc Cut began digging Cut 1 w BOS of 21'. material face dec.
ExtendedComments: Continued digging inbound in Acc Cut until 2000 when the dredge began to dig into Quadrant A Cut 1. The dredge was able to travel 825' due to the decreasing slope of the material. The dredge began digging in the area where shell is obundant. The shell has caused some cavitation in the MP. Delays were due to moving anchors fill site and a Misc Delay to check the MEC screen at 0750 and 1450.

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbound in Cut 1 w BOS of 21' SS of 52fpm and BS of 72fpm
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging in Cut 1 and was able to travel 730' until the float hose ran out. TE was very good at 79% and can be attributed to the low face of the material. Average face of the material towards the end of Cut 1 was 4 to 5' and decreased as the dredge cont. digging inbound. Delays were attributed to moving anchors cleaning the cutter and MP due to deposits of shell. Misc Delays were for checking the MEC at 0130 0410 0920 and 1300. At 1300 the crew performed a MEC drill.

BriefComments: Dr moved to Cut 2 bc ran out slack float hose. Low face mtrl wshells & silt
ExtendedComments: DrIL digging inbound in Cut 1-2 BA-A. Dr moved @0030 to cut 2 bc ran out of slack resuming to dig @ 0250. @0655 dump moved y-vls (pumping w3 lines) meanwhile DrIL moved anchors & checked cutter & MEC screen teeth. Screen checked 4x (0030 0655 1155 & 1725). 2 keeper 1 bossreplacedFace varied as sta decreased; low face affected production. Lman hit some shell & silt. Hard mtrl (higher cutter amps) & MP cavited several times. DP: 1 pass set 5' both crns Vel: 19.6fps SS: dig 55back fpm

BriefComments: Dr moved to Cut 3 bc ran out slack float hose. Still low face shell cont decreased
ExtendedComments: DrIL digging inbound in Cut 2-3 BA-A. The DrIL ran out of slack & she was moved to Cut 3 @ 0605. Cutter cleaned & MEC screens checked 6x (0210 0605 1540 1830 2000 & 2340). @ 2130 down to make a new eye on stbd swing anchor (cable is ~120' shorter). 2000' of subline are expecting from Atl City. Dump pumped on 3 lines N.Low face as sta decreased affected prod. Face 3' higher on stbd crn.Harder mtrl @end of cut 2. DP: 1 pass set 5' both crns. Vel: 18.9fps. SS:55 rollback 105 fpm.

BriefComments: Dr moved to Cut 4. 2000' subline added. Gasket stern cnx changed. Low face
ExtendedComments: DrIL digging inbound in Cut 3 BA-A. @0705 the DrIL was moved to Cut 4 being located in place @ 1100. Also 2000' of subline were laid @ NE of current pos (othmisc dly). Dr resumed digging @1635.@1650 the gasket on stern conn was replaced but she remained down bc rough seas to fix a leak on stern conn. Low face affected prod. Hard mtrl wbroken shells fine & med sand. DP: 1 pass set 6'p4's steps. Vel: 19.2 fps. SS: dig 70 105 fpm

BriefComments: DrIL resumed digging outbound @1020. Low face. MEC checked 2x
ExtendedComments: DrIL digging outbound in Cut 4 BA-A. The DrIL resumed digging @1020. Prior to starting up cutter & MEC screen checked. @1840 down to move anchors & check cutter & MEC screen. High cutter amps after 1945 bc ground swell of the oncoming winter storm caused cutter tripped off. Low face affected prod. All plant transfered from 070. DP: 1 pass set 4-5's5'p steps. Vel: 19.5fps. SS: dig 70 back 130 fpm.

BriefComments: Opts. began at 1220 digging outbnd in Cut 5 with BOS of 21' and a face of 5.5'
ExtendedComments: Dr. began digging at 1220 after Mj Wx delay 071. Dr. is digging outbound in Cut 5 and was able to travel 550'. Note that while digging outbound STA are decreasing. BOS has been kept at 21' and has dug through a consistent face of 4 to 5'. The low face allows for single swing with a SS of 56fpm and a BS if 65fpm. Delays were due to moving anchors for 0.50hrs and a Misc Delay of 0.25hrs to check the MEC screen at 1900.

BriefComments: Finished Cut 5 then moved to 4+50 in Cut 4 to finish after last weeks wx delay
ExtendedComments: Conitnued digging outbnd in Cut 5 starting at STA 6+20 with a BOS of 21' and a SS 52fpm and BS of 63fpm. Dr. completed Cut 5 at 1405 and began to tow into position to Cut 4 BOS dropped to 22'. Cut 4 was not compeleted due to last week's Wx Delay. Dr. began digging outbnd at STA 4+94 and was able to cover 285' before the end of the day. Material has been dense with pockets of shell. Delays due to moving anchors 2.01 hrs towing dredge to Cut 4 3.83hrs. Misc Delays due to checking the MEC.

BriefComments: Cut 4 was completed with BOS of 22'. Dr. moved to Cut 6 digging outbnd with BOS of 22'
ExtendedComments: Dr. cont. digging Cut 4 from STA 2+09 to 0+00. Cut 4 was completed at 0805 then Dr. began to be towed to begin digging Cut 6. Dr. was able to travel 530' in Cut 6. Due to the boundary layout of Cut 6 production was not as successful as previous days. The Dr. was restricted from completeing full swings in the beginning of the cut. The SS was 51fpm and the BS 59fpm. Delays were due to moving anchors and changing cuts. Misc. delays were attributed to checking the MEC screen at 0125 0425 1005 1455 and 1955.

BriefComments: Comp. digging Cut 6 and towed to Cut 7 digging outbnd @ STA 9+35 w BOS @ 22'
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging outbnd in Cut 6 for 500' & finished cut @ 1300 w a SS 48fpm & a BS of 50fpm. Dr. was towed to Cut 7 & began digging outbnd @ 1440 @ STA 9+35. Prod. was not as successful as previous days. The Dr. was restricted from completeing full swings in the beginning of the cut. The ladder was getting stuck on the face due to the restricted angle of the borrow area. The SS 49fpm & the BS 60fpm. Delays were due to moving anchors and changing cuts. Misc Del. were due to checking the MEC at 045 0720 1300 1905 2055

BriefComments: Cont. digging Cut 7 from 5+18 to 1+18 with BOS at 23'. Material predominetly mudsilt
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging outbnd w SS of 42fpm BS of 44fpm & a travel of 400' before going down into subjob 071 Mj Wx Delays @ 1500. Material @ the end of cut 7 was found to be mudsilt. Due to material there was low accumulation of material on the beach. Delays were due to fill site and moving anchors. Misc Delays were due to MEC that was checked at 0455 0745 1530

BriefComments: Began digging inbound Cut 1 @ 10:40. BOS @ 22' Low face. SS ~ 75fpm
ExtendedComments: Dredge was towed out from the harbor at first light. By 10:40 the connection was made and she began digging inbound in Cut 1 with BOS @ 22'. This short Cut had to be dug to complete BA A. These cuts had approx. 4.6' of face which was dug with an avgSS of 75 fpm. Note that Cut 2 material was very dense and casued low production. Primary delays include changing cuts and waiting on the dump.

BriefComments: Low TE. Dump delay x2 (6hrs); Change Cuts (4.83hrs); Change Swing Wire(4.83 hrs) Good DWH
ExtendedComments: Dredge finished Cut 2 @ 01:00. Moved to Cut 15 to dig predicted shell area. Reported that shell was not an issue in the material of this area. Velocity remained high at 19 fps. DWK met estimate at 2558 cyhr but TE was very low and a limiting factor of total quatity moved. Delays included Dump delay x 2 (6hrs); Replaced STRB breast wire (4.83hrs); Change cuts (4.83 hrs); Move anchors (0.83hrs). SSBS = 6980 fps.

BriefComments: Good TE. High face. Delays: Chg cut(2.25hr) Anchors x2(2.25hrs) Dump x2(1.16hrs)
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois began the day digging outbound in Cut 15 with BOS @ 22' using double swing in high face ~ 10' SSBS = 86100 fpm. At 08:25 the dredge shut down and moved to Cut 16 to begin digging outbound with BOS @ 22'. High bank at beginning of cut caused us to start further back. Rest of cut was dug with double swing due to high face ~ 10'+. Cut 16 SSBS = 65100. Good TE. Delays: Change cuts (2.25hrs); Move anchors x 2 (2.25hrs); DUmp x 2 (1.16hrs); Tighten Strd breast friction (0.17hrs).

BriefComments: Good TE. High Face 7-10'. Not as much shell as predicted. Move to Cut 17 (2.75hrs)
ExtendedComments: Dredge Illinois continued digging outbound in Cut 16 with BOS @ 22' and Double swinging. High face @ 7-10'. Not as much shell in material as predicted. Good TE today with minor delays for Changing cut (2.75hrs); Anchors x 3 (1.74hrs); Checking MEC screen x 2 (0.59hrs). SSBS = 7597 fpm. High face has made production satisfactory at 2477 CY WH but has slowed down travel to 32 FTWH. Seas are beginning to pick up.

BriefComments: Good TE. High Face (9-10'). Good MED Sand material. Down for weather at 21:15.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continued to dig outbound in Cut 17 with BOS @ 22' using a double swing method. Still digging in predicted shell area- note that there has been very little shell in the material. Also note that there has been a higher content of Med. Sand reported in this area. Good TE. Delays include Weather (2.75hrs);Move anchors x 3 (1.33hrs);Misc. Delay for checking MEC Screen (0.17 hrs). Dredge went down at 21:15 becasue rough seas have prevented the moving of anchors. SSBS = 6993 fpm

BriefComments: Began digging inbnd in Cut 8 @ 1110 with BOS of 22' and a TE of 88.3%
ExtendedComments: Dr. transitioned from 071 Mj Wx Delay to 045 Base @ 1110. Began digging outbnd in Cut 8 @ sta 17+20. Dr. had to dig down at the beginning of cut causing a decrease in DigWH in compared to the estimate. Material is predominately fine and is having problems building on the beach. Dr. had a SS of 59.5fpm and a BS of 61.9fpm. After Wx Delay Dr. was down to move anchors and check MEC at 1545 & 2020

BriefComments: Cont. digging in Cut 8 finishing at 2045. Fine sand had trouble building on beach.
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging Cut 8 finishing at 2045 @ sta 7+00. BOS was kept at 22' with a SS of 57fpm and a BS of 73.4fpm. Material continued to be predomenately fine sand. Material type was not building up on the beach very well. Dig\Pay was cahnged to 1.16 to account for fine material. Dr. was down to move anchors and to move to Cut 9. Misc Delays were due to MEC at 0810 & 1605.

BriefComments: Began Cut 9 inbound. Very fine sand running off beach = High DP. Engine room delay 3.25hr
ExtendedComments: Dr. began digging Cut 9 & was able to travel 550' in a day. Dr. kept an avg. SS of 56fpm and a BS of 67fpm. Material cont. to be predomately fine sand. Fill site had to extend dikes 400' to keep material from running out of template. Dr. was down early in the day due to main generator running hot repairs were made. MEC was checked at 0001 0230 0950 1635 & 2130.

BriefComments: Cont. dig Cut 9 until 1100. Dr. subline broke when being removed. Very fine material.
ExtendedComments: Dr. cont. digging Cut 9 for 210' until going down @ 0820. Dr. had an avg. SS of 33fpm and a BS of 36fpm. Dr. began to wash out line to remove subline. While removing subline broke and job tansitioned to subjob 081 Mj Mech Delays.

BriefComments: Began digging in Cut 11 @ 1220. Material cont. to be fine & not stack on beach
ExtendedComments: Dr. was towed out of Egg Harbor inlet and transitioned from 071 to 045 at 1220. The dr. skipped cut 10 to 11 in hopes of finding better material. As of now the material has cont. to be very fine in the beginning of the cut. Subline was removed and the riser now sits in cut 13. BOS was kept at 22' in Cut 11 with a SS of 60fpm and BS of 73fpm.

BriefComments: Cont. digging inbnd in Cut 11 w BOS of 23'. Mat. remained fine now stacking on beach.
ExtendedComments: Dr. cont. digging inbnd in Cut 11 traveling 480'. High TE for the day at 87.9%. SS was 63.6fpm & a high BS of 93.8fpm due to running of fine material in the cut. Material remained fine but is now stacking on the beach. Down due to fill (0.58hrs) to move anchors (1.41hr) and check MEC at 07051235 1935. 5 teeth were replaced along with port breast wire.

BriefComments: Cont. dig inbnd in Cut 11. Dr.down for maj. of day to replace gasket & float hose
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging inbnd Cut 11 traveling 329'. Low TE due to replacing gasket and a hole in the float hose. Dr. began digging in better material starting at 13+00 some shell but began stacking on Fill Site. Face of material has began to decrease to 7.3' as Dr. comes to end of cut. Dr. has a SS of 47.6fpm & a BS of 59fpm. Majority of delays were due to repairing float hose and gasket. MEC checked at 0425 1200.

BriefComments: Finished digging Cut 11 & dug into Cut 6. Began dig outbnd in Cut 12. Mat. predom. fine.
ExtendedComments: Dr. finished digging Cut 11 and continued into Quad. A Cut 6. Portion of 6 that was not completed was dug for 120'. Once Cut 6 was completed dr. moved to Cut 7 and dug down into Cut 12. Material has remained fine and face in these cut were low with and avg. of 5'. Dr. had a SS of 50.7fpm and BS of 56.2fpm. Delays were due to moving anchors & changing cuts. Misc delays were due to PLC computer being down and MEC checks at 0240 0730 0145 2000.

BriefComments: Began dig outbnd in Cut 12. Good TE at 85.4%. Mat. very fine trble stacking on beach.
ExtendedComments: Began digging outbnd in Cut 12 w BOS @ 23'. Material has remained very fine & the fill has had trouble stacking the material. Dr. traveled 1114' in a day with good TE @ 85.4%. Dr. had a SS of 64.3fpm and BS of 74.1fpm. Wx became bad in the afnoon dr. cont. to dig in 4-6' swell. Dr. went down to move anchors and checked MEC @ 0535 0845 1630 2345.

BriefComments: Stop digging at 010 due to seas. Began dig @ 0445 before going down again @ 1115
ExtendedComments: Dr. began day not digging due to rough seas. Swell was 4-6' high. Dr. was able to dig from 0445 to 1115 traveling 163' before going down due to seas. Material remained very fine. The dredge pumped water for the remainder of the day until sea conditions became suitable.Some of the material that was dug from 0445 to 1115 may have been washed off Fill Site due to dr. pumping water for the majority of the day.

BriefComments: Cont. digging outbnd in Cut 12 traveling 327' after replacing gasket. Mat. remains very fine
ExtendedComments: Dr. cont. to dig outbnd in Cut 12 w BOS of 23'. Dr. remained down most of the morning to fix a leak in the stern connection. The crew replaced the stern gasket & operations began at 1015. Production was good w and avg. of 2675CYwh. TE was low due to time down to replace the gasket. Material has remained very fine and dense when digging. The average dig face is 9.5' in the area that was traveled. The dredge was down to move anchors & to check the MEC @ 0830 1630 2140.

BriefComments: Fine Material. High face ~9'. Changed Cuts (3hrs);Swing Wire (2hrs);Anchorsx2(1.87hrs)
ExtendedComments: Dug 381' outbound in cut 12 with BOS at 22'. Beach reported a very fine material that does not stack well. At 1600 Dredge began washing out line to move to Cut 13. Travel 165' in Cut 13 with BOS @ 22' and increasing face. Avg face ~ 9'.Avg MP RPM = 290 RPM. Avg SSBS = 7680 fpm. Delays for change cuts (3hrs);fixing swing wire (2hrs);Anchors x2 (1.8hrs); Grease up & Change teeth (0.42hrs)

BriefComments: More med sand stacking better lowered DP. High face ~ 9' face. Anchors x 4 (2.91hrs)
ExtendedComments: Dug outbound 573' in Cut 13. BOS @ 22'. Improved material in Cut 13. More Med Sand more shell fragments and no silt is allowing the material to stack up on the beach. High face in BA (~9') and TE of 82.71% allowed production to meet estimate (2376 CYWH). Main Pump ~= 300 RPM. SSBS ~= 8798. Velocity ~=18.5 fps. Delays: Anchors x 4 (2.91 hrs);Clean Cutter (0.58 hrs);Grease up (0.33 hrs); Change teeth (0.33hrs).

BriefComments: Dug 251' in Cut 13 Moved to cut 14 & dug 403'. Lower face at start Cut 14 ~=5'.
ExtendedComments: Dredge Dug 251' outbound in Cut 13 before moving back to Cut 14 where she dug 403' outbound. There was low face at the beggining of Cut 14 (~=4.5') which lowered production for the day below the estimate. Material continues to improve. Current material is a Med sand with some shell fragments. Stacking well on beach. SSBS = 7985 fps. Delays: Change Cut (3.25 hrs); Shift Anchors x 3 (1.66 hrs);Clean Cutter x 2 (0.34 hrs);Dump (0.5 hrs).

BriefComments: Dug 597' outbound cut 14. Lower face Strb corner = low prod. face~= 4' Port & 8' Strb
ExtendedComments: Dug 597' outbound in cut 14 with BOS @ 22'. This cut offered lower face on the Strb side which borders the already dug access channel. The avg face for the Strb side of this cut was ~= 4'; The avg face for the Port side ~= 8'. High cutter and swing amps in stripcharts suggest that the material here is more dense. Material still stacking well on the beach. SSBS = 7588 fps.MP = 275 RPM.

BriefComments: Began diggin inbnd in Cut 10 at 1330 w BOS of 23'. Mat. cont. to be fine in the area.
ExtendedComments: Dr. was towed from Absecon Inlet to Great Egg Harbor Inlet after repairs were completed on the Cutter Shaft. The dr. was able to begin operations at 1330 digging inbnd in Cut 10. Dr. had a SS of 29.1fpm and a BS of 59.7fpm. Material cont. to be very fine in the area with an average face of 5.5'.

BriefComments: Cont. dig inbnd in Cut 10 travel 600' w a dig face of 7'. Mat. remains very fine.
ExtendedComments: Dr. continued digging inbound in Cut 10 traveling 600' wi a dig face of 7'. TE was very good at 81.3%. The material continued to be very fine. Dr. experienced high cutter amps due to the density of the material. Beach has had trouble stacking material on the beach. Dr. delays were due to moving anchors and cleaning the cutterchecking MEC at 0110 0650 1215 and 1830.

BriefComments: Dr. able to cover greater area than predicted due to lower face than shown in estimate.
ExtendedComments: Dr. continued digging to uncover brokenburied subline until 16:45. While digging dr. dug a majority of the time on its port side to reveal subline. Dr. was then towed to Cut 15 starting at STA 13+80 w BOS of 23'. DS was 2487cywh and BS was 1620cywh. Material in both cuts improved to predom. Med Sand. Delays were due to moving anchors & towing to cut 15. MEC checked at 0716 1320 1645.

BriefComments: Northbound Cut 15. Increasing face ~ 7'. Med-Fine sand stacking well. No Mj delays
ExtendedComments: Towed out to BA in morning but had to wait until tide shift for swells to calms down and make connection to riser. Began pumping at 16:20. Dug Northbound in Cut 15 towards the broken subline. BOS @ 22' 275' Swing width. Had to dig down some in begginning which affected production. At approx 23:00 a strong outgoing tide prevented good coverage and stunted production. SSBS ~= 72104 fps. Misc delay to check MEC.

BriefComments: Low DWH due to large swells and digging down in Cut13. Chg Cuts (5.08hrs). Dive (3.5hrs)
ExtendedComments: Cont. to dig inbound in Cut 15. Standby for divers at 08:30 (3.5hrs). Large swells lifted cutter off bottom and lowered production throughout day. Moved to Cut 13 @ 13:30 (5.08hrs) took longer to change cuts due to large swells. Once in Cut 13 the digging in process also lowered production. Poor TE is result of dive ops and large swells. Material in Cut 13 was reported as dense by levermen. Material in Cut 13 seems to be more fine than in Cut 15 but is still stacking on the beach. SSBS ~= 6582 fpm

BriefComments: Higher face (~9'). Lowered MP RPM to stop material running on beach. Finer Sand in cut 13
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig inbound in Cut 13 with BOS @ 22'. Material was a more fine sand. At 03:15 it was requested by the beach that the MP RPM be lowered (From ~280 to ~260 RPM). This reduced velocity pressure and ultimatley production but it prevented the fine material from running outside the pay templete on the beach. MP Pressure ~= 126psi. Velocity ~= 17.3 fps. DigWH 2002 cywh. SSBS ~= 7289 fps. TravelWH ~= 24 FTWH

BriefComments: Low face 3-4' Swells digging down in cut 14 & lowered RPM all reduced prod. & TE
ExtendedComments: Cont. dig inbound in cut 13 BOS @ 22. Very low face in last ~100 of cut - low production. Finished Cut 13 at 15:15 then moved to cut 14. 5'+ of shoaling at beginning of Cut 14 caused dredge to sit on ground and wait on tide to start digging. Shoaling also made dredge have to dig down to BOS depth for over an hour (reduced production). Large swells in BA made productive swinging difficult (high cutter and swing amps). low TE due to Tide x 2 (6.25 hrs) Change Swing Wire (1.58 hrs) CHhange Cuts (2 hrs)

BriefComments: Low face on toes (~5.5') MP RPM increased @ 8:45. Cutter blade found broken @ 21:45
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging inbound in Cut 14 towards the broken cutter head with BOS @ 22'. MP RPM increased to ~285 at 08:45. This increased production by about 400 cywh. Still lower production than estimate becasue of lower density due to low face on both toes of this cut (A result of both neighbor cuts already dug). At 17:10 the dredge hit something hard. Later the cutter was inspected and it was found that a single blade had begun to break off from the tip of the cutter. Believed to be concrete block

BriefComments: Began dig outbnd in Cut 18. Lower TE to wait on tide and avoidance area.
ExtendedComments: Began digging outbnd in Cut 18 w BOS of 23'. Short swings on stbd side between STA 17+00 to 16+00 due to opstruction found using magnetometer. Dr. was able to travel 520' in the day w a DigWH of 2562. Broken subline was removed in cuts 16 & 15. Another 1000' was removed from used subline w the riser now located in cut 21. Dr. was down 4.67 hours in the morning to wait on tide & another 3.92 to move anchors.

BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 18. high dig & Pay due to sea cond. med. sand stacking well on fill.
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging outbnd in Cut 18 travel 574'. High dig & pay due to good material. Mat. is stacking well on beach. Avg dig face of 9' & calm sea conditions allowed for high production. Fast travel and an area coverage of 159863 sq. ft. was due to favorable weather conditions. High TE due to few delays due to moving anchors changing teeth fill site and checking MEC screen.

BriefComments: Cont dig outbound. Vel lowered 16:15 to pump under pier. stacking well. no mj delays
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging outbound in cut 18 with 275' swing width and BOS at 22'. At approx. 16:15 the MP RPMs were lowered in order to decrease the velocity (~18 to 16.5 fps). This was done to help the dump pump material under the music pier on the beach. The material remained a Med sand with some shell fragments that stacked well on the beach. SSBS = 7298 fps. MP RPM lower from ~ 300 to 275 rpms. Misc. delay was to check MEC screen at 19:40.

BriefComments: Low density in AM pump under pier. Large swells reduced DWH. Change cuts (3.17hrs)
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging outbound in Cut 18 with BOS at 22'. Walked in to higher face (~10.5'). began double swinging in 8+ foot of face. Finish cut at 16:50 and moved to Cut 17 to begin digging outbound at sta 10+50 with BOS at 22'. Low face in first 200' of cut 17 where left off previously. SSBS = 7190 fps. Large swells (3-5') made it difficult to keep cutter head down to digging depth - Caused lowered production and high amps. Misc 0.17hr delay to Check MEC. Beach report more silt and fine but still stacking well

BriefComments: Cont. dig outbound Cut 17. Lower face for first 200' (~4') increasing to ~8' face.
ExtendedComments: Continued to dig outbound in cut 17. Traveled 552 ' with 80.9% TE. Low face in the morning sessioon of digging resulted in lowered production. The low face allowed a travel rate of 42 fthr. When the dredge walked into higher face (~8') she was only able to travel ~27 fthr. SSBS ~= 75105 ftmin. Delays included: Clean Cutter x 3 (1.83 hrs);Anchors (1.75 hrs);Grease up (1.0 hrs).

BriefComments: High face (~11') in cut 17. Low face (~4.5') in cut 16. Change cuts (2.75hrs).
ExtendedComments: Dug outbound in cut 17 to Sta 0+50. High face in Cut 16 (~11'). High face cause low travle rate (~27 fthour). Moved t Cut 16 at 13:15 (2.75 hr delay time). Cut 16 offered very low face (~4.5') which lowered the overall production for the day. Several hundred feet of Cut 16 was skipped and will go undug becasue it offers only 1-2' of face. BOS @ 22' MLW. Cut width = 275'. SSBS ~= 83107 fpm. Other delays included Moving anchors x 2 (1.25 hrs;Check Cutter & MEC (0.17 hrs).

BriefComments: Low face on port side. 4-6' swells. Out of anchor @1030 - down for weather (13.5hrs)
ExtendedComments: Cont. dig outbound in cut 16. Low face on port side at the beginning of the day. Rough seas (4-6') also casued low production. At 1030 the dredge ran out of anchors and the seas were too rough to move them. The Illinois was down for weather for the remainder of the day (13.5hrs).

BriefComments: Higher face (~7.5'). Large swells (4-6') reduced prod. TE affected by bad WX. Foggy.
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging out bound in Cut 16 with BOS @ 22' and swing width of 275'. Face availible was higher today as she walked into to ~ 7.5' of face. Large swells in BA (4-6') effected production of the dredge for the day. SSBS ~= 7395 fpm. Long delay in AM waiting on wether to calm to move anchors (8.75hrs). Other delays included Anchors x 2 (0.34hrs) and Changing Cuts (3.0hrs). Material Remains a MED Sand that is stacking very well on the beach.

BriefComments: Cut 16 ~5.5' face. Cut 19 ~ 8' face. Dig down to grade for 100' - low prod. Chg cut -4hr
ExtendedComments: Began digging outbound in Cut 15. Only dug small area of cut that offered ~5.5' face of material that shoaled in since the it was dug on 426. AT 10:45 we began digging down to grade in cut 19. The digging in process took 100' and lowered production. Once dug in the cut offered ~8' of face to be dug. Material is more MED sand with some shell fragments. Stacking very well on the beach and not running far. Change cut delay (4.0 hrs); Anchorswait on tide x 2 (3.16 hrs); Clean cutter x 2 (2.16 hrs)

BriefComments: Cont. dig outbnd in Cut 19 w high prod w face ~ 9'. Low DP due to mat. stacking well.
ExtendedComments: Cont. to dig outnd in Cut 19 traveling 473'. High face ~ 9' gave good production with predom. med. sand. Material is stacking well on beach making fast travel for fill site. Dr. began with short swings on port side due to avoidance area. Delays due to moving anchors and cleaning cutter still left good TE @ 78.2%

BriefComments: Cont. dig outbnd in Cut 19. Unable to move anchors due to wx caused low prod.
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging outbnd in Cut 19 traveling 285'. Dr. down for 9.91 hours due to wx. Dr. could not move anchors due to swell which caused low prod. and bad TE. Material remains to be pred. Med Sand with a face of ~ 11.5' and is stacking well on fill site. Amount of fine sand has increased compared to what has been previously dug.

BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 19. Lower D&P due to swell & ^ in fine material @ end of Cut 19.
ExtendedComments: Cont. to dig outbnd in Cut 19 traveling 365'. Material has more fines than earlier in the cut. Mat. is running some on the fill site but still stacking well. Large swells also affected prod. and the ability to swing affectively. Face is ~ 10.5'. Dr. down time predominetly due to moving anchors and waiting on tide to do so.

BriefComments: Finished Cut 19 and towed to Cut 20 & dig down to grade for 50' - low prod. Chg cut -5hr
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging cut 19 where material was finer than beginning of cut. Dr. had to lower velocity at 03:25 for fill site. Cut 19 was competed at 16:50 and preped. to move to beginning of Cut 20. Began dig at 21:50 & had to dig down for 50' which lowered production. Once dug in the cut offered ~9' of face to be dug. Material was predom. Med sand with some shell. Mat. was reported to be stacking very well on the beach.

BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 20. Very high prod. due to high face ~10' good mat. & calm seas
ExtendedComments: Cont. to dig outbnd in Cut 20 traveling 560' w a BOS of 22'. Production was exceptional for the day due to high face ~10' good mat. which was predom. medium sand and calm seas. Material remained medium with some shell fragments that stacked well on the beach. SSBS of 94.9112fpm. Little down time also accounted for good prod. giving a TE of 84.4%.Delays were predom. due to moving anchors & cleaning the cutter.

BriefComments: Cont. dig cut 20. High prod. due to high face ~ 11' calm seas & good material
ExtendedComments: Cont. dig outbnd in Cut 20 w BOS of 22'. Production was high due to predom. medium sand material and a high face of ~11'. Low prod. from 0355 to 0435 due to kink in float hose. Delays were predom. due to moving anchors and to clean the cutter. SSBS was 83.798.9fpm. Beach MEC inspector found suspicious object & made crew check MEC screen. Object was of no consequence after inspection.

BriefComments: Cont. to dig in Cut 20. High face ~ 12.5'. Finished project at 12:20. Began demob.
ExtendedComments: Cont. to dig outbnd in Cut 20. Material remained predom. med. sand with a face of ~12.5'. Calm seas caused good production. Dr. had to slow down prod. for 5.67hrs for Fill. Dr. began washing out at 12:20 after verification from Fill Site that the project had been completed. Dr. then started subjob 018 transition to Brigantine. Delays were due to moving anchors and a leak in the shore pipe.

BriefComments: Began digging @ 12:20 in Cut 3 w BOS of 23'. High face of ~15'
ExtendedComments: Dr. was towed from Ocean City and began digging in Brig. Inlet at 12:20. Dr. began digging at STA 27+27 & had to dig down very little due to previous project. Material is predom. medium sand with a mixture of fines. Reported to be stacking well on the beach. Delays due to Fill Site still preparing for start up.

BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 3. Calm seas and high face of ~15'. Travel of 338'
ExtendedComments: Dr. cont. digging inbound in Cut 3 w BOS of 23'. High face and calm seas caused high production. Avg. face of material was ~15' and predom. medium sand. Material was reported to be stacking well on beach. Dr. was able to travel 338' and move anchors twice throughout the day. Few delays due to moving anchors and waiting on Fill Site to move equipment.

BriefComments: Finish Cut 3 & towed to Cut 4. BOS of 23' with face of ~12'. Fast travel due to lower face.
ExtendedComments: Finished digging Cut 3 @ 1325 & began to wash out line. Dr. was towed to Cut 4 and began digging inbound at sta 22+00 @ 1705. Dr. had high face of material in cut 3 of ~ 15'. Lower face in Cut 4 ~12' and had to dig down to begin cut. Dr. was to complete large area & travel. This can be attributed to calm weather and lower face in Cut 4. Delays were due to moving anchors and changing cuts. Took crew 2.83 hrs to move from Cut 3 to Cut 4.

BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 4 w BOS of 23'. Lower face ~12.5' made for faster travel.
ExtendedComments: Cont. digging inbound in Cut 4 w BOS of 23'. Material is predom. medium sand & stacking well on beach. Dr. was able to cover large area due to smaller face than previous days of ~12.5'. Dr. had to clean cable and tires out of cutter near sta 26+00. Other delays were due to moving anchors and replacing 4 cutter teeth.

BriefComments: Cont. dig in Cut 4. High face of ~15' and delays made for slower travel.
ExtendedComments: Dr. continued to dig inbound in Cut 4 w a BOS of 23' traveling 365'. Dr. dug into higher face than previous day at ~14'. High face and rough seas caused slower travel. Dr. continues to dig trash ie. cables and tires causing delays to clean out the cutter. Other delays due to moving anchors changing teeth and an engine room repair to a valve.

BriefComments: Cont. dig cut 4. High dig face of ~16'. TE of 85%. Mat. predom. Med. sand.
ExtendedComments: Dr. continued to dig inbound in cut 4. Traveled 375' with dig face of ~16'. Materal remains predom. Med sand and is reported to be stacking well on the beach. Fill site was able to travel 625'. Delays due to moving anchors and checking cutter.Engine room over heated due to mussels collecting and blocking water from reaching the cooling system.

BriefComments: Dredge began digging in Cut 1A and moved to Cut 1B to find better material.
ExtendedComments: The material is fine black sand with a strong petrolium ordor. Calibrations have been performed on dredge prior to digging.Density gage is not functioning properly currently have someone on site to fix the instrument. Dredge has moved around to find sufficient material and is currently digging in Cut 1B.

BriefComments: The Dredge Illinois was moved to station 45+00 and began to dig in Cut 3B.
ExtendedComments: The material has improved since the dredge was moved to the new location in the Borrow Area.

BriefComments: Dump reports better material this day sand stacking up. Down 4.58hrs for swing shaft
ExtendedComments: CSD IL is dredging a 240' cut primarily in cut B swinging 40' into cut A. Dump continues to report improved material more fine sand and material is stacking up better. Major delays today include the swing shaftgetting to hot - 4.58hrs down. Long delay to move anchors 3hrs due to the anchor barge being down. The dredge is seeing large amounts of debris in the cutter main pump and UWP. Primarily wood - 2x delay to clean main pump 2x delay to clean cutter 1x to clean UWP.

BriefComments: IL started swinging 275' wide following 18' contour into Area A. 4.25hrs on dump 3x.
ExtendedComments: CSD IL continued dredging in cuts A and B this day. The dredge started swinging a 275' wide cut this morning. Around station 34+50 the dredge started following the 18' contour on the PORT side into cut A. The dredge is swinging approx. 100ftmin day levermen taking 3ft steps in each corner night leverman taking 1ft5ft steps on average. MiscOther delay 2.17hr for weather on the dump thunderstorms and lightning forced them to shutdown. 5.33hr mechanical for working on the swing shaft.

BriefComments: 275' wide cut following 18' contour. High face across cut material coming in from slopes
ExtendedComments: IL continued dredging 275' wide cut across cuts A and B with high face on either side and material flowing in from the slopes to increase production. As the dredge progressed in the cut this day the face evened out to approx. 5' insurvey across the cut. Levermen dropped the ladder down from 25' to 26.5' and started doing extra cleans to try to take more material in the higher face surveys show the dredge is leaving approx. 22'. 9.08hrs total delay for the dump 5x this day. 0.42hr eng. room gland seal hose.

BriefComments: Continue dredging in high face across the cut 4x rock stops 2.17hrs 2x dump for 5.9hrs
ExtendedComments: IL continued dredging 275' wide cut across cuts A and B with high face on either side and material flowing in from the slopes to increase production. Levermen dropped the ladder down from 25' to 26.5' and started doing extra cleans to try to take more material in the higher face surveys show the dredge is leaving approx. 22'. Stripcharts show the dredge is averaging 100ftmin swing speed and the levermen are taking 4-5' sets primarily doubly swinging.

BriefComments: 3x clean pump 2.33hrs (rocks) 3x clean cutter 1.17hrs (junk). 3.17hrs change cuts
ExtendedComments: IL continued dredging outbound swinging 275' wide cut 100fpm swing speed dredging around 26.5' deep taking 4-5' steps. At station 25+85 the dredge exhausted floatline and had to pull backturn around to station 45+00. The dredge is still swinging 275' wide cut face has dropped off (approximately 6' less face in this cut) ladder at 24.5'. Dump reports very fine material that is flowing off the beach no pipe added on the beach after moving to the new cut. 0.5hrs engine room delay for lost main gen.

BriefComments: Bad fill materialdark silty smells like petroleum. Moved IL to dig Cut C late afternoon
ExtendedComments: IL dredging inbound 275' wide cut with the ladder at 25' continue taking 4-5' steps double swinging average swing speed 100fpm. Reclamation is reporting material to be very fine flowing off the beach. Got permission for IL to dig cut C this morning dredge had to wait until the afternoon for high tides to spin around and dig outbound into cut C around station 45+00. Clean MP 5x 3.25hrs rocks & wood. Clean cutter 3x 1.58hrs trash. Dump delay due to only 2 working dozers trying to mobilize local rentals.

BriefComments: 14.92hrs dump delay 7x. Due to dozer breakdown only 2 working dozers.
ExtendedComments: IL dredging outbound in rockaway inlet. Swinging 275' wide cut avg swing speed 100fpm ladder at 25' taking 3-4' steps. The dredge is swinging between Cut C (200') and Cut B (75') this area of Cut B is previously dredged with 19-20' existing ground. Cut C insurvey shows depths of 6-8' with the large change in face the dredge is double-triple swinging the cut C area to take as much face as possible while only swinging the 75' into Cut B every other step to avoid overdredging this area.

BriefComments: Dredge digging outbound in Rockaway Inlet swinging 200' in Cut C and 75' in Cut B
ExtendedComments: The dredge has previously dug in Cut B leaving an average face of 19-20'. The Dredge is swinging 75' to the port to clear remaining material to grade.The ladder is digging at 25' while taking 3-4' steps. Dredge crew cleaned cutter head and changed one tooth due to rocks. At Station 4140 in the Borrow Area the dump began to recieve muddy material.The dredge had to slow the velocity to build material on the dump.

BriefComments: Dredge Illinois continues digging outbound in Cut C swinging 275'.
ExtendedComments: Dredge is swinging 75' wide into Cut B on port side where it has previously dug and left an average face of 19-20' of material.The Dredge is digging at 25.5' taking three to five foot steps. Dredge was down for 5.33 hours for beach crew to break back shore pipe to pump on STA 70+00 to 65+00. The Dredge had an hour delay to clean the cutter and replace two teeth due to rocks in cutter. Dredge was delayed 1.92 hours to move all five anchors in Borrow Area.

BriefComments: The Dredge was down for 4.75 hours for the dump to Yvalves.
ExtendedComments: The Dredge Illinois continues digging 200' in Cut C and swinging 75' into Cut B. The dredge is digging at 25.5' while taking three to five foot steps. There was a 1.08 hour delay to clean the cutter and replace two teeth. There was a 2.41 hour delay to clean main pump due to rocks in material.

BriefComments: The Dredge was down 4x for dump for a total of 12.24 hours of delay
ExtendedComments: An hour dump delay was to wash out the line. During the 7.83 hr delay for the dump dredge crew replaced the service water suction pipe and added one 780' piece of subline making the total subline length 12464'. The dredge was down for 0.78 hours to clean main pump due to rocks.The Dredge Illinois continues digging 200' in Cut C and swinging 75' into Cut B. The dredge is digging at 25.5' while taking three to five foot steps.

BriefComments: Dump delays 4x for a total of 12.24 hours 1.75 hr delay to clean main pump due to rocks
ExtendedComments: Engine room delay for 0.83 hr.Due to electrial problems with battery pack PLC cabinet and gyro lost power several times during the evening. PLC cabinet was able to get power back and contine working. Gyro is not working properly looking into solutions to fix the issue.The Dredge continues to dig outbound in Rockaway Inlet digging in Cut C swinging 200' in Cut C and 75' in Cut B. The dredge is removing on average 12-16' of material in Cut C and 4' of material in Cut B.

BriefComments: Dump delay 3x adding pipe for 3.75 hrs and delayed 3x to addmove Y-valve for 10.5 hrs
ExtendedComments: Dredge was delayed 2 hours to clean main pump and replace 1 tooth. The Dredge Illinois continued to dig in Cut C swinging 200' in Cut C and 75' into Cut B.When the dredge reaches station 26+50 in Cut C it will move 275' to the port to continue swinging in Cut A where it has last dug on September 15th 2013.

BriefComments: Dump delays 5x 3 delays for dump to catch up for 4.5 hrs 1 delay to add pipe for 1.33hr
ExtendedComments: 1 dump delay to add Yvalve for 3.83 hrs.Yesterday dredge crew performed man overboard drill as well as a fire drill.Dredge is digging in Cut A starting at station 26+50 and continues to dig outbound.Dredge is swinging 200' in Cut A and swinging 75' wide to the starboard side in Cut B.The dredge is digging an average dig face of 10 feet.

BriefComments: Delays on dump 5x 4.74 hrs for dump to catch up 7.5 hours to move Yvalves
ExtendedComments: Dredge was delay 1 hour to move anchors 1 hour to clean cutter and change 4 teeth and 1.17 hours for choke in main pump.The dredge continues to dig in Cut A swinging 275' swinging wide to the starboard side.The dredge on average is taking 9' of dig face. Chris Slimmer was on site trouble shooting the electrical problems the dredge was experiencing on September 23rd.All equipment is functioning properly after changes were made.

BriefComments: Delays on dump 7x for 13.1 hrs 6.26 hrs for catchup 5.42 hrs to move Y-valves
ExtendedComments: Dredge was delayed on dump for 0.67 hrs reattach shore pipe and 0.75 hrs to fix leak in shore pipe.Other dredge delays include 0.75 hrs to move anchors and 0.5 hrs to wash line. The Dredge continues dig to Cut A swinging 275' outbound 200' in Cut A and swinging wide 75' into Cut B.On average taking 8.5' of dig face.Dredge will be moved back during high tide to Cut C at STA 26+50 due to float line limitations.

BriefComments: Dredge delayed due to Engine Room for 7 hrs and dump for 6.92 hrs.
ExtendedComments: IL went down around 1700 hours due to generator failure.Crew continues to troubleshoot until technician arrives onsite.Repositioned dredge from Cut A and Cut B to Cut B and Cut C starting at STA 26+00to continue digging outbound once systems are back online. Cutter head was cleand and replaced 10 teeth due to daily wear.

BriefComments: Dump broke back switched to subjob 042 at 1700
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued to dig 275' wide cut into Cuts B and C swinging 150' in Cut C and 125' into Cut B and taking 3-5' steps with an average ladder depth of 23.6'. Leverman reports hitting rock and moved the ladder depth to 22' and was able to lower ladder back down once clear of rock.Dredge has completed pumping to dump and is in process of washing lines.

BriefComments: Completed pumping to pier. Finished job at 1700
ExtendedComments: Dredge continued to dig 275' wide cut into cuts B and C swinging 150' in cut C and 125' into cut B taking 3-5' steps with ladder depth at 23'. Most delays were for dump to move material under pier and meet template. Average dig face for today was 9.55'. Post survey shows dredge is leaving approx. 4' material.

BriefComments: Increased ground swells restict production. BOS @ 7' below existing grd.varies
ExtendedComments: Max depth being that of 7ft below existing leverman cross-sections reflects that of exisiting grade. With help from SE the ladder depth varies as dictated by BD cross-sections; 7ft of tolerance is being maximized as appropriate given current sea state. Dredge IL continues to dig in BA 1 Cut 6 making one pass with variable ladder depth 3-5ft steps swinging at total +-280ft (all of Cut 6).

BriefComments: Illinois digs 3.83hrs before 3-4ft seas requires shutdown. Digging Resumes @ 1350hrs
ExtendedComments: Sea state handicaps TE on the Illinois; 10rev.hrs lost to SJ070. Step size increased by a foot as material and encountered face allows; dig pattern remains the same: Cut6 275' swing and BOS@7ft below existing. While digging IL's maintains: ~4000cyhr vel.18.2fps swng.spd.- 88fpm w cutter amps avg'ing 893. Check lines run to verify dig pattern & leave depths heave compensator issues limited the quantityquality of data but verification possible.

BriefComments: Ladder raised to 57' encountering bank. Chk surveys show leaving 3' from 10'face
ExtendedComments: IL works to complete CUT 6 digging inbound from BOS where excavated depth will be 7ft below BD. Check surveys indicate spillage of <30%; BOS varies with grade.

BriefComments: Ladder raised 1' until survey can be complete. Currently digging 6' of face.
ExtendedComments: IL completed Cut 6 at 0555 hrs and began digging in Cut 5 at 1040 hrs. The dredge continues to dig inbound swinging 275' with 5' steps. Excavated depth is 7' below the BD. BOS varies with grade. Delays for the day included 4.17 hrs to change cuts 0.58 hrs waiting on dump to move y-valves and 1.42 hrs to shift anchors.

BriefComments: Narrow porition of beach passed digging inbound in CUT 5;swing 285' 1pass5'step
ExtendedComments: Dump Delay Extended: .92hrs piping across narrow portion of beach (sta289-291).25wash-out2.6 breaking off Y-valve.08tending leak1.19adding pipe2hrs install addtional Y-valve-; dring periods of down time dredge crew replaced two teeth & moved anchors. Peak production levels ~avgd.2800cyhr @ 19fps cutter rpm 30 low swng amps ~174 sustaining a density of 1.2. Narrow portion of beach 10CYLF @ 300'.

BriefComments: Completed Cut 5 relocated to Cut 4 inbound. Down for major repairs inport.
ExtendedComments: Cut 5 was completed at 1245 repositioned and commenced digging in Cut 4 at 1600 and digging inbound swinging 285' with 5' steps.Dig instruction was updated to drop the ladder one foot and take 10' of face since surveys show 3' of material left.At 2400 a liner bolt was displaced from the main pump.Normal wear and tear appears to be root cause approximately 1000000cy of material has been through the pump since last rebuild. Crews are in process of towing dredge to marina.

BriefComments: Main pump repairs completed recommenced digging at 1655
ExtendedComments: Departed Shinnecock Inlet at 1310 and resumed digging inbound at 1655 in Cut 4 275'swings w5' steps. Leverman background updated with colored arcs as to indicate ladder depth for patricular travel lifting ~.5' at each interval; cross section reflects finish grade(BD -7); stbd.swing limits shifted as to maintain face ( avoid swinging into Cut 5's port boundary-open water).

BriefComments: 9.41hrs of dig in Cut 4 before weather delays.
ExtendedComments: Sea state handicaps TE on the Illinois; 9.17rev.hrs lost to SJ070.During inclement weather dredge was pushed approximately 450' out of cut by seas. Hydro survey conducted for beach AD on Sta 296+00 - 304+00; CND Sta 305+00 - 310+00.Spreader location:Sta 303+00 low 308+00 high.

BriefComments: Resume digging in Cut 4 @ 1525 15.41hrs Wxdelay accounted for in SJ070
ExtendedComments: Levermen report varriable ladder depth mid-swing troublesome as such low dig face due to profile across cut. Working on compromise to achieve consistent face. Digging inbound 285'swing 5'steps and single pass. With proceeding cuts to the port shifting cuts was necessary as to avoid loosing face on stbd swing as Cut 5's over swing consumed matl. from Cut 4's stbd swing. Enhanced production and S.Charts indicate success of shift.

BriefComments: Completed digging in Cut 4 shifted to Cut 3.
ExtendedComments: Completed Cut 4 at 0715 and began digging in Cut 3 at 1100. The dredge continues to dig inbound swinging 285' with 4-5' steps.Survey cross-sections show excavated depth is 7' below the BD. BOS varies with grade with color coded arcs on the Hydraulic Positioning Computer for the levermen to follow for depth. Delays for the day included 3.75hrs to change cuts 2.42hrs waiting on dump to move y-valves and 1.25hrs to shift anchors.

BriefComments: Heavier material being encountered smaller steps maintain velocity from~5 - ~3
ExtendedComments: Digging Cut 3 inbound where BOS is 10ft below exsting grd. 275ft swings with buffer in prt and stbd. corners. Ladder depth with respect to p.tides & directives from engineers via color coded background on leverman's screen indicating 10ft of face per segment of travel. Leverman reporting heavey line with 5ft steps and drops in velocity. Approx. sta. 5+00. Step sized now avging 3' to sustain16fps. Previous day velocity avging >18fps. S.charts indicate material change; matl. not running as readily. mid swing.

BriefComments: Continue to dig inbound in Cut 2.
ExtendedComments: Dump progressed 800' with continued quality material.Leverman continues to vary ladder depth at .5ft based on BD data and color codes on Hydraulic Positioning Computer and dig instructions.Currently have not encountered the heavier material that was experienced in Cut 3 around this Station. G.L. 103 repairs were completed around 1600 however G.L. 107 continued to be utilized until 116.Beach and dredge coordinated down time better.8 teeth replaced.

BriefComments: Completed digging inbound in Cut 2 and began digging inbound in Cut 1 at 1730 hrs
ExtendedComments: Dump progressed 500' with continued quality material. Leverman continues to vary ladder depth at .5ft based on BD data and color codes on Hydraulic Positioning Computer and dig instructions. At 1730 hrs the dredge moved into Cut 1 digging inbound maintaining the same dig pattern as in Cut 2. While digging the IL is averaging: 3495 CY Hr Vel. 18.4 fps Swing speed of 74 fpm and Avg. Cutter Amp of 975.

BriefComments: Completed digging inbound in Cut 1 and began digging inbound in Cut 13 at 1430 hrs
ExtendedComments: Dump progressed 900' with continued quality material. Leverman began varying ladder depth at 1ft based on BD data and color codes on Hydraulic Positioning Computer and dig instructions. Dredge is digging with BOS at 3ft below the cross section to allow 10ft of dig face. While digging the IL is averaging: 3673 CY Hr Vel. 18.4 fps Swing speed of 67 fpm and Avg. Cutter Amp of 1149.

BriefComments: Dredge continues digging in Cut 13. Down for weather at 2115 hrs
ExtendedComments: Dump progressed 450' with continued quality material. Leverman continues varying ladder depth at 1ft based on BD data and color codes on Hydraulic Positioning Computer and dig instructions. Dredge is digging with BOS at 3ft below the cross section to allow 10ft of dig face while averaging 3235 CYWH. At 2115 hrs the dredge went down for rough seas. Conditions are expected to worsen throughout the day on 1110.

BriefComments: Dredge down in AM for rough sea's
ExtendedComments: Dredge resumed digging at 10:00 after being shut down for rough sea's. Spent a total of 1.33hrs pumping water for the Y-Valve on the beach. The dredge traveled 415' throughout the day with an estimated production of 31250 cy for the day. The 1.33hr engine room delay is accumulated from the port main engine tripping and changing the air line rotor seal on the port clutch.

BriefComments: Under Water Pump impeller requires replacement dredge in Shinnecock Inlet
ExtendedComments: The dredge began the day continuing to dig in Cut 14 inbound with BOS at 3ft below the cross section to allow 10ft of dig face. Positioning computer went down at 0315 and dump site and dredge crew were able to complete changing 6 teeth and move Y-valves during down time until computer was back up.At approximately 1245 UWP impeller failed and dredge was towed into port for maintenance.

BriefComments: Dredge under tow at 0750 back into BA#1 Cut 12.
ExtendedComments: Leverman reported issue with Hydraulic Positioning Computer after first cut.Possible issue with Port Friction wirereel causing dredge to shift ~40' off centerline when swinging to Stbd.Evening Leverman reported that manual gage and depth on screen are not matching expected.Levermen were directed to use manual gage readings until survey. Survey cross-sections show that computer depth was accurate and manual gage is incorrect causing overdepth of 2' average since 1900. Back to computer depths for dig

BriefComments: Continue digging inbound in Cut 12.Dump delay 4.42 mainly moving Y-vlvs
ExtendedComments: Survey cross-sections showed overdig of 4' when leverman was using manual gage and when previous leverman used computer depths the dig was at 7'. Levermen directed to use computer depths and colored arc on Hydraulic Positioning Computer.Raised ladder 1' for remainder of Cut 12 to dig 9' of face and removing 6' of material so that material can fill back into OD dig.

BriefComments: Completed cut 12 began cut 11 digging outbound. 4 hrs of delay related to changing cuts
ExtendedComments: Completed cut 12 digging at 9'.Moved the dredge to cut 11 digging outbound due to the possiblity of breast and swing anchors interferring with subline.Digging to 10'.The crew worked on repairing the hauling gear at the stern during the move to cut 11 as well as another half hour delay to replace eye bolt.Shore crew moved Y valves while changing cuts.

BriefComments: Con'd digging outbound in cut 11.4.92hrs of delay related to dump operations.
ExtendedComments: The Dr. Illinois continued digging outbound in cut 11.The dump moved the Y valve down the beach for 2.25hrs while the Illinois greased the ladder and winches checked the cutter and replaced 13 cutter teeth.

BriefComments: Completed cut 11 moved to cut 15 continuing to dig outbound.
ExtendedComments: The dredge Illinois continued completed digging in cut 11 around noon and moved to cut 15 again digging outbound.The line was flushed twice throughout the day to prevent it from becoming overloaded.

BriefComments: Continue in Cut 15 outbound delays at dump for shore piping.
ExtendedComments: Breaking down subline to provide dump with more piping and allow Borrow Area #1 to contine providing down to the breach.

BriefComments: Cnt digging Cut4 outbound beach pumping taper near Sagaponack Pond.
ExtendedComments: Delays include 3.54 hrs for dump to move y-valves (2x) wash the line. Change in DigPay ratio from 1.01 to 1.03 due to pumping taper near Sagaponack Pond. Plan to move to Cut 3 and dig STA 935 - 1200 after completeing Cut 4.Continue making 4-6' steps with average swing speed of 73 fpm by the nightime foreman and 100 fpm by the day foreman.

BriefComments: 13.75hr weather dly assigned to SJ070. Finished Cut4 move to Cut3 @ 2300.
ExtendedComments: Shutdown for weather from 04:15-16:00; swells to big to keep ladder on the bottom of cut. Finished Cut 3 traveling 305' then moved to Cut 4 to finish 265' of cut. Cutter Amps continueing to spike during digging reaching a max of 2230 and averaging 923. Average cutter speed for night leverman is 76 and avg for daytime leverman is 91 based on 2hr strip chart analysis. Plan to swing the riser Northward so dredge can move into Cut 5 digging outbound upon completing Cut 4.

BriefComments: Completed Cut 3 and beach Subjob 060.
ExtendedComments: Completed pumping to Beach STA 178+00 - 186+00 and had to stop several times for dump to break down pipe back to STA 174+00 - 177+00 and repump to several areas that were lacking material on slopes.Washed out lines at 1200 to move to Cut 5 and allow beach to break down and pump towards the east for Subjob 050.
